title: easy cookies
directions: Mix together.
You may add chips, nuts, M&M's, etc.
Drop with teaspoon on cookie sheet, about 1-inch apart.
Cook 12 to 15 minutes or until brown in 350° oven.

title: southern fried corn
directions: Cut corn from cob.
(Cut top grain, then scrape cob with knife.)
Combine sugar, salt, flour and pepper and add to corn, mixing well.
Add water and mix well.
Heat bacon drippings in skillet over medium to low heat.
Add corn mixture, cooking slowly until creamy (about 10 minutes).
Stir continuously.
Remove from heat and add a little butter if desired.

title: soft sugar cookies
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, then milk.
Sift flour, salt, soda and baking powder together.
Add slowly to the mixture.
Drop by teaspoons on greased cookie sheets.
Sprinkle with plain or colored sugar.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.

title: virginia chunk sweet pickles
directions: *Or use what you have; any nice solid cucumber makes a nice pickle.

title: quick chicken pie
directions: Boil chicken; remove from bone and chop.
Add cream of chicken soup and broth by pouring over the chicken.
Mix milk, margarine and flour.
Pour over chicken.
Bake at 350° until brown.

title: blueberry salad
directions: Dissolve jello in 2 cups boiling water.
Drain blueberries and pineapple.
Keep juices from both.
Add enough water to the juices to equal 1 1/2 cups of liquid; add to jello.
When jello thickens, add blueberries and pineapple.
Chill until firm.
Combine remaining ingredients (cream cheese, sour cream, sugar and vanilla); beat well.
Spread over jello.
Sprinkle top with pecans.
Chill.

title: smoky corn chowder
directions: In saucepan cook onion in butter or margarine until tender, but not brown.
Blend in flour, salt and pepper.
Add milk all at once.
Cook and stir until thickened and bubbly.
Stir in sausage and corn.
Simmer 10 minutes.

title: sweet & sour chicken(microwave)
directions: In a large shallow baking dish, place chicken in single layer.
In bowl, mix together salad dressing, soup mix and preserves.
Pour over chicken.
Bake, uncovered, 9 minutes per pound.

title: asparagus au gratin
directions: Wash asparagus and snap off ends.
Cut diagonally into 2-inch pieces.
Blanch in boiling water for 1 minute.
Drain.
Blanch peas for 1 minute to heat through.

Mix half and half, green onions, onion, tomato, bay leaf and clove in a small saucepan. Simmer, uncovered, for about 10 minutes to reduce by one-third. Sprinkle half of the bread crumbs on the bottom of a buttered 9-inch square baking dish.
Spread asparagus evenly over the bottom, then peas.
Remove bay leaf and clove from mixture.
Pour over the peas.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper, then top with Parmesan cheese and remaining bread crumbs.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes at 375°.

title: stuffed chicken cutlets
directions: Prepare Stove Top stuffing.
For each chicken cutlet put 1 tablespoon of stuffing in middle, roll and put in toothpicks to keep closed.
Dip in egg, then in bread crumbs.
Brown on all sides.
Put in separate pan.
When all cutlets have been browned, pour cream of chicken soup over it and cover pan with aluminum foil.
Bake in oven for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: kathryn's taco soup
directions: Great for a large group on a cold day!

title: pork and rice supper
directions: In a skillet over medium heat, melt butter with oil.
Add celery, onion and green pepper.
Saute until tender.
Remove vegetables to small bowl.
Add more butter to skillet, if needed. Add pork cubes, cooking until pink color is gone.
Do not cook very brown.
Remove meat.

title: cozy lime chicken
directions: In small bowl, mix lime juice and olive oil.
Dip each chicken part in mixture, covering completely.
On foil-lined baking pan, arrange chicken in single layer.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper. Arrange oven rack at least 6 inches from heat and set temperature at broil (450°).
Broil chicken about 15 minutes; turn and pour remaining lime-oil mixture over chicken.
Continue to broil about 15 minutes more or until fork can be inserted in chicken with ease.
Pour mushrooms in butter from can over chicken and return to oven for about 2 minutes or until mushrooms are hot.

title: butter creams
directions: Grease a large platter and set aside until cooking is complete.
In a large heavy pot, mix and cook mixture.
Stir continuously until mixture begins to cook.
When mixture begins to cook, put candy thermometer in pot and cook to soft ball.
At soft ball, pour on platter and allow to cool.
Beat until mixture reaches balling consistency.
Ball and coat with coating chocolate.

title: taco burgers
directions: In a large bowl, combine soup mix, ground beef, green pepper, tomato and chili powder.
Shape into burgers.
Grill until done. Serve with shredded lettuce and Monterey Jack cheese.

title: grandma's split pea soup
directions: Place peas in enough water to cover peas. Add ham bone, onion, carrot, celery, salt and pepper. Bring to a boil and cover and simmer for 1 1/2 to 2 hours until peas are soft. Blend soup so that it is smooth and creamy. Before serving, add water if necessary.

title: hash brown potato casserole
directions: Bring to a boil chicken soup and margarine.
Add sour cream, cheese, onion and hash browns.
Pour into baking dish; may top with seasoned bread crumbs, if desired.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Cook hamburger; drain.
Put in a casserole dish.
Put onions on top of hamburger.
Mix 1/2 cup milk with cream of chicken soup. Put on top of onions.
Cover with Tater Tots.
Bake 30 minutes at 300° or until brown.

title: tropical cheese spread
directions: Combine softened cream cheese and pineapple, mixing until well blended.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Chill.

title: western stew
directions: Shred cabbage; add sugar, celery seed, salt and pepper. Combine oil and vinegar.
Bring to a boil in a small sauce pan and pour over cabbage; refrigerate.

title: mulled cider
directions: Add all ingredients to saucepan.
Heat until mix starts to boil.
Cover.
Reduce heat and simmer 10 minutes.

title: tabbouleh
directions: Wash the crushed wheat and squeeze out the excess water.
Add 1/4 cup lemon juice and refrigerate for at least 1 hour.
(The longer the better.)
Mix the garlic, onion, parsley and spices all together in the oil and set it aside in the refrigerator.

title: chocolate drop cookies
directions: Beat butter and sugar until creamy.
Add eggs and vanilla. In separate bowl, stir in flour, cocoa, baking soda and salt. Gradually add butter mixture.
Stir in chips.

title: barbecue
directions: Brown the meat and onions.
Add the rest of the ingredients and simmer for 1 hour.

title: mound cake with coconut filling and icing
directions: Mix all ingredients. Pour into 3 pans. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: quick root beer
directions: Put everything in a gallon jug and add warm water.
Set in the sun for 5 to 7 hours.
Put into the refrigerator until cold.

title: dill dip
directions: Mix all ingredients well and chill.
Good served with potato chips or crackers.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs and milk and beat.
Add dry ingredients.
Fold in blueberries.
Bake in cupcake cups at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: fruit salad with sour cream
directions: Mix together fruit, marshmallows and coconut.
Toss lightly with sour cream.
Serve as a fruit salad.
(Fruit cocktail may be used instead of orange slices and pineapple.)

title: friendship tea mix
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large bowl, stirring and mixing well. Store mix in an airtight container.

title: add anything cookies
directions: Cream Crisco and sugars.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Add dry ingredients.
Then mix in the 3 cups of anything.
Drop rounded teaspoons onto cookie sheet.

title: norwegian pancakes
directions: Beat eggs until light and fluffy.
Add salt and sugar.
Stir well. Add flour and milk gradually.
Mix.
Pour thin coating into large frying pan over medium heat.

title: carrot cake
directions: Beat first 3 ingredients.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bake in a 350° oven for 45 minutes in a greased pan or two 8 x 8-inch pans.

title: cream puffs or eclairs
directions: Place boiling water, butter and salt in heavy saucepan; stir over heat.
When mixture boils vigorously, add sifted flour all at once, stirring briskly.
Stir constantly until dough forms soft ball and leaves sides of pan.
Do not overcook.
Remove from fire and turn into mixing bowl.
Cool 2 minutes.
Beat in eggs 1 at a time, beat briskly until mixture thickens and becomes stiff.
Drop from spoon onto ungreased cookie sheet; leave 2-inch space to spread.
Bake in very hot oven, 450° for 15 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350° and bake 20 to 25 minutes.
When cold, cut top off and fill center with whipped cream and replace top.

title: egg puff
directions: Beat eggs. Add ingredients in order given.
Place in square or rectangular baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Serves 20 to 24.
Also good for hors d'oeuvre.

title: lettuce and strawberry salad
directions: Mix all but dressing in large roaster. Just before serving, add bottled dressing to taste. Transfer to large salad bowl. Serves 12.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together (except crackers).
Put crushed cheese crackers on top and bake at 400° for about 20 minutes.

title: fruit and marshmallow salad
directions: Combine the fruit, nuts, marshmallows and salad dressing; fold in the Cool Whip.
Chill about 2 hours.

title: baked pork chops
directions: Trim fat from pork chops.
Melt into 3 tablespoons fat.
Brown chops in the fat.
Layer chops and sliced onion in casserole dish. Mix water, soup, catsup, Worcestershire sauce and seasoning.
Pour over the pork chops.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Makes 6 servings.

title: miniature cheese cakes
directions: Put 24 cupcake liners in cupcake pans.
Place vanilla wafer in each.
In medium bowl, beat the cream cheese, sugar, eggs, lemon juice and vanilla until fluffy.
Fill liners 3/4 full of mixture. Bake in preheated oven for 15 to 20 minutes.
Top each with cherry pie filling.
Chill.

title: brown rice
directions: Melt margarine in glass casserole dish.
Stir in soups and rice.
Cover; bake for 1 hour at 325°.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: ham and cheese quiche
directions: Thaw pie shells.
Bake for about 5 minutes.
In a large bowl beat eggs and milk.
After pie shells have baked for 5 minutes, layer bottom of both pie shells with ham, cheese, onion and mushrooms.
Pour egg mixture into pie shells.
This mixture will fill two pie shells.
Bake at 425° for 15 minutes.
Lower oven temperature to 300° and continue baking 45 to 60 minutes or until knife inserted in center comes out clean.

title: pecan cheese crackers
directions: Combine cheese and butter; cream thoroughly.
Add cayenne pepper, flour and pecans.
Mix thoroughly.
Shape into rolls. Wrap in wax paper or aluminum foil.
Refrigerate overnight.
Slice 1/4-inch thick and bake in 350° oven for 12 to 15 minutes.
Do not brown.

title: chocolate oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix sugar, cocoa, butter and milk in a saucepan and bring to a full boil; cook for 2 minutes longer.
Remove from heat and add rest of ingredients.
Mix thoroughly and drop by teaspoons on waxed paper.
Will be ready in about 5 minutes.

title: banana punch
directions: Combine sugar and water.
Heat until sugar is dissolved; cool. Blend bananas and orange juice until smooth; add 3 cans of water. Combine all ingredients except the ginger ale.
Pour into 3 (1/2 gallon) milk cartons or 3 gallon sized Ziploc bags and freeze. Take out of freezer at least 1 hour ahead of time.
Place in punch bowl.
Pour ginger ale over the punch before serving time.
This makes a slush.
You may float fresh fruit or frozen fruit on the top.
Serves 50 to 60.

title: rhubarb jam
directions: Mix rhubarb, water and sugar.
Cook until tender, then add jello.
Keeps well in freezer.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Bake empty pie crust for 5 minutes. Remove and set aside.
Turn oven back to 325°.
In saucepan, melt chocolate and margarine.
Add sugar and vanilla.
Beat and add eggs (one at a time).
Pour into pie shell and bake at 325° for about 30 minutes or until top begins to crack slightly.
Serve topped with whipped cream or ice cream.

title: patience candy
directions: Put 2 cups sugar and milk on to boil.
In a heavy skillet, put 1 cup sugar and caramelize it slowly.
(Heat until melted and light brown.)
Then add to the other sugar and milk.
Add it slowly so it will not boil over, stirring constantly.
Continue cooking to the soft boil when dropped into cold water.
Remove from heat.
Add salt, nuts, butter and vanilla and beat until creamy.
Pour into a well-greased pan to cool.
Cut into squares.

title: quick corn relish
directions: In a medium saucepan, combine vinegar, sugar, celery seed, mustard, salt and Tabasco sauce.
Simmer 2 minutes.
Add corn, green pepper, pimento and onion.
Simmer 2 more minutes. Remove to bowl. Cover and chill several hours or overnight.
Makes about 2 cups or 6 servings.

title: hominy casserole
directions: Saute onion in margarine. Mix soup, Cheez Whiz and onion. Pour over hominy. Bake at 325° for 30 minutes in covered dish. Uncover. Top with crushed Fritos. Bake 15 minutes.

title: carrot salad
directions: Combine jello, boiling water and marshmallows in small pan. Heat until dissolved.
Cool long enough to pour over the cream cheese which has been mixed well with the drained pineapple.
Set aside.

title: golden fruit punch
directions: Combine juices and water; cover and chill.
Pour into punch bowl.
Slowly pour ginger ale down
side of bowl, then stir gently.
Scoop sherbet on top.
Makes 24 (4 ounce) servings.

title: sweet monkey bread
directions: Sprinkle pecans evenly in bottom of well greased bundt pan. Combine white sugar and cinnamon.
Cut biscuits into quarters. Roll in sugar mixture and layer in pan over pecans.
Combine margarine, brown sugar and water; heat to boiling and pour over dough.
Bake at 350 degrees for 25 minutes or until golden brown. Let cool 5 minutes and invert on platter.

title: southwestern pasta salad
directions: Cook pasta according to package directions; drain.
Rinse with cold water and drain.
Combine pasta and 1 3/4 cups creamy Southwestern Salad Dressing, toss.
Chill.
Spoon pasta mixture onto a lettuce lined platter. Top with black beans and next 4 ingredients.
Serve with remaining dressing.
6 servings

title: quick chocolate fudge
directions: Boil together sugar, milk and cocoa.
When boiling, add the corn syrup and cook until it forms a soft ball in water.
Take from fire; add butter and vanilla.
Beat until creamy.
Add nuts and pour into buttered pan.

title: grandma pusey's easy refrigerator rolls
directions: In mixing bowl, dissolve yeast in water.
Add sugar, salt and 1/2 of the flour.
Beat thoroughly.
Add egg and shortening.
Beat in gradually rest of flour until smooth.
Place in Tupperware bowl and cover with damp cloth and plastic lid.
Place in refrigerator. Punch down occasionally as dough rises in refrigerator.

title: date pudding cake
directions: Sprinkle soda over chopped dates and nuts.
(I buy bulk dates not the packaged dates which are chopped with sugar on them.)
Put other ingredients in a pan and pour hot water over all.
Mix well. Grease and flour a 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until done.
Cool.
Cut squares and serve with whipped cream or Cool Whip on top.
Very good.

title: delicious cheesecake
directions: Mix cream cheese, sugar and vanilla at medium speed with electric mixer until well blended.
Add eggs and mix well.
Pour into crust and bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until center is almost set.
Cool.
Top with strawberry or blueberry pie topping. Refrigerate 3 hours or overnight.
Makes 8 servings.

title: carrot cake
directions: Sift all dry ingredients together.
Mix oil, eggs and pineapple; beat in dry ingredients.
Add vanilla, carrots and pecans.
Pour mixture into a tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour or until done.
May ice it or serve with powdered sugar on it.

title: hanky panky
directions: Brown meat and sausage.
Drain well.
Add Worcestershire sauce and spices.
Mix all; cut cheese into small pieces and add to mixture.
Cook on low until cheese melts.
Spread on rye slices. Place on a cookie sheet and freeze about 20 minutes, then put in plastic bags and store in freezer to use as needed.
Broil on cookie sheet about 3 minutes (watch).
Don't broil too close to flame.
(Great for cocktail party, can be done way ahead.)

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Boil salted water; add grits and cook as directed on box.
Add margarine, cheeses and Worcestershire.
Stir until melted.
Pour into greased casserole dish.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: squash saute
directions: Heat the oil or margarine in a frying pan.
Grate equal amounts of the squash, zucchini and onion.
Saute vegetables in oil and season with black pepper to taste.

title: microwave bread pudding
directions: Spread bread cubes in an 8-inch dish. Sprinkle with brown sugar, salt, raisins and cinnamon.
Measure milk in a quart bowl. Add oleo.
Microwave on High for 4 minutes or until oleo is melted. Stir in eggs and mix well.
Pour over bread cubes. Microwave on Medium 12 minutes.

title: banana bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a large mixer bowl, combine 1 cup of flour, the sugar, baking powder, baking soda and salt.
Add mashed banana, shortening, margarine or butter and milk.
Beat with an electric mixer on low speed until blended, then on high speed for 2 minutes.
Add eggs and remaining flour.
Beat until blended. Stir in nuts.
Pour batter into a greased 8 x 4 x 2-inch loaf pan. Bake for 55 to 60 minutes or until a toothpick inserted near the center comes out clean.
Cool for 10 minutes on a wire rack. Remove from pan.
Cool thoroughly on wire rack.
Wrap and store overnight before slicing.
Makes 1 loaf (16 servings).

title: hobo hamburgers
directions: Make hamburger into large patties.
Use large enough pieces of aluminum foil to put 1 patty on foil.
Dice onion on top of patties, then put enough sliced potatoes on top to cover meat. Salt and pepper.
Put 1 1/2 teaspoons butter on top.
Wrap up like a tent.
Bake for 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: basil-garlic steak rub
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Rub over steak before grilling.

title: pulled taffy
directions: Boil the first 4 ingredients together until mixture turns brittle when dropped in cold water.
Add flavoring and soda.
Pour on buttered platter.
Turn in edges as it cooks.
When cool enough to handle, pull to clear and brittle.
Cut into pieces and wrap.

title: dumplings
directions: Mix dry ingredients well.
Cut in shortening as for pie crust until crumbly.
Add enough milk to make a stiff dough.
Roll out on well floured board, 1/8 to 1/4-inch thick.
Cut into squares and drop into boiling broth.
Reduce heat and cook about 20 minutes, uncovered.

title: joan donahue's tortellini soup
directions: Brown sausage; drain and remove from pan.
Saute onions and garlic until tender.
Add broth, V-8 (or wine and water), tomatoes, carrots, basil, oregano, tomato sauce and sausage. Bring to boil, reduce heat and simmer 30 minutes.
Stir in zucchini, tortellini, parsley and green pepper and simmer, uncovered, for 35 to 40 minutes more.
Serve with grated Parmesan cheese.

title: foolproof pastry
directions: Combine flour, sugar and salt; cut shortening into mixture with a fork.
In a separate bowl, beat vinegar, egg and water. Pour into flour mixture and stir with a fork until mixture is moistened.
Shape into a ball, wrap in wax paper and chill for 15 minutes.
Roll out on a cold pastry board or between two pieces of waxed paper.
Bake at 425° or until golden brown.
Good crust!

title: aunt hanna's coffee cake
directions: Cream butter; add sugar and mix well.
Add egg; beat well. Add vanilla and lemon extract; mix well. Sift in flour, salt, baking powder and milk alternating.
Grease 8-inch round pan with butter.
Sprinkle pan with flour.
Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: thumbprints
directions: Cream shortening and brown sugar.
Add egg yolk and vanilla. Beat thoroughly.
Sift flour and salt. Stir into creamed mixture. Roll dough into ball, 3/4-inch in diameter.

title: microwave nacho cheese dip
directions: Melt cheese in microwave.
It is easier to do one block at a time.
After three minutes in microwave, stir and add half the milk.
Keep heating until all thick lumps are dissolved when stirred.
Stir in jar of picante or salsa.
Add taco sauce to taste.

title: marinated mushrooms and zucchini
directions: Place mushrooms,
zucchini
and/or yellow summer squash and red pepper in a plastic bag; set in a deep bowl.

title: peach crunch cake
directions: Put fruit into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sift the cake mix over the top of the fruit.
Melt butter and pour over cake mix.
Add coconut and pecans.
Bake 55 minutes at 350°.
Add Cool Whip.

title: chocolate crunch pie
directions: Prepare pudding as on package; fold in Cool Whip.
Stir 1 cup cookies and the combination mixture in.
Spoon into pie crust. Sprinkle with remaining cookies.
Freeze until firm.

title: coconut pie
directions: Mix and cook until thick.
After thickened, remove from heat and add a dash of vanilla, margarine and coconut.
Pour mixture into precooked pie crust.

title: buttermilk salad
directions: Heat pineapple and Jell-O; stir until dissolved. Cook 5 minutes; cool. Add buttermilk, Cool Whip and pecans; mix well. Refrigerate.

title: hot spiced tea
directions: Combine tea, honey, cinnamon, and cloves in saucepan.
Simmer 5 minutes.
Makes 4 servings.

title: sweet potato casserole *
directions: Cook potatoes in boiling water until tender.
Drain.
Peel and half potato lengthwise.
Place in 10 x 6-inch baking dish. Sprinkle lightly with salt.
Drain apricots, reserving syrup. Arrange apricots over potatoes.
In saucepan, combine brown sugar, cornstarch, salt and cinnamon; stir in apricot syrup and raisins. Cook and stir over high
heat until mixture comes to a boil; stir in pineapple juice. Pour mixture over potatoes and fruit.
Bake, uncovered, at 350°, basting occasionally, for 20 minutes or until well glazed.
This may be prepared 2 days before you plan to serve it.

title: layered cabbage slaw
directions: In a 2 quart bowl (or larger), layer the ingredients (I make 3 layers).

title: pecan sandies
directions: Mix oleo, vanilla and powdered sugar, then add flour and chopped pecans.
Roll into balls in palms of hand. Bake at 300° for about 10 minutes.
Cool slightly.
Roll in powdered sugar. These freeze well too.

title: autumn buffet punch(from south hills pittsburgh aauw)
directions: Mix together.
This serves 45 (4-ounce) cups and the men love it.

title: cucumber sauce for chicken
directions: Combine seasonings with cucumbers. Fold into cold whipped cream.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients.
Mix remaining ingredients until well blended.
Add nuts and raisins if desired.
Pour into 2 greased and floured loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 55 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center come out clean.

title: nut bread
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients together, then add chopped nuts.
Put in greased pans and let stand 20 to 30 minutes.
Bake for 40 minutes at 350°.

title: flat bread
directions: In a bowl, mix together all ingredients except water.
Add enough water to make a stiff dough. Roll dough out thin on floured board.
Bake on a lefse grill, then place in a 325° oven until crisp.

title: butterscotch icebox cookies
directions: Cream Crisco, sugar, egg and vanilla together.
Sift dry ingredients together.
Add to creamed mixture.
Mix thoroughly. Shape into log.
Wrap in wax paper.
Refrigerate 6 hours or overnight.
May also roll out thin.
Spread jelly over dough. Reroll, then refrigerate.
Slice thin.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 11 minutes.

title: crispix party mix
directions: Pour melted sauce over dry mixture.
Stir to coat real good. Cook in microwave on High heat for 2 minutes.
Stir and cook 2 more minutes.
Drain on paper towels.
Store in container with tight fitting top.

title: savory pork chops
directions: Place chops in a baking dish and sprinkle with salt and pepper.
On each chop, place a slice of lemon, cut about 1/4-inch thick. Sprinkle 1 teaspoon brown sugar over each chop.

title: speedy guacamole
directions: Slice avocados in half lengthwise; remove pits.

Scoop out pulp with a spoon into a small bowl. Mash with a fork until smooth. Add lemon juice, onion, tomato and salt to bowl; mix well. Add sour cream, red pepper flakes and cilantro to bowl; mix well. Spoon guacamole into a serving bowl. Serve with tortilla chips or quesadillas.

title: honey date bars
directions: Mix honey, eggs and vanilla; beat well.
Sift together flour, baking powder and salt; add with dates and nuts.
Spread in greased 12 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Cool in pan. Cut in 3 x 1-inch bars, roll in sugar.
Makes 39 bars.

title: apple cake
directions: Beat eggs, oil and vanilla until foamy.
Mix dry ingredients, add to egg mixture.
Add nuts and apples; mix.
Bake 1 hour at 350° in 13 x 9-inch pan.

title: ham roll-ups
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Preboil broccoli (or cabbage or white asparagus).
Pour off water or place in strainer.
Place drained vegetable on ham and roll up.
Place cheese on top.
Place roll-ups in baking dish and bake until cheese is melted.

title: cranberry nut bread
directions: Grate orange rind, then squeeze juice.
Put shortening, juice, water and rind in bowl and mix.
Add rest of ingredients.
Bake in well-greased loaf pan at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: gourmet eggs
directions: Take eggs and put in small saucepan.
Cover with cold water. Bring to a good boil.
Turn off burner and leave eggs for 10 minutes or longer.
Peel under cold water.
Mash with butter, salt and pepper.
Enjoy.

title: peach cream cake
directions: Cut cake into 1/4-inch slices; arrange half the slices on bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
In large bowl, combine sweetened condensed milk, water and extract.
Add pudding mix; beat well. Chill 5 minutes.
Fold in whipped cream.
Pour half the cream mixture over cake; arrange half the peaches on top.
Repeat layering, ending with peach slices.
Chill 4 hours or until set. Refrigerate leftovers.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Combine broccoli and onion with fried, drained bacon, raisins and sunflower seeds.
Mix mayonnaise, sugar and vinegar.
Add to broccoli mixture and toss.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: Break spaghetti into 1-inch pieces; cook and drain.
Do not overcook.
Saute mushrooms in margarine.
Remove skin and bones from chicken; cut into large pieces.
Turn into buttered casserole dish.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake 40 minutes at 300°.
Serves 8.

title: chocolate raspberry truffle cheesecake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Combine graham cracker crumbs, cocoa, 2 tablespoons sugar and butter (or margarine), mixing well.
Spread evenly over bottom and sides of 9-inch spring-form pan (or two 9-inch pie pans).
Refrigerate crust while preparing filling.

title: bacon and egg bake
directions: Put bacon slices on bottom of greased casserole; add onion. Mix 1/4 cup of milk to cream of mushroom soup.
Pour this on top of bacon and onion.
Add sliced hard-boiled eggs, 2 cups of grated Cheddar cheese, salt and pepper.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes, until hot.
Serve on English muffins or toast.

title: dilly burgers
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Make ground beef into 12 thin patties. Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Place one onion slice on each of 6 patties.
Evenly divide dill slices over onion slices.
Top each patty with one of remaining 6 patties, pressing edges together to seal.
Place in a baking dish.
Combine undiluted tomato soup with Worcestershire sauce.
Spoon over meat.
Bake 40 to 45 minutes. Serves 6.

title: chicken cheese lasagna
directions: Saute green pepper, onion and mushrooms in margarine until tender. Stir in soup (undiluted), milk and Velveeta cheese.
Cook until well blended.

Place 3 noodles in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan and cover with half of the soup mixture and half of the chicken. Repeat the two layers of noodles, soup and chicken. Top with Parmesan cheese. Cover lightly and bake in a 350° oven for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix all (but 1/4 cup chopped nuts) and shape in ball.
Wrap in plastic wrap; freeze for 15 minutes.
Remove; roll in remaining nuts.
Store overnight in refrigerator.

title: death by chocolate
directions: Bake devil's food cake; cool.
In trifle bowl or large glass bowl, crumble 1/2 of cake.
Next, layer with chocolate pudding, then Cool Whip and then layer with three crumbled Heath bars. Repeat process again, ending with Cool Whip and sprinkle with Heath bars.
Chill and serve.
Serves about 12.

title: chicken stir-fry
directions: In bowl, stir together soup mix, cornstarch, water and soy sauce until smooth.
In a 10-inch skillet or wok over medium-high heat, in 1 tablespoon of hot oil, stir-fry half of the chicken until browned.
Remove.
Repeat with remaining chicken.

title: frito pie
directions: Brown
meat
and
drain.
Mix together the soups, milk, chilies
and tomato sauce.	Heat until bubbly.
Mix with meat. Layer
Fritos
on bottom of pan. Layer meat mixture next.
Top with cheese.
Place in oven until cheese is melted.

title: curry chicken casserole
directions: Mix chicken soup, mayo, lemon juice, water, dried onion chips, salt, pepper and curry to taste.
Spread bite size, partially cooked chicken over a layer of green beans.
Pour mix over chicken and beans.
Cover with crackers.
Sprinkle Cheddar on top.
Bake at 300° for 40 minutes.

title: four o'clock favorites
directions: Beat margarine and sugar until light and fluffy.
Blend in eggs and vanilla.
Add combined flour and baking powder; mix well. Stir in remaining ingredients.
Drop teaspoonfuls of dough onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: sweet potato balls
directions: Mash potatoes.
Add margarine, sugar and nutmeg.
Form potatoes into balls and roll in cornflakes.
Place in a greased baking dish and bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: texas hash
directions: Saute onions & bell pepper in oil until yellow. Drain and add ground beef, fry until it falls apart. Stir in the rest of the ingredients. Pour into greased 2 qt. casserole dish, cover & bake at 350 for 1 hour, 15 minutes uncovered.

title: eggplant casserole
directions: Cook
together eggs and eggplant, then mash.
Add other ingredients.
Pour
ingredients into a greased casserole dish. Bake until light brown at 350°.

title: overnight casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Let stand overnight in refrigerator. Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: potato quiche
directions: Press excess moisture from potatoes and place in greased deep dish pie pan.
Pour melted butter over and bake 30 to 45 minutes at 425°.

title: diabetic baked barbecued spareribs
directions: Trim excess fat from ribs.
Cut into 6 portions.
Place in baking dish.
Combine remaining ingredients; pour over ribs. Cover and let stand 15 minutes.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Remove cover; baste.
Bake 1/2 hour.
Spoon off excess fat and serve.

title: pronto pup mix
directions: Mix all dry ingredients together.
Add egg and milk and beat until smooth.
Dip frankfurters in batter and fry in deep oil until brown.

title: fig preserves
directions: Pour boiling water with soda over figs.
Let stand 10 minutes. Rinse in cold water and drain.
Measure 4 cups sugar and only enough water to dampen sugar.
Bring Karo to a boil and add figs. Boil 15 minutes.
Set aside 10 to 12 hours.
Boil 30 minutes or until syrup looks like honey.

title: raw apple cake
directions: Combine ingredients in order.
Mix for about 5 minutes.
Put in ungreased tube pan. Bake at 350° for 1 1/4 hours.

title: basic cookie recipe
directions: Cream sugar, shortening and eggs.
Spoon flour into dry measuring cup, level off and pour measured flour onto a square of waxed paper.
Add salt and soda to flour and stir to blend.
Add blended dry ingredients to creamed mixture; and mix well.
Divide Dough into 3 portions for variations listed.
Bake at 350 degrees for 12-15 minutes.
Yields 6-7 Dozen.

title: baking powder biscuits
directions: Mix dry ingredients, cut in shortening with pastry blender or two knives until consistency of coarse meal.
Stir in milk to make smooth dough.
Turn onto floured board, pat or roll lightly to 1/2 inch thickness.
Cut in rounds.
Bake on ungreased sheet at 450 degrees for 10 to 16 minutes.

title: chocolate chocolate chip cake
directions: In a large mixing bowl, combine cake mix, pudding and wet ingredients.
Mix well.
Fold in chocolate morsels.
Pour into greased Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 55 minutes.

title: four-decker mocha dessert
directions: In mixing bowl, cut butter or margarine into flour until crumbly.
Stir in 3/4 cup of the peanuts.
Press mixture evenly the bottom of a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Bake in a 350° oven for 20 minutes.
Cool.

title: corn fritters
directions: Sift flour, baking powder, salt and paprika.
Add corn and beaten egg yolks.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.
Drop by spoonfuls in hot grease and fry until brown.
Serve with honey.

title: pan-fried fish filets
directions: Melt butter
and oil in pan.
Mix bread crumbs, cheese, salt and pepper; blend.
Mix oil and eggs together.
First dip fish in flour, then in egg mixture; drain and coat with bread crumbs.
Fry in hot butter and oil for 3 to 5 minutes.
Melt 4 tablespoons butter
in
frying pan; add lemon juice, mix, then serve over filets.

title: party meat loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients except soup; form into loaf.
Bake for 1 hour.
Pour soup over loaf. Bake 20 more minutes.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: cider punch
directions: Mix all the ingredients together and pour over a block of ice in a punch bowl.

title: corn relish
directions: Cut corn off of the cob to equal 1 gal. Add all ingredients into a large pan. Cook at low heat until
done. This recipe varies depending on how sweet and how hot you want it. Just add more or less vinegar or sugar or bell pepper to suit your taste.

title: lime molded salad(shared by va bullard, radford, va)
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in hot water.
Cool to lukewarm and add vinegar.
Add rest of ingredients.
Pour into oiled mold; chill until firm.

title: cheese dip
directions: Blend tomatoes and heat in a double boiler for 30 to 45 minutes, stirring once in awhile.

title: dirt dessert
directions: You will also need 6 clean, new flower pots, 6 plastic flowers and 6 gummy worms.

title: quick scalloped potatoes
directions: Microwave Directions:
Power select: High Medium, Medium-stand approximately cooking time 35 minutes.
Yields about 6 servings.

title: angel food trifle
directions: Prepare pudding mix according to package directions.
Stir in almond extract.
Spread preserves on one side of cake slices. Place a layer of cake slices in bottom of a large glass serving bowl, preserves side up.
Sprinkle with sherry; spoon pudding over cake.
Repeat layers, ending with pudding.
Cover and refrigerate until chilled.

title: carrot-nut salad
directions: Combine bread and butter. Cook slowly until crumbs are coated. Remove from heat. Add peanuts and mix well. Add carrots to mixture. Sprinkle with oil and vinegar. Serve on lettuce leaves. Serves 6.

title: grapefruit gelatin ring
directions: Dissolve gelatin in 1/4 cup cold water.
Let stand 5 to 7 minutes.
Add 1/2 cup boiling water.
Stir until dissolved.
Add remaining ingredients.
Stir until sugar is dissolved.
Pour into ring mold.

title: chicken and vegetable bake
directions: In 1 1/2-quart casserole, mix soup, milk, vegetables, chicken, Worcestershire and 1/2 can onions.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until hot.
Stir.
Sprinkle with remaining onions. Bake 5 minutes or until done.

title: corn bread salad
directions: Prepare corn meal to make a thin cake of corn bread, 3/4 inch thick.
Bake, crumble and set aside.
Mix all ingredients together and toss.

title: shoney's strawberry or blueberry pie
directions: Mix cornstarch and salt with water.
Boil until thickened. Remove from heat.
Add 2 tablespoons Jell-O (dry) or 1/2 box to mixture.
Cool.
Put berries in baking shell; pour mixture over berries.
Chill in refrigerator.
Top with whipped cream.

title: pumpkin raisin muffins
directions: Combine pumpkin pie mix, nut bread mix, egg and raisins.
Stir until just moist.
Spoon into greased medium muffin cups, filled about 2/3 full.
Sprinkle tops with sugar and cinnamon mixture. Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes or until golden brown.
Serve warm.
Makes about 30 muffins.

title: zucchini italiano
directions: Combine oil, onion and garlic in an 8-inch square glass baking dish and cook 3 minutes.
Stir in zucchini, seasoned salt and oregano.
Cover and cook 3 minutes; stir.
Cook additional 3 minutes.
Stir.
Let stand covered 5 minutes before serving. (Cook in microwave.)

title: company sweet potatoes
directions: Combine sweet potatoes, sugar, milk, butter, eggs and vanilla. Mix well.
Spoon into a lightly greased 2-quart casserole. Combine coconut, brown sugar, flour, 1/3 cup melted butter and pecans, mixing well.
Sprinkle over top of sweet potatoes. Bake at 375° for 45 minutes or until golden brown.
Yields 10 servings.

title: cookies '84 recital
directions: Flatten crescent rolls in 10 x 15-inch pan.
Pour Eagle Brand over roll and sprinkle dry coconut pecan frosting mix over that. Melt margarine and drizzle over frosting mix.
Bake at 400° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Cool.
Cut into bars and serve!!
Piano recital students and parents enjoyed them!!

title: crunchy frisco salad
directions: Toss spinach, mushrooms and oranges.
Just before serving, add French fried onions and dressing; toss gently.
Serve immediately.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Mix together and top with 1/3 cup melted butter and 3 cups crushed corn flakes.

title: melt in your mouth sugar cookies
directions: Combine butter, oil and sugar in large mixing bowl; beat well. Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each addition.
Stir in vanilla.
Add flour, baking soda and cream of tartar.
Shape dough into 1-inch balls.
Place on ungreased cookie sheets.
Flatten with bottom of a glass dipped in sugar.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Cool on wire racks.
Makes 6 to 7 dozen cookies.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Combine
all
ingredients together.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done.

title: noodle casserole
directions: Cook noodles; drain.
Brown meat; drain.
Pour tomato sauce over meat.
Bring to a boil; set aside.
Put cooked noodles in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Blend cream cheese, cottage cheese and sour cream.
Add onions and green pepper.
Spread over noodles. Pour meat mixture over top.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: chicken picantefort collins, colorado
directions: Boil chicken and take off skin.
Cook vegetables according to pkg. directions.

title: caramel corn puffs
directions: Mix butter, sugar and syrup.
Heat in a saucepan.
Bring to a slow boil.	Stir constantly (approximately 5 minutes).
Remove from heat.	Add 1/4 teaspoon soda; stir.
Place popcorn on a large cookie sheet or baking pan that has been sprayed with Pam.	Pour syrup mixture over the popcorn.
Bake 1 hour at 250°.
Stir every 15 minutes.

title: spareribs and kraut
directions: Trim fat from pork and cut into serving pieces.
You may brown if desired.
Add small amount of water and cook slowly 1 hour. Empty can of kraut and the cabbage into the kettle with pork.
Add the scrubbed unpeeled potatoes.
Cook slowly 1 hour.
I usually cook the pork, kraut and cabbage for 15 minutes before I add the potatoes.
This is a German dish.
Serves 4.
Can double recipe.

title: irish soda bread
directions: Cover raisins with hot water and let stand five minutes. Grease pan.
Sift together dry ingredients.
Rub in shortening with fingertips.
Add caraway seed.
Dry raisins with paper toweling and add.
Mix beaten eggs and buttermilk lightly with fork.
Stir into flour mixture to make a soft dough.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Measure oatmeal into bowl; stir in melted margarine; mix well.
Stir in eggs and sweetener; add mixture of flour, baking powder and salt alternately with the combined milk and vanilla.
Add raisins.
Drop onto cookie sheet from level teaspoon; bake until golden brown (about 10 to 15 minutes).
Yield: 4 dozen cookies.
Thirty-six packets artificial sweetener = 1 1/2 cups sugar.

title: taco burgers
directions: In a mixing bowl, combine salsa or taco sauce, bread crumbs, chili powder and salt.
Add ground beef; mix well.
Shape meat mixture into 4 (3/4-inch) thick patties.
Arrange patties in an 8 x 8 x 2-inch microwave-safe baking dish.
Cover loosely with waxed paper.
Microcook on 100% power (High) for 3 minutes.
Drain off fat.
Give the dish a half turn and turn meat patties over.
Cook on High for 3 to 5 minutes more or until no pink remains.
Place lettuce on buns.
Top with cooked meat patties and process cheese spread.
Pass additional salsa or taco sauce with burgers.
Makes 4 servings.

title: chow mein chow
directions: Melt oleo in small saucepan. Stir in sauces and garlic; keep warm.
In a large roasting pan, mix popcorn, corn chips, pretzels, soy beans and noodles.
Stir in oleo mixture to coat.
Bake in preheated 250° oven for 45 minutes, stirring occasionally, until dry. Cool.
Store in airtight container.
Makes 9 cups.

title: 5 layer delight
directions: First layer- Mix flour, butter and pecans in 9 x 12 pan. Bake at 350 degrees for 10 minutes, cool.

title: sandwich bread cheese cake
directions: Blend cream cheese and sugar until fluffy.
Cut crusts off bread and flatten each slice with rolling pin.
Spread cream cheese lightly on each slice.
Roll up each slice of filled bread.
Dip lightly into melted butter; roll in sugar with cinnamon mixed in. Place on cookie sheet and bake for 15 to 20 minutes at 350°, until bottoms are brown.
Cool and serve.

title: party mix
directions: Combine and place on 14-inch square pan.
Bake at 225° to 300° for 2 hours.
Stir often and test.
Yield:
13 to 16 cups.

title: peanut butter log
directions: Combine sugar, corn syrup, water and salt in a saucepan.
Boil until it spins a thread or to hard ball stage (252°).
Beat until stiff egg whites.
Pour boiling hot syrup in a thin stream over egg whites beating constantly until stiff like bread dough.
Roll out on wax paper sprinkled with confectioners sugar.
Roll with rolling pin until quite thin.
Spread with peanut butter and roll up in long roll.
Allow to stand until firm; cut into desired length.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Beat together eggs, pumpkin, oil and water.
Sift together flour, sugar, baking soda, salt and spices.
Fold dry mixture into pumpkin mixture.
Add nuts and raisins.

title: "hungry jack casserole"
directions: Brown hamburger and onions.
Drain.
Add brown sugar and barbecue sauce and pork and beans.
Pour into large casserole. Top with biscuits; sprinkle cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until biscuits are done.

title: crab louis salad
directions: In medium bowl, combine mayonnaise, catsup, onion, Worcestershire sauce, vinegar, lemon juice, salt and pepper. Chill 30 minutes.
In center of salad platter, heap crab.
Circle with lettuce, egg, cucumber and tomato slices.
Pass the dressing separately.
Serves 4.

title: potato casserole
directions: Thaw potatoes completely.
Melt margarine and pour over potatoes (in large baking 9 x 13-inch dish).
Stir in sour cream, cheese and soup.
Top with crushed corn flakes.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: chicken salad
directions: Combine chicken, salad oil, orange juice, vinegar and salt. Let stand while preparing other salad ingredients.
Can let it stand overnight.
Gently toss together remaining ingredients, stirring in mayonnaise last.
Makes 12 big servings.

title: light bread
directions: Mix flour, soda, salt and baking powder in large bowl.
Pour in raised yeast mixture.
Stir until flour has been absorbed.
Knead until light.
Divide in two equal portions.
Drop each half of dough into greased standard size loaf pan, turning over to grease on all sides.
Press in bottom of pan to form smooth loaf.
Let rise until doubled in bulk.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 35 minutes. Yields 2 loaves.

title: sunshine jelly mold
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Put into a mold or bowl.
Serve chilled.

title: hobo stew
directions: Cook
meat
and
spices;
add
Veg-All, corn and tomato paste and sauce.	Mix together.
Add egg dumplings to meat and vegetables.
Simmer on low heat for 1 hour.

title: mandarin orange salad
directions: Dissolve Jello in boiling water.
Cool and add orange juice, pineapple, and oranges.
Congeal and add topping.

title: ale bread
directions: In bread machine, place all ingredients in order suggested by manufacturer.
Select basic bread setting.
Choose color and loaf size if available.
Bake according to bread machine directions. Check dough after 5 minutes of mixing.
Add 1 to 2 tablespoons of water or flour if needed.

title: "hamburger" cookies
directions: Tint coconut with green food coloring.
Divide frosting into 3 containers.
Tint one red, one yellow and leave one white.
Layer white frosting, green coconut, mint cookie, red frosting and yellow frosting between 2 wafer cookies.
Apply sesame seed to top of vanilla wafer using a tiny amount of honey.

title: baked saucy chicken(quick and easy)
directions: Coat chicken in favorite oven baking mix.
Place on greased baking pan.
Bake until done.
Remove from pan and place in glass baking dish.
Open can of cream of chicken soup and dab onto chicken.
Do not dilute soup!
Sprinkle a little butter on top. Sprinkle entirely with paprika.
Cover and bake an additional 10 minutes.
Serve.
Can be done either in oven or microwave.

title: cinnamon biscuits
directions: Bake biscuits as package reads.
Combine sugar and cinnamon and mix evenly.
Melt butter in the microwave.
If you need more, make more.
After biscuits have turned golden brown, remove from oven.
Take a biscuit; roll it in the butter until covered, then in the cinnamon and sugar mixture until covered.
(Be sure the biscuits are warm.)

title: "healthy" brownies(no cholesterol)
directions: Mix margarine and sugar to creamy consistency.
Add cocoa; blend well.
Add egg substitute, then add flour, salt, nuts and vanilla.
Pour mixture into greased 9-inch square pan.
Bake in 350° oven for 25 to 30 minutes or until center tests dry with toothpick.

title: chicken hawaiian
directions: Drain pineapple, reserving juice.
In a large skillet, cook onion and celery in oil until tender.
Add chicken.
Blend catsup and reserved pineapple juice with enough water to make 2 1/2 cups liquid.
Add salt and pepper; pour over onion, celery and chicken. Simmer 5 minutes.
Dissolve cornstarch in soy sauce.
Gently stir into chicken mixture.
Add green pepper and pineapple.
Cover and simmer 5 minutes.
Serve over hot rice.

title: chicken chili
directions: Put chicken in pan with water.
Add salt, pepper and celery flakes to taste.
Cook until tender.
Remove chicken from broth. Add beans, tomato soup, brown sugar and chili powder.
Cook slowly 1/2 hour.
Add water if liquid cooks down.
When chicken is cool, cut into bite size chunks.
Add to chili.
Bring to boil.
Thicken with flour and water.
Serve with hot dog buns opened, spread with butter and lightly toasted under broiler.

title: pecan cranberry pie
directions: Beat eggs slightly.
Add sugar, salt, syrup and melted butter; mix well.
With spoon, add remaining ingredients.
Pour into a deep 9-inch pie crust (unbaked).
Bake for 10 minutes at 400°, then for 30 to 40 minutes at 350°, or until mixture sets.

title: banana bread
directions: Peel and mash bananas; put in separate bowl.
Mix rest of ingredients all together; beat, then add bananas.
Stir.
Grease pan.
Put in oven at 350°.
Check at 45 minutes.

title: apple crisp
directions: Slice apples to cover two 8 x 10-inch pans.
Sprinkle next 3 ingredients over apples.
Mix other ingredients and sprinkle over apples.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Bring butter and peanut butter to a rolling boil.
Remove from heat.
Add confectioners sugar and vanilla flavoring.
Stir until smooth.
Pour into lightly greased pan, 7 x 9-inches.
Cool at least 2 to 3 hours until set.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Saute onion until clear.
Shut off heat and add paprika and chicken pieces.
Cover with cold water.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Simmer until chicken pieces are tender, always making sure chicken is covered with water.
Add 1 cup uncooked rice.
Cover and cook until all liquid is absorbed by rice.
Stir once.
Lower heat when cooking chicken.
Serve at once.
Makes enough for 4 people.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Spray 9 x 13-inch pan with Pam.
Mix all ingredients and bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Also can be baked in muffin pan using temperature and baking time from Jiffy cornbread mix box.
Yields 2 dozen muffins.

title: veg dip
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients together, then mix all the rest.

title: glazed beets
directions: Drain beets, reserving 1/3 cup juice,

In a saucepan, combine the sugar, cornstarch and salt. Stir in beet juice and vinegar. Cook and stir over medium-high heat until thickened and bubbly. Cook and stir 2 minutes more. Add beets and butter.
Heat through. Yields 4 servings.

title: grandma's refrigerator rolls
directions: Place water in large warm bowl.
Sprinkle in yeast; stir until dissolved.
Stir in sugar, salt, butter, eggs, whole wheat flour and enough all-purpose flour to make a stiff dough.
Grease top; cover tightly with plastic wrap.
Refrigerate for 2 hours or up to 3 days.

title: potatoes deluxe
directions: Peel potatoes; add 1 teaspoon salt and enough water to cook until tender.
Drain, cool and cube.
Saute onion and green pepper in butter until tender.
Add mustard, 1 teaspoon salt, pepper, milk and cheese.
Heat until cheese is melted, stirring well.
Put potatoes in 1-quart greased casserole.
Pour sauce over potatoes and mix well.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes.
Makes 4 servings.

title: tuna bake sandwiches
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Fill hot dog buns with tuna mixture. Wrap individually in foil.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: strawberry trifle
directions: Cream together until well blended and smooth. Set aside for a few hours or overnight.

title: marinated mushroom-spinach salad
directions: Combine oil, vinegar, basil, salt, pepper and garlic, blending well.
Pour over onion and mushrooms.
Let stand at room temperature 2 hours, or refrigerate overnight.
Stir occasionally. Place spinach in serving dishes.
Arrange mushroom mixture over top.
Serve immediately.
Serves 6.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Prepare and bake cake mix in layers.
Dissolve gelatin in 2 cups boiling water. Stir in strawberries.
Let stand until thick. Prepare pudding, using package directions.
Layer cake, pudding and gelatin in large punch bowl.
Chill until firm.
Spread whipped topping over top.
Serves 15.

title: funny cake
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder, sugar and salt.
Add the shortening, milk and vanilla to the dry ingredients and beat until moist.
Add the egg and the milk and beat until it forms a batter. Pour the batter into the pie shells.
Mix together the hot water, sugar and cocoa to form a syrup.
Divide the syrup evenly and pour it over the cake batter.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes and at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: meatless chili chowder
directions: Combine all ingredients in a very large pot and bring to a boil, then simmer, stirring occasionally, for 30 minutes.
Makes 10 cups.
Freezes well.

title: pork chops in adobo sauce
directions: Place following ingredients in blender:
tomato sauce, vinegar, onion, garlic, flour, chili powder, oil, salt, oregano and cumin.
Blend well.

title: raspberry delight
directions: Boil raspberries, water and cornstarch together.
Set aside to cool.
Beat butter, eggs, powdered sugar and vanilla until fluffy. Fold cooled raspberries into egg mixture.
Pour into graham cracker crust.
Top with whipped cream or graham cracker crumbs. Store in refrigerator.

title: frozen bread
directions: When thawed, roll out bread (about 9 x 13-inch).
Saute hamburger and onion and drain.
Season to taste with salt, pepper and garlic.
Spread hamburger and onion onto bread.
Chunk cheese onto meat.
Roll like a jelly roll.
Brush with melted butter. Bake at 350° until nicely browned.
Slice and serve.
Great Saturday lunch.

title: cabbage chowder
directions: In a kettle, combine carrots, butter and caraway seed; cook until just crisp-tender over low heat, about 5 minutes.
Add soup, milk, water, cabbage and sausage.
Bring to a boil; reduce heat and cook until cabbage is tender, about 15 minutes.

title: chicken pie
directions: Mix chicken, soup, broth, eggs and can of peas and carrots all together and put in large baking dish.
Mix Bisquick, milk and margarine and pour on top of other.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: no bake fruit cake
directions: Mix together in a heavy saucepan the marshmallows, milk and sugar.
Boil until the mixture reaches a rolling boil; can boil slightly longer.
Let mixture cool slightly.
Place graham crackers in a large bowl and add the cherries, pineapple, raisins, coconut and pecans.
If desired, more nuts and fruit can be added.
Pour the marshmallow, milk and sugar mixture over these ingredients. Mix well.
Pour into Pyrex dishes and place in refrigerator.

title: tomato pudding
directions: Mix puree, water, sugar, salt and Tabasco. Boil 5 minutes. Place bread in casserole. Pour butter over it. Let soak in. Pour tomato mixture over bread. Bake 30 minutes at 375°. Can be made several hours ahead. Cook 45 minutes if refrigerated.

title: broccoli-cheese casserole
directions: Cook broccoli until tender; place it in an 8-inch casserole dish.
Place the unmelted cheese on top of the broccoli and sprinkle the crushed Ritz crackers on top.
Pour melted butter over the top of the crackers.
Bake 30 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: mexican finger food
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Spread onto 4 to 5 large tortillas (floured).
Roll up and chill, then slice into bite size pieces.

title: dried beef casserole
directions: Rinse beef in boiling water 15 seconds per slice. Combine all ingredients in a 3-quart casserole. Refrigerate 12 to 15 hours. Cook, uncovered in microwave 25 minutes. Stir every 10 minutes.

title: microwave applesauce
directions: Combine apples, water and lemon juice in 2-quart glass casserole dish.
Microwave 10 to 12 minutes on High or until apples are tender.
Stir in remaining ingredients.

title: beef casserole
directions: Cut zucchini in 1/2-inch slices.
Cook 8 minutes in salt water and drain.
Cook beef and onion in oil until done and drain.
Add zucchini, salt and pepper.
In a separate pan, stir butter and flour until bubbly.
Add milk.
Stir until thick.
Add cheese, salt and pepper.

title: lemon bars
directions: Combine and crumble like corn meal.
Spread on 8 x 11-inch pan bottom.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: chocolate covered ritz crackers
directions: Spread crackers with peanut butter. Dip all in melted chocolate. Drain on wax paper. Cool. Can freeze.

title: baked grits
directions: Cook grits in salted water, stir in oleo and cheese.
Cook until done.
Let cool.
When cool, stir in eggs.
Pour into casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: tea concentrate #3
directions: Mix water and sugar and boil for 5 minutes.
Pour hot sugar water over next 3 ingredients.
Cool and remove tea leaves.
This amount fills approximately 3 1/2 plastic 1/2 gallon ice cream containers.
Freeze and have handy for a crowd or in smaller containers to fill a pitcher or glass.

title: boiled chocolate oatmeal cookies
directions: In a large saucepan, mix by hand the sugar, cocoa and milk. Put on stove and add butter or margarine and bring mixture to a boil.
Boil for 1 1/2 minutes.
Remove from heat and stir in quick cooking oatmeal and vanilla . Stir well.
Let mixture sit to begin to harden.
Spoon onto wax paper, cookie tray or plastic tray. Makes about 24 cookies.

title: chili pie
directions: Spray 8-inch round pan.
Combine ingredients; press mixture into bottom of pan.
Bake 10 to 15 minutes.

title: mexican fruitcake
directions: Mix all together and pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 45 minutes at 350° (35 minutes if using glass pan).

title: country breakfast
directions: In a 10-inch skillet, cook potatoes, green pepper and onion in margarine until lightly browned.
Season to taste.
Beat eggs lightly, then pour over potato mixture.
Cover; cook until eggs are done.
Top with cheese.
Cover; continue cooking until cheese is melted.
Yields 4 servings.

title: sweet and sour meatballs
directions: Place cranberry sauce, chili sauce and Worcestershire sauce in pan on medium heat until it bubbles.
Make small balls of seasoned ground beef and drop them into the sauce.
Cook for about 1 1/2 hours.
Make a day ahead and refrigerate for best flavor.
Use in a chafing dish as hors d'oeuvres.
Makes about 100 small meatballs.

title: basic pie crust
directions: Mix shortening, milk, and boiling water until it resembles whipped cream.
Add flour and salt.
Mix into soft ball.
Press with fingertips into pie pan.
Bake at 450° for approximately 15 minutes.

title: ratatouille
directions: Melt the 1/4 cup butter in a large saucepan.
Add onion, celery, mushrooms and garlic.
Cook 3 to 4 minutes over medium heat.
Add zucchini, tomatoes, eggplant, salt and pepper.
Cover and cook 15 to 20 minutes.
Serve hot.

title: barbecue beef
directions: Mix all ingredients in roaster.
Add meat.
Cover and bake at 300° for 5 hours.
String meat with fork.
All juices will be absorbed.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Cream shortening and butter.
Add sugar; beat until creamy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each.
Sift flour and dry ingredients together.
Add to mixture alternately with milk which vanilla has been added to. Blend thoroughly.
Turn into greased and lightly floured tube pan (you can use Pam instead).
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 20 minutes.

title: banana torte
directions: Place all ingredients near at hand before starting.
Empty can of Eagle Brand into medium mixing bowl.
Layer wafers and bananas in a suitable Pyrex dish (deep enough so that ingredients will not run over); set aside.
Add instant pudding mix to milk and beat until blended, 1 minute.
Add whipping cream and continue to blend/mix while blender/mixer is still whipping.
Add iced water in and continue until blended in mixture.
Pour over banana/wafer immediately as pudding will start to congeal.
Place in refrigerator for 1 to 2 hours before eating to let flavors soak through.

title: spicy turkey breast
directions: In a blender or food processor, combine garlic, rosemary, pepper and paprika.
Turn motor on.
Add olive oil and process until coarsely chopped.
Skin the turkey breast; wash and pat dry. Spread the garlic mixture over the turkey breast.
Place on rack in roasting pan; cover.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours or until meat thermometer inserted into center registers 170°. Remove from oven.
Let stand 20 minutes before slicing.

title: stuffed crabs
directions: It is best to make Crab Gumbo and Stuffed Crabs on the same day, because the gumbo or soup from crabs adds to the success of the stuffed crabs.
Some cooks take the crab's claws and shells that the crab meat has been taken from, put them in a pot with 1 quart boiling water and use in the stuffed crab after an hour's boiling.
It answers the same purpose as the gumbo.

title: wild punch
directions: Mix ingredients together and chill for 2 hours before serving for best results.

title: chicken with pineapple sauce
directions: In a saucepan, combine brown sugar and cornstarch. Stir in pineapple, soy sauce, garlic salt and ginger. Cook and stir over low heat until thickened. Place chicken in a greased 9-inch square pan or baking dish. Pour half of the sauce over chicken. Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 15 minutes. Baste. Bake 10 minutes longer. Baste several times. Sprinkle with chives.

title: chicken snitzell
directions: Pound chicken very thin.
Soak in enough milk to cover them overnight.
Dip in mixture of half cheese and half bread crumbs. Fry on each side until well done.

title: cabbage soup
directions: Simmer beef ribs, chicken wings and water for 3 hours.
Remove meat from bones.
Discard bones.
Refrigerate meat and broth separately overnight.
Skim off and discard fat the next day. Combine broth and meat.
Add other ingredients and simmer for 3 hours.
Serve in bowls with a dollop of sour cream.

title: taco dip
directions: Mix together cream cheese, sour cream and taco sauce.
Spread onto a cookie sheet.
Refrigerate overnight.
Make the layers just before you're going to serve it.

title: cottage cheese patties
directions: Mix all and drop by spoonfuls in small amount of oil and fry. Place in casserole and cover with 1 can mushroom soup, 1 cup sour cream and small amount of milk to make thin sauce.
Heat in oven until heated through.
Serve hot.

title: delta bars
directions: Mix together first 8 ingredients.
Grease and flour a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spread in pan.
Combine brown sugar, beaten egg white and nuts; mix and pour over topping. Bake in 350° oven for 25 minutes.
Cut in squares while warm.

title: dry rub
directions: Mix together and rub into meat 3 hours ahead of time.
Wrap in plastic wrap and chill in refrigerator.
In lieu of oregano, use marjoram, thyme, basil or rosemary.
To make spicier, use more cayenne or use brown sugar to make a sweeter taste.
Any leftover rub can be stored in air tight container for 3 to 4 weeks.

title: ground beef casserole
directions: Add ground beef to onion, green pepper and butter; cook until it changes color.
Cook noodles and drain; add salt and pepper to taste.
Add tomato sauce to noodles and then mix noodles and ground beef mixture together.
Mix soup and milk together; then mix with ground beef mixture.
Pour into 2 casserole dishes and top with grated cheese.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: peter paul mound cake
directions: Mix makes 3 layers.
Bake at 350°.

title: cream cheese brownies
directions: Mix together the cake mix, melted margarine and egg.
Press in bottom of 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
In a large bowl, mix the cream cheese, eggs and 10x sugar; mix well.
Pour on top of cake mixture.
Bake at 325° for 55 minutes.
Cut into squares.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli according to instructions. Place drained broccoli in casserole dish. Mix soup and mayonnaise together and pour over broccoli. Sprinkle cheese on top of soup mixture. Mix stuffing and butter together; spread over casserole and bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until bubbly and heated through.

title: stir-fry
directions: Cut up sirloin steak and chicken into thin strips.

Cook steak and chicken in oil until done, then add the remaining ingredients with a little stir-fry sauce and a little water. Simmer at low heat for about 20 minutes, then after it cooks, serve on rice.

title: ham and potato scallop
directions: Combine soup and milk with whisk.
Add potatoes, ham, onion, green pepper and pepper.
Mix well.
Turn into 2-quart casserole. Dot top with butter.
Bake, uncovered, at 350°
for 1 hour.
Cover and continue baking 45 minutes or until potatoes are tender.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Cut meat crosswise into 1/2-inch slices.
Dip in flour and brown quickly on all sides.
Set aside.

title: poppy seed cake
directions: Mix together cake mix, instant pudding, oil and eggs.
Set aside.
Mix 1 cup boiling water plus 1/4 cup poppy seed well. Add to cake mixture. Bake in a lightly greased
pan at 350° for 1 hour.

title: brother randy's sad cake
directions: Grease and flour a large loaf pan (at least 2-quart pan). Combine all ingredients and bake 40 to 45 minutes at 350°.

title: pot roast chicken
directions: Mix ginger, garlic, salt, shoyu and sugar and rub it over chicken inside and out.
Heat liquid shortening and brown chicken well on all sides.
Add remaining mixture and liquid from mushrooms.
Cover and simmer until done.
Remove chicken and cut into pieces.
Make gravy with remaining liquid and cornstarch; add mushrooms.
Pour over chicken and garnish with green onions or Chinese parsley.

title: 6 way cookies
directions: Mix condensed milk, peanut butter and one of the six items listed.
Drop by teaspoonful onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° until brown on bottom.
Cookie will look soft on top.

title: nannie's lasagne
directions: Brown ground beef, garlic and onion.
Add sauce mix, tomato paste and 3 cans of water and simmer.
Cook noodles, drain and rinse.
In bowl, mix 2 eggs (beaten), cottage cheese and Parmesan cheese.
Layer in a 13 x 9-inch pan a little sauce, then noodles, cheese and egg mixture and Mozzarella cheese.
Repeat layers (3 in all).
End with Mozzarella cheese and sprinkle with Parmesan cheese on top.
Bake at 375° for about 30 minutes, until cheese melts and is bubbly.

title: sirloin tip
directions: Melt shortening.
Brown meat.
Stir in consomme, wine, soy sauce, garlic and onion salt.
Heat to boiling.
Reduce heat to low and cook until meat is tender (a crock-pot can be used also). Blend cornstarch and water; boil until thick.
Pour over meat mixture.
Pour in rice.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Mix in order given.
Bake at 325° until brown and toothpick comes out clean (about 1 hour and 20 minutes).
Makes 2 loaves.

title: strawberry squares
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients; bake in a shallow pan or cookie sheet at 350° for 20 minutes.
Stir occasionally.
This mixture will be crumbly.
Sprinkle 2/3 of this crumb mixture in the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan (it will not completely cover the bottom of the pan).
Combine egg whites, sugar, berries and lemon juice. Beat at high speed for about 10 minutes.
Mix Dream Whip according to the directions on the package.
Fold Dream Whip into strawberry mixture by hand.
Spoon this mixture into the 9 x 13-inch pan and top with remaining crumbs.
Freeze 6 hours before serving.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: cheddar cheese cracker spread
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Use milk to thin to proper consistency with hand mixer.

title: beets with brown sugar and cloves
directions: In 2-quart saucepan, heat beets, 1 inch of water and salt to boiling.
Cover and simmer 20 to 30 minutes or until tender. Drain beets, peel and slice.
(This may be eliminated if using canned beets.)
In same pan, combine remaining ingredients.
Cook over low heat, stirring until smooth.
Add beets and stir gently to coat.
Heat.

title: strawberry pretzel salad
directions: Layer pretzels, margarine and 3 tablespoons sugar in 9 x 13-inch dish and bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Cool.
Cream the cheese and blend in sugar.
Add Cool Whip and spread over pretzels.
Dissolve jello in water.
Add frozen strawberries that have been pureed.
Stir.
The jello mixture will be slightly thickened.
Pour over layers.
Refrigerate.

title: snack mix
directions: Mix several of the ingredients of 1 cup measurement each.
Be creative.
Nice for gifts, too.

title: quesadillas
directions: Cut tortillas into 5 pieces, lengthwise.
Place an even amount of cheese, onion, chilies and tomato onto each piece of tortilla. Place in baking dish.
Cook for approximately 6 minutes on High in microwave or bake at 275° in oven until cheese is melted.
Makes 40 pieces.

title: orange salad
directions: Put the first 3 ingredients in blender; blend until creamy. Fold in orange slices and chill.

title: surprising pumpkin cake
directions: Beat the eggs until they are well mixed.
Add the oil, pumpkin and all-bran and mix well.
Add all remaining ingredients, except the chocolate chips and Grape-Nuts and mix well.
Stir in the chips and Grape-Nuts.
Pour into a greased Bundt pan and bake 45 to 50 minutes at 350°.

title: light "n" fruity pie
directions: Dissolve gelatin completely in boiling water, stirring about 3 minutes.
Add ice cubes and stir until gelatin is thickened, about 2 to 3 minutes.
Remove any unmelted ice.
Blend in Cool Whip; whip until smooth.
Fold in fruit.
Chill, if necessary, until mixture will mound.
Spoon into crust.
Chill 2 hours.
Garnish if desired with fresh fruit.

title: green junk
directions: Mix jello and Knox gelatine with water by package directions. Put cream cheese in while still warm.
Let congeal a little before adding remaining ingredients.

title: date pecan blondies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour a 13 x 9-inch pan. Beat brown sugar and butter or margarine until light and fluffy. Add eggs and vanilla; mix well.
Add flour, baking powder, salt and nutmeg; mix well.
Add dates and stir well.
Spread into greased pan.
Sprinkle chopped pecans on top.
Bake for approximately 20 minutes or until light golden brown.

title: cucumbers greek style
directions: Pour buttermilk into a bowl and add remaining ingredients, except celery strips.
Let stand 1 hour in the refrigerator, until ready to serve.
Mix well before serving.
Serve with chilled celery strips as an appetizer.

title: almond brittle(candy)
directions: Cut a 1-foot length of aluminum foil; lay on a heatproof surface and butter it evenly (butter, margarine or nonstick spray work equally well).

title: nachos
directions: On microwave-safe plate, put chips in a single layer.
Put small amount of grated Cheddar cheese on center and a little salsa on the cheese.
Microwave until cheese melts.

title: baked apples
directions: Core apples and peel each about 1/4 of the way down.
Arrange in slow cooking pot.
Fill centers with raisins and dates. Combine sugar, water, butter, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Pour over apples.
Cover and cook 2 to 4 hours.

title: apple dump cake
directions: Place apples, sugar and cinnamon in a 9 x 13 sprayed cake pan.
Mix together.
Sprinkle cake mix evenly over it.
Put nuts and coconut over mixture.
Pour melted butter over all.
Bake at 350° until apples are done and top is brown (about 30 to 35 minutes).
Serve with whipped cream.

title: mystery muffins
directions: Mix together.
Pour into muffin pan. Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: orange jello salad
directions: Add Jell-O to one cup boiling water and stir well, then add sherbet and stir until melted.
Add Cool Whip and stir until blended.
Add mandarin oranges and whip with mixer until oranges are chopped.
Chill two hours before serving.

title: potato-leek soup
directions: Cut off the tops of the leeks an inch or two above the white part.
Discard the tops and a thin disc at the root end, as with an onion.
Cut the leeks once lengthwise, and rinse each half under running water.
Check for mud under outer leaves.
After rinsing, cut crosswise 2 or 3 times.

title: simple breakfast casserole(breakfast)
directions: Line 8x8 baking dish with hash browns.
Sprinkle with sausage or bacon.
Mix eggs, milk, salt, pepper and dry mustard.
Pour over meat and hash browns.
Top with Cheddar cheese.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: homestyle pizza bread
directions: In large bowl, combine 1 1/2 cups flour, 1 teaspoon basil, yeast and salt; mix well.
Stir in very warm water and oil and beat on low speed 1 minute.
Add remaining flour; blend on medium speed, mixing well, about 2 minutes.
Turn out onto lightly floured surface.
Knead 2 minutes or until smooth and elastic.
Turn into greased 13 x 9-inch pan; cover and let stand 10 minutes.
Press into pan and, using fingertips, make indentations in dough over entire surface.
Blend remaining 1 teaspoon basil with tomato sauce; spoon over dough to within 1-inch of edges.
Sprinkle with green onions.
Let rise in warm, draft-free place 30 minutes.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes or until edges are golden brown. Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: zucchini chocolate cake
directions: Cream margarine, oil and sugar.
Add eggs, vanilla and sour milk.
Beat well with mixer or by hand.
Stir in dry ingredients and beat well.
Stir in zucchini.
Turn batter into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle chocolate chips over top and bake in 325° oven for 45 to 50 minutes or until top springs back when touched lightly with fingertips.
Needs no frosting.

title: marinated flank steak
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Marinate steak in dressing for a minimum of 2 hours.
Bake in preheated oven for approximately 1 1/2 hours (depending on size of steak and desired doneness).
Remove steak and slice diagonally.
Serve with cooked sauce for dipping.

title: mojo isleno
directions: Add the first 9 ingredients in a saucepan and cook for 1 hour (moderate heat).
Cook fish (season before cooking with salt and garlic).
Serve fish with sauce.
Great if served with white rice.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Sift flour.
Add salt, baking powder, nutmeg and cloves. Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Roll out dough 1/4-inch thick.
Sprinkle with sugar.
Bake in 400° oven for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: rotel chicken
directions: Grease a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Drain and chop chicken. Layer in bottom of dish.
Sprinkle onion over chicken.
Layer entire package of Doritos chips over chicken.
In saucepan, combine Ro-Tel, cheese and soups (undiluted).
When warm and cheese is melted, pour over chicken and chips.
Cook in a 350° oven for 20 minutes or until bubbly.

title: chocolate chip and raisin cookies
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Beat sugar, peanut butter, margarine and vanilla until smooth.
Stir in milk and eggs; gradually add dry ingredients.
Stir in chips and raisins.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on cookie sheet 1-inch apart.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: country chicken and vegetables
directions: Arrange chicken in a large, shallow baking dish.
Arrange cut vegetables over the chicken and season.
Pour broth over chicken and vegetables.
Cover with foil and bake about 1 hour at 375°. Remove foil and bake an additional 15 to 20 minutes.

title: roast pork loin
directions: For stuffing, cook mushrooms and green onions in margarine until tender.
Stir in wine, bring to boil, reduce heat and simmer until liquid evaporates.
Remove from heat and stir in bread crumbs and carrots, salt and pepper to taste.
Rub roast with soy sauce. Cut loin in 2 pieces lengthwise (may already be cut).
Place one side down, place stuffing on top and cover with other piece of meat.
Tie together 5 or 6 places.
Roast at 325° for 2 to 3 hours. Let stand 15 minutes before serving.
Place on platter and remove strings.
Make sauce of drippings to serve with roast.

title: cinnamon cake
directions: Mix together cake mix, oil, eggs, water, pudding and sour cream.
Separately mix nuts, cinnamon and sugar.
Grease and flour an angel food cake pan.
Put 1/3 of batter in pan.
Sprinkle some of the nut mixture around in a circle.
Repeat until batter and nuts are used.
Swirl with a knife.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°. Sift powdered sugar on top before serving.

title: spicy spareribs
directions: In a 3-quart saucepan bring spareribs, water, onion and garlic to a boil.
Cover and simmer 1 hour or until ribs are tender and starting to fall off the bone.
Remove ribs from bones and put in a foil-lined shallow pan into which they just fit in a single layer.
Stir together molasses, ketchup and mustard; spoon over ribs.
Bake in a preheated 375° oven until very hot (20 to 25 minutes).

title: meal in one
directions: Cut cabbage in wedges and place in buttered casserole. Arrange beef, rice and onion between and over wedges.
Combine tomatoes, water and seasoning.
Pour over casserole.
Cover; bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: chocolate zucchini cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together well and bake in greased 9 x 13 inch pan at 350° (glass pan at 325°) for 30-35 minutes.

title: ice tea punch
directions: Mix all together and pour over ice cubes in glasses.

title: cheese squares
directions: Preheat oven to 325°. Beat eggs and milk together. Mix with cheese. Pour into greased glass baking dish (9 x 13). Bake for 1 hour.

title: pineapple casserole
directions: Mix sugar, flour, cheese and pineapple. Put in 2-quart casserole.
Cover with Ritz crackers.
Pour melted margarine on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: french oven beef stew
directions: Mix beef, onions, celery and carrots in a covered baking dish. Mix together cooking tapioca, sugar, salt and pepper and pour over vegetables, stirring to coat meat and vegetables.
Cover and cook about 2 hours at 325°, until meat and vegetables are about done.
Stir occasionally.
Peel 3 medium potatoes; add 1 cup frozen lima beans (optional).
Stir all together with meat and vegetables and cook an additional 1 hour.

title: festive cheese spread
directions: Mix well and form into a ball.
Chill several hours or overnight for flavors to blend.
Serve with assorted crackers.

title: baked chicken
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Melt margarine in rectangular 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Mix rest of ingredients.
Coat chicken with mixture. Place chicken, skin side down, in pan.
Bake uncovered 35 minutes. Turn over and bake until done, about 15 minutes.

title: chocolate eclair
directions: Mix pudding and milk. When thickened, add Cool Whip. Fold in until creamy. Line bottom of 9 x 13 pan with crackers. Pour 1/2 pudding mix over crackers. Pour remaining pudding over crackers. Top with another layer of crackers. Heat frosting about 1 minute in microwave to soften. Spread over crackers.

title: chocolate cream pie
directions: Combine cornstarch, milk, salt, syrup, egg yolks and sugar in medium microwave bowl.
Microwave on Medium-high 6 to 8 minutes or until thick.
Stir every 2 minutes with wire whisk.
Stir in vanilla and pour into crust.
Chill several hours or overnight. Garnish with whipped cream or egg white topping.

title: pepper relish
directions: Cut up green peppers and onions.
Mix together all ingredients and cook for 30 minutes.
Pack into sterilized jars and seal at once.

title: ginney's kielbasa
directions: Cut up 1 package kielbasa thin; put in crock-pot.
Slice 1 green pepper and 1/2 onion.
Put in crock-pot on top of kielbasa, then add 1/2 box brown sugar.
Repeat with the remaining ingredients and top with the rest of the brown sugar.
Add 2 tablespoons of water to pot and cook 2 1/2 hours.
Drain most of the liquid at the end of cooking time.
Serve with mustard.

title: teriyaki sauce
directions: Great marinade for flank steak!
Combine and marinate flank. Turn meat at least twice.
Sauce is delicious served over rice, after heating in microwave.

title: harvard beets
directions: Mix sugar and cornstarch.
Add vinegar and water.
Boil 5 minutes, stirring frequently.
Add butter and drained beets.
Salt to taste.
Let stand over low heat 1/2 hour.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Mix milk, cream-style corn, corn meal, flour, peppers, eggs, sugar, soda, baking powder, grated cheese, bacon drippings and crumbled bacon.

title: florida frosty
directions: Combine orange juice, yogurt and banana in a blender.
Blend until smooth.
Serve immediately.
This is a great after school snack.

title: orange balls
directions: Cream the butter and sugar, vanilla wafers then the orange juice.
Make into small balls.
Roll in pecans.
Can be frozen and served later.

title: angel rolls
directions: In a mixing bowl, combine 1 1/2 cups flour, sugar, yeast, salt, baking powder and baking soda.
Add the buttermilk, oil and water; beat until moistened.
Stir in enough remaining flour to form a soft dough.
Turn onto a floured surface and knead until smooth and elastic, about 4 to 6 minutes.
Cover and let rest for 10 minutes. Roll out to 1/2 inch thickness; cut with a 2 1/2 inch biscuit cutter.
Place on a greased baking sheet.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 18 minutes or until golden brown.
Brush tops with butter.
Yield: 14 rolls.

title: whole wheat dinner rolls
