directions: Mix the oil, egg, salt and sugar together in a small bowl. Measure out whole wheat flour and all-purpose flour.
Mix the whole wheat flour with the ingredients in the small bowl.
Add the all-purpose flour.
Mix with wooden spoon until you can't stir any more. Place dough on a floured surface and knead it until it's not sticky.
Place dough in a lightly greased bowl.
Cover and place in refrigerator until the next day.
Roll out the rolls on a floured pastry cloth until the dough is approximately 1/2-inch. Place rolls in a greased pan and let rise until they are doubled in height.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
Grease top of rolls with butter.
Let cool.

title: layered strawberry salad
directions: Mix well.
Press into an 8 x 13-inch baking dish.
Bake for 8 minutes at 400°.
Cool.

title: fried fish yummies
directions: Clean
and
fillet
fish;
cut strips into small pieces about the size of scallops.
Mix flour, corn meal and salt and pepper in bowl.
Measure
milk
into
a bowl.
First dip fish into
milk, then eggs, then cornmeal/flour mixture.
Drop into hot grease
and deep fry until done.
Drain fish.	Serve with cocktail sauce and munch out!

title: chicken asparagus casserole
directions: Wash and drain chicken; season with salt and pepper.
Dust with flour.
Fry in deep fat fryer or skillet until brown but not done; drain.
Place chicken in casserole dish; cover with asparagus spears.
Spread with soup; sprinkle with cheese.
Bake in 350° oven for 40 to 45 minutes.
Makes 8 servings.

title: pineapple meat balls
directions: In a large bowl, crumble white bread and milk.
Add ground round, egg, salt, garlic powder and pepper.
Mix well with fork. Form into small balls.
Melt butter in a large skillet.
Brown meat balls on all sides, shaking pan often to keep balls round. Remove and set aside (or skip all of this and buy a bag of precooked meat balls).

title: chocolate pudding cake
directions: Sift flour, baking soda, salt, sugar and 2 tablespoons cocoa together.
Stir in milk and margarine.
Spread in pan.
Sprinkle with brown sugar and 1/4 cup cocoa, then pour over all the hot water.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: creamy broccoli casserole
directions: Peel stalks of broccoli and cut in about 1/2-inch pieces.
Cut tops into quarters.
Steam with salt until crisp.
Place in a shallow 2-quart casserole.
Sprinkle lemon juice over broccoli. Mix soup, mayonnaise and curry; pour over broccoli.
Sprinkle with bread crumbs and drizzle with melted butter.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 20 minutes or until bubbly.

title: santa's peanut butter fudge
directions: Combine milk and sugar in a saucepan.
Boil without stirring until candy temperature registers 240° (soft ball forms when a little is dropped in cold water).
Remove from heat.
Add Marshmallow Fluff, peanut butter, vanilla and dates.
Stir only until combined.
Pour into 8-inch pan.
Let stand in refrigerator at least 20 minutes before cutting.
This is a wonderful and easy way to make fudge that keeps soft several weeks.

title: oriental dish
directions: Boil chicken and debone.
In large skillet, add small amount of oil and add celery, pea pods, water chestnuts and onion.
Once they become tender, add quartered tomato, bell pepper and squash until all ingredients are tender and juicy.
Add oyster sauce (very little) to ingredients and finally combine with the chicken.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Serve on a bed of rice.

title: hot pineapple casserole
directions: Mix pineapple juice, flour and sugar until well blended. Stir in pineapple and cheese. Bake at 350 degrees for 20 minutes. Remove from oven. Mix melted butter and Ritz crackers. Put on top and bake 10 to 15 minutes more.

title: 24 hour salad
directions: Beat eggs until light.
Gradually add sugar, light cream and lemon juice.
Mix together and cook in double boiler until thick, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and cool.

title: cabbage soup with sausage
directions: Chop cabbage and onion and fry in 1/2 of the oil.
When cabbage turns yellow, sprinkle with flour, add remainder of oil and simmer for a few minutes.
Dilute with stock; season with salt.
Add cubed potatoes and sliced sausage and boil for approximately 20 minutes.
Add chopped parsley before serving.

title: hamburger fried rice
directions: Cook rice and set aside.
Brown meat in skillet.
Drain well. In separated skillets, cook 2 or 3 medium onions (more if you love onion) and peppers.
On low heat, add 1/2 stick of butter or margarine and saute.

title: scalloped corn
directions: Beat egg.
Mix with sour cream.
Add to corn.
Mix in corn bread mix, melted oleo and salt.
Mix well.
Bake 1 hour in 350° oven.

title: blintze casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Line casserole with blintzes.
Add margarine.
Mix everything but eggs.
Beat eggs.
Add to mixture. Pour.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: oven-fried chicken
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients.
Dip chicken in butter.
Dredge in breadcrumb mixture.
Place in a greased 12 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until tender.
Yields 4 servings.

title: pineapple cream cheese salad
directions: Dissolve gelatine in one cup cold water.
Set aside.
Mix pineapple, sugar and lemon juice in a medium saucepan.
Bring to a boil.
Remove from heat.
Add the gelatine and let cool.
Whip the whipping cream together with the cream cheese and add to the cooled pineapple mixture.
Pour into a 9 x 12-inch pan and chill until firm.

title: scampi
directions: Heat oil in large nonstick skillet over medium heat.
Add shrimp, garlic salt and lemon juice. Cook, stirring constantly, for 2 minutes.
Add onions. Cook 2 more minutes. Serve over pasta. One of my favorites.
Yields 6 servings.
Has 320 calories, 5 g fat.

title: peanut butter candy
directions: Boil sugar and milk for 1 minute.
Remove from stove.
Add peanut butter.
Stir and pour into pan.
Cut when firm.

title: green bean and bacon casserole
directions: Place bacon in 1-quart casserole.
Microwave 3 to 6 minutes on High.
Remove bacon, crumble and set aside.
Add bread cubes to bacon drippings.
Stir.
Microwave 2 minutes on High, stirring once.
Drain and set aside.

title: squash puffs
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Add flour and mix well.
Drop in hot oil by teaspoonful and cook until lightly browned.
Serve hot.

title: busy day beef stew
directions: In crock pot layer potatoes, carrots and meat.
Add soy sauce, salt, paprika, pepper and flour (sprinkled).
Top with chopped onion.
Combine beef broth and tomato sauce and pour over all.
Cover and cook on low heat for 9 - 11 hours or on high heat for 5 - 6 hours. Yield 6 - 8 servings.

title: rice casserole
directions: Place raw rice in casserole.
Brown onion and garlic in butter and add to rice.
Pour in consomme, soup and mushrooms and mix well.
Cover and bake 1 hour at 350°.
Excellent served with chicken, turkey or wild duck.
Serves 6.

title: chocolate reese's cups
directions: Mix sugar, margarine and peanut butter well together.
Make into small balls.
Put on a cookie sheet lined with wax paper. Chill until firm.

title: baked haddock fillets with crab meat stuff
directions: Place 1 fillet on the bottom of a large glass baking pan. Melt butter and mix it with stuffing and crab meat.
Put 1 coat of stuffing mixture over first fillet, then place second fillet over mixture, then put remaining mixture over second fillet.
Bake at 450° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: picante sauce
directions: Cook 50 to 60 minutes.
Pour into hot jars and seal.

title: raspberry coffee cake
directions: Cut cheese and oleo in Bisquick until crumbly.
Blend in milk. Turn dough onto floured board and knead 8 to 10 times on wax paper. Roll dough into 12 x 8-inch rectangle, then turn onto greased cookie sheet and remove paper.
Spread jam down middle, make 1/2-inch slits on both sides.
Bake at 425° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: elsie's chicken imperial
directions: On waxed paper, coat chicken breasts with 1/4 cup flour.
In 12-inch skillet, over medium heat in hot butter, cook chicken until lightly browned on all sides.
Set chicken aside.
In drippings over medium heat, cook mushrooms and onion for 5 minutes, stirring frequently.
Stir in cream, wine, salt and pepper and blend well. Return chicken to skillet.
Reduce heat to low.
Cover and simmer 20 minutes or until chicken is fork-tender.
Remove chicken to warm platter.
Serve over noodles or rice.

title: devils food cake
directions: Mix cloves, cinnamon and cocoa in sugar, then cream in crisco, beat eggs and cream, add buttermilk with soda dissolved in it alternating with flour.
Beat on medium speed about two minutes.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: sheepherder's bread
directions: Dissolve yeast in 1/2 cup warm water with sugar for 10 minutes.
Place all the flour and salt in a large bowl.
Add yeast mixture and rest of water.
Mix and knead for about 10 minutes. Place in large greased Dutch oven or cooking pan suitable for oven cooking with cover.
Let rise 1 hour.
Punch down and let rise again for 1/2 hour.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour and 10 minutes with cover on or until done.

title: pistachio delight
directions: Will need a 13 x 9-inch pan.

title: gluten
directions: Combine gluten flour and water into firm ball.
Roll with hands into a log.
Cut into 1/2-inch slices.
Brown onion in oil in large pan.
Add gluten slices and cover with water.
Simmer, closely covered, 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Serves 10.

title: apricot salad
directions: Drain and cut fruits, saving the juices.
Dissolve jello in hot water; add 1 cup juices.
When slightly thickened, add fruits. Cook the sugar, flour, egg and 1 cup juices until mixture thickens, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat; add butter. Cool.
Whip cream and fold into cooked mixture; spread the mixture over salad and top with nuts and/or grated cheese.

title: mom's custard pie
directions: Line unpricked pie crust with a double thickness of heavy-duty foil.
Bake at 450° for 8 minutes.
Remove foil, bake 5 minutes longer.
Remove from oven and set aside.

title: harvard beets
directions: In a medium saucepan melt oleo over low heat.
Blend in flour, salt and sugar.
Gradually add vinegar and beet juice, stirring constantly.
Continue to cook and stir until sauce has thickened and appears glassy.
Add beets to sauce and gently mix with sauce. Cook (simmer) only until beets are hot.
Remove from burner.

title: maandazi
directions: Mix flour, sugar and baking powder.
Heat oil until it is warm and pour over the flour mixture.
Mix well.
Use enough lukewarm water to make a very firm dough.
Roll out to about 1/4-inch thickness.
Cut with a small round cookie cutter or cut in pieces about 1 x 1 1/2-inches.
Cook in hot oil.

title: girl scout caramel sundae squares
directions: Spray a 9 x 2 x 13-inch Pyrex dish with Pam.
Crunch cookies; spread in dish.
Spread Cool Whip over cookies.
Spread caramel topping over Cool Whip.
Sprinkle coconut and nuts over caramel; drizzle chocolate syrup over top.
May be frozen or eaten at once.

title: brownies
directions: Mix all together and bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: beer rolls
directions: Mix thoroughly and drop by spoonful into muffin pans.
Bake at 350° to 400° for 20 minutes.

title: brunswick stew
directions: Cook all of your meats and chop, then add the rest of the ingredients and cook on medium heat for 30 minutes.

title: saucy fish
directions: Saute onions and garlic in oil about 3 minutes. Add oregano and tomatoes. Simmer 15 minutes. Preheat oven to 400°. Cover bottom of glass pie plate or shallow baking pan with sauce. Dip fillets in sauce and fold in half.
Pour remaining sauce over all. Bake 10 minutes or until done.

title: beau monde dip(excellent with pumpernickel bread)
directions: Mix
all
ingredients
together with spoon.
Arrange so bread can be dipped in mixture by guests.

title: dinner rolls and variations
directions: Soften yeast in warm water.
Combine sugar, shortening and salt in large bowl.
Stir in hot milk; cool to lukewarm (110° to 115°).
Add softened yeast and egg; beat well after each addition. Add 2 cups flour; beat well.
Gradually add remaining flour; stir in to make soft dough.
Cover; let rise in warm place until double (or more).
This takes 1 1/2 to ? hours.
Punch down.
You are now ready to shape into your favorite rolls (cloverleaf, Parker House, etc.).
Place in or on greased pans.
Let rise again until at least double in bulk.
Bake at 375° to 400° for 10 to 12 minutes, or until desired brownness.
(Makes 24 rolls.)

title: barbecue chicken wings
directions: Rinse and dry wings.
Cut off tips and half at joint.
Bake wings 15 minutes.
Turn; bake 15 minutes longer.
Mix sugar, cornstarch, ginger, salt and pepper in saucepan.
Stir in lemon juice, soy sauce and Worcestershire.
Cook over moderate heat stirring until thick.
Simmer 3 minutes.
Remove from heat. Brush wings with a light coating of glaze baking turning and brushing with glaze every 10 minutes for 40 minutes.

title: hot fudge sauce
directions: Mix sugar, cocoa and butter.
Heat slowly in saucepan, stirring constantly, until melted.
Bring to a boil.
Add 1 teaspoon cold water; boil again.
Add milk slowly; cook until thickened.

title: old-fashioned gingerbread cookies
directions: Cream together sugar and shortening.
Add eggs and molasses. Mix well.
Sift the flour, ginger, cloves, nutmeg, baking soda, salt and cinnamon.
Add sifted ingredients to creamed mixture. Wrap tightly and place in refrigerator for several hours.
Bake at 325° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Heat a can of frosting and pour over cookies.

title: rafter "x" beef brisket
directions: Brush brisket with liquid smoke.
Rub on powders.
Place in large cooking bag in large roasting pan.
Pour in sauces. Marinate overnight.
Pierce several holes in top of bag.
Roast at 325° for 4 hours or until tender.

title: "granma" cookies
directions: Mix margarine, sugar, cocoa and milk.
Boil 2 minutes.
Add oats and peanut butter.
Mix.
Drop by tablespoons onto waxed paper.
Let stand until cooled.
Enjoy!

title: chocolate fudge
directions: Put sugar, Pet milk, corn syrup and butter in a saucepan. Bring to a boil; stirring constantly.
Continue to cook over moderate heat for 5 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Add chocolate chips and vanilla and stir.
Stir in nuts. Pour into a lightly buttered 8 x 8-inch or 8 x 9-inch pan.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Boil macaroni; drain.
Put in casserole dish.
Add grated cheese; mix well.
Pour milk in.
Add margarine, eggs, salt and pepper.
Cook at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour covered.

title: stir-fried turkey and vegetables
directions: In a medium bowl, combine sugar, cornstarch, ginger and soy sauce; mix well.
Add turkey; stir to coat.
Let stand 10 minutes. In a large skillet or wok, heat oil over high heat.
Add carrots and broccoli, stirring lightly to coat with oil.
Add broth. Cover; cook for 2 minutes.
Add turkey and soy sauce mixture; stir gently over medium heat.
Add onion; stir-fry 1 minute.
Add mushrooms; stir-fry until mixture is hot.
Serve over noodles or hot rice.
Makes 4 servings.

title: five layer salad
directions: Fry bacon; crumble.
Put salad in order in bowl.
Put bacon over top.
Mix salad dressing and sugar; pour over top.
Sprinkle 1/3 cup cheese on top.
Do not stir.
Refrigerate.

title: baked mac and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni.
Slice cheese.
Grease bottom of square 9 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan with butter.
Put a layer of cheese then layer of macaroni, etc., ending with layer of cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: italian bean salad
directions: Open all cans of beans; drain thoroughly in a colander.
In a large mixing bowl, add remaining vegetables.
In a saucepan, combine sugar and vinegar; bring to a boil.
Stir until sugar is dissolved.
Add oil, salt and pepper.
Add drained beans to chopped vegetables; cover with hot marinade.
Let cool at room temperature for several hours, then refrigerate until ready to use, at least 24 hours.
Yields approximately 2 1/2 quarts.

title: sweet cucumbers
directions: Mix sugar, white vinegar and canning salt until dissolved. Pour over vegetables. Put in refrigerator. Will keep up to 6 weeks in a covered container in the refrigerator.
These may also be frozen in small containers after about a week.
They are crispy when thawed out.

title: onion cheese muffins
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large bowl; beat 1 minute.
Fill medium-sized greased muffin tins 2/3 full.
Bake 15 minutes at 400°.
Serve warm.
Makes 12 to 16 muffins.

title: glazed sweet potatoes
directions: Mix ingredients together and pour over sweet potatoes in a baking dish.
Bake 30 minutes in a moderate oven.

title: chocolate sheet cake
directions: Sift flour and sugar together in a large bowl.
Combine butter, shortening, cocoa and water in a saucepan and slowly bring to a boil.
Pour the cocoa mixture over the flour and sugar and mix well.
Stir in buttermilk, eggs, salt, soda, cinnamon and vanilla.
Pour into a greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan and bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Begin making the icing 5 minutes before the cake is done.

title: lisa's lemon topped cheese cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix together graham cracker crumbs, sugar and melted butter.
Mix well.
Press this mixture into the bottom and sides of a 9-inch spring-form cake pan.
Bake shell in oven for 5 minutes.
Mix the cream cheese, sugar, vanilla and eggs together.
Pour into the graham crust and bake in the oven for 30 minutes.
Remove from oven.

title: zucchini pickles
directions: Cut zucchini into thin slices and cut onions in quarters. Slice onion very thin and add to zucchini. Cover with water and add salt. Let stand two hours and drain thoroughly.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Peel apples and slice thin.
Mix ingredients until a smooth batter.
Add apples to batter (also pecans).
Bake at 325° in greased Bundt pan 1 hour and 20 minutes.
Drizzle with frosting made from powdered sugar and a little water.

title: black velvet cake
directions: Mix cake mix, pudding mix,
eggs, water, oil, sour cream and 1/3 cup chocolate chips.
Layer cake
mixture,
then
a
layer of chocolate chips, cake mixture, then chocolate chips.
Bake in greased and floured Bundt cake pan at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Cook macaroni according to package directions; drain.
In 2-quart casserole, combine hot cooked macaroni with tuna, soup, cheese, milk and olives.
Cover and bake for 20 minutes or until hot and bubbly.
Makes 4 servings.

title: mike's chicken piquante
directions: Place chicken breasts in bottom of baking dish. Drizzle 1 teaspoon honey over each one.
Pour piquante sauce over all. Cover with lid or foil and bake at 350° for about 1 hour or until done. I like mine hot and sweet!

title: broiled scallop puffs
directions: In saucepan, cover scallops with water; add salt.
Cover and simmer for 10 minutes, drain and cool.
Cut scallops in half. Combine mayonnaise, pickle relish, parsley, lemon juice, Worcestershire sauce and the dash of salt and pepper; fold in beaten egg white.
Place scallops on baking sheet; top each with a little of the mayonnaise mixture.
Broil about 3 minutes, until golden brown.
Serve immediately.
Makes about 24 hors d'oeuvres.

title: delicious dip
directions: Peel hard-boiled egg.
Cut in half.
Remove yolk.
Mix with mayonnaise, salt and pepper.
Cut 2 paper triangles.
Tape them to toothpicks.
Put yolk mixture and sails into egg halves.
Sail into your mouth.

title: corn casserole
directions: Beat eggs and add remaining ingredients, except 1/4 cup cheese. Put in 9 x 13-inch casserole dish and sprinkle remaining 1/4 cup cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: meatballs in tomato sauce for a microwave
directions: Combine ground beef, onion, egg and salt in medium mixing bowl; mix well.
Shape into 18 (1-inch) meatballs.
Place in 9-inch round glass baking dish.
Cover with plastic wrap. Microwave on High for 8 minutes.
Drain drippings.
Combine remaining ingredients in small bowl.
Pour over meatballs and continue cooking on High for 5 to 6 minutes or until pipping hot.

title: broccoli au gratin
directions: Place broccoli in a 10 x 6 x 2-inch baking dish. Cover and microwave on High for 4 to 5 minutes. Stir broccoli.
Add onion and microwave, covered, for 5 to 7 minutes. Drain.
Combine soup, sour cream and cheese. Spoon atop broccoli.
Microwave, uncovered, on High for 8 minutes, turning once.
Sprinkle 1 cup croutons on top.
Microwave, uncovered, on High for 1 to 2 minutes more or until heated through.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: vegetable and pasta casserole
directions: Mix soup mix with oil.
Combine oil mixture
with vegetables. Broil in a 425° oven for 15 to 20 minutes.
Toss with cooked orzo.

title: garlic butter potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cut up potatoes to 1 inch size pieces. Add salt, pepper, and garlic to taste.
Cut up butter on top of potatoes.
Bake in a dish covered with foil for 20-25 minutes. Stir once.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients and cook until clear.
Add peanuts.
Cook to 280° on candy thermometer.
Remove from heat; add soda.
Stir.
Pour onto buttered cookie sheet.
When cool, break into pieces.

title: amazing coconut pie
directions: Combine milk, sugar, Bisquick, eggs, butter and vanilla in blender.
(Start blender immediately.)
Cover and turn on blender on low speed for 3 minutes.
Pour mixture into a greased 9-inch pie pan.
Let set for 5 minutes.
Sprinkle coconut over pie mixture, then bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
You may want to add coconut into mixture when blending if you prefer.

title: pot roast
directions: Place roast in roaster with oil.
Bake in 400° oven for 1 hour (covered).
Remove from oven and add one envelope of brown gravy. Add 2 cups of water also.
Cook for 1 hour over top of stove until tender (covered).
Add 1 jar of mushrooms and serve.
This makes a very tender roast.

title: reuben casserole
directions: Layer sauerkraut and noodles in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix soup, milk and onions.
Spoon over noodles.
Layer corned beef and bread crumbs on top.
Dot with margarine.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: easy pot roast
directions: In bowl, blend together all soups.
Put roast and vegetables in a Dutch oven.
Pour soups over all and cook in a 300° oven for 4 hours.
Serve with rice or noodles.

title: german apple cake
directions: Fold in 4 cups thickly diced apples and 1 cup pecans, chopped.
Bake in greased and floured 9 x 13 inch pan for 1 hour at 350°.

title: pineapple casserole
directions: Mix flour and sugar together.
Stir in pineapple and cheese. Put in greased casserole dish (approximately 9 x 9-inch or 8 x 12-inch).
Sprinkle crackers on top.
Melt butter and pour over top.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: cheese 'n wiener crescents
directions: Cut cheese slices into 6 strips each.
Slit wiener to within 1/2 inch of ends and insert 3 cheese strips.
Center wiener on the dinner roll and roll up.
Place on a baking sheet, cheese side up. Bake at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: spiced crumb cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients.
Cut in shortening with pastry blender until a fine crumb mixture.
Add egg and molasses, blend well.
Add sour milk and beat until smooth.
Pour into greased and floured square pan.
Bake at 350° for approximately 45 minutes or until cake tests done.
May be served plain or with icing.
(This recipe came out during World War II.)

title: chocolate apple bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease two (9 x 5 x 3-inch) loaf pans. In a small bowl combine flour, salt, baking powder, baking soda, cinnamon and nutmeg; set aside.

title: chicken pizza
directions: Preheat the oven to 425 degrees. Brush the pizza crust with oil.
Combine the sage, pimiento, soup, chicken and celery.
Mix well.
Spread over the crust. Sprinkle with cheese. Bake about 20 minutes or until the crust is golden brown.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook hen until done; cool and debone.
Cook noodles in broth. Saute in oleo the onion, water chestnuts, garlic, celery and pepper.
Add soups and pimento.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Shred zucchini and mix together with all other ingredients.
Bake at 325° until top springs up when touched lightly.
Makes two loaves or 1 sheet cake.

title: fruity diamonds
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Sift together flour, soda and salt.
Stir in oats.
Add to creamed mixture and mix until crumbly.
Firmly pack half the mixture in greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Spread with date filling.
Add remaining crumbs and pat smooth.
Bake in moderate oven, 350°, for 30 minutes.
Cut in fairly big diamonds.
Press walnut half into top of each diamond.

title: cheese cookies
directions: Mix. Chill dough.
Roll to 1/8-inch thickness.
Cut into rectangles 1 x 2-inches with a knife dipped in flour.
Brush with beaten egg and top with caraway seed, poppy seed or almond sliver. Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Serve with drinks as an hors d'oeuvre or as a savory for dessert.

title: garden rice
directions: Brown rice in oil.
Add pepper, onion, tomatoes and water. Cover and simmer about 30 minutes.
You may wish to add a dash of Mexican seasoning.
Serves 6.

title: hamburger soup
directions: Fry hamburger and drain.
Add to rest of ingredients.
Squeeze the whole tomatoes between your fingers and add to soup.
Add the liquid that is in the cans.

title: taco casserole
directions: Cook ground beef until brown; drain grease.
Add onion.
In the same skillet add taco sauce, soup and green chilies to meat. Line a 9 x 13-inch pan with tortillas and add cheese.
May be layered.
On top add tortillas and cheese.
Cover with foil.
Cook at 350° for 1 hour.

title: scalloped corn
directions: Combine ingredients; pour into buttered 1 1/2-quart round casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes.

title: kulaszkis
directions: Mix oleo into cream cheese, one stick at a time.
Add flour, one cup at a time, mixing well after each addition.
Form dough into 4 balls of equal size.
Refrigerate overnight.
Remove from refrigerator 1 hour before baking time.

title: beef-veg casserole
directions: Cook beef in frying pan so it is cooked but not browned. Place in casserole dish (3-quart), then put in a layer of sliced potatoes, a layer of sliced carrots, a layer of cooked meat and a little of chopped onion.
Repeat layers again and again.
Lastly, add 1 can undiluted can of tomato soup.
Put on cover.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Take off.
Cover and bake 10 minutes more.

title: guadalupe pie
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Spread in 9 1/2 x 13 1/2-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Cool.

title: bacon wrapped water chestnuts in sauce
directions: Wrap each chestnut in 1/2
strip
of
bacon
and secure with toothpick.	Bake at 375° for 45 minutes or until bacon is done. Make sauce with remaining
ingredients
and
pour
over chestnuts.

title: whole-grain pancakes
directions: Variations:
Add grated apple, applesauce or blueberries.

title: mediterranean meatballs
directions: Mix together beef, rice, onion, egg whites, parsley, allspice, salt and pepper.
Form into 1-inch meatballs.
Place oil into large covered frying pan.
Add meatballs in a single layer. Barely cover with water.
Bring to a boil and put on lid.
Simmer meatballs until rice is tender (about 40 minutes).
Remove meatballs to heated plate.
Leave 3/4 cup of liquid in pan.
Beat egg yolks in bowl.
Add lemon juice.
While stirring, add broth from pan.
Return this mixture to pan and heat.
Stir until it is thick.
Return meatballs to pan.
Gently heat for serving.

title: freezer ice cream
directions: In blender, beat the eggs; add sugar (with flour), evaporated milk, part of the sweet milk and vanilla flavoring (or chocolate syrup).
Blend this well.
Pour this mixture into your freezer tub and add remaining sweet milk up to the fill line.
Stir after adding milk; assemble freezer parts.
Add crushed ice alternately with rock salt.
Freeze and enjoy!

title: fresh apple skillet cake
directions: Mix flour, soda, salt and sugar in one bowl.
Mix cooking oil, egg, apples, nuts and vanilla in separate bowl.
Mix both together well and pour into a greased 9-inch iron skillet.
Bake 50 to 60 minutes at 350°.

title: french vinaigrette
directions: Add small amounts of oil to mustard and stir each time.
Once the oil is done, add small amounts of vinegar and stir each time. Add condiments to taste.

title: irish potato candy(easy)
directions: Mash potato and combine thoroughly with sugar and vanilla. (If mixture is too stiff, add 1 teaspoon milk.)
Roll out on lightly floured surface.
Spread with peanut butter.
Roll up like a jelly roll and cut into circles.
Candy will have pinwheel look.

title: crabmeat imperial
directions: Saute peppers in butter.
Add salt, pepper, mustard, mayonnaise and Worcestershire sauce.
Gently add crab and place mixture in casserole.
Combine pimentos, crumbs, butter and paprika.
Sprinkle on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until crumbs are brown.

title: granny's biscuits
directions: Mix flour and lard until well combined.
Make well in middle of mixture; pour in buttermilk.
Stir until mixed.
Knead dough until it isn't real moist.
Cut or pinch into shape for cooking. Bake at 450° until golden.

title: spicy lasagne
directions: In Dutch oven, saute onion and garlic in drippings and oil until tender.
Add next 7 ingredients.
In bowl, mix Ricotta, Swiss cheese and egg.

title: fluff frosting
directions: Cook the milk and flour until thick.
Set aside until cold. Cream the margarine and sugar until very fluffy and white.
After flour mixture is very cold, blend the two mixtures together.
Add the vanilla.
Frost cold cake and refrigerate until set.

title: marinated vegetable toss
directions: Combine all vegetables in a salad bowl; pour Italian dressing over.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: festive fruit cake(needs no baking)
directions: Starting school at Kernville, and having only 9 students in my Kindergarten class.
That was in 19__.

title: randy's favorite spaghetti sauce
directions: Mix all together (except hamburger) in a crock-pot.
Cook for 8 hours on low.
Add browned hamburger before serving.
Makes 8 to 12 servings.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream butter, sugar and egg together.
Add biscuit mix, nuts and chips.
Bake at 375° on ungreased cookie sheet for 10 minutes.

title: chicken ala ethal
directions: Boil and simmer chicken about 1 1/2 hours.
Lightly grease 9 x 13-inch pan.
Put chicken in bottom of pan.
Mix soup and milk together; pour over chicken.
Layer Swiss cheese on top of chicken. Mix stuffing mix with melted butter and put over chicken and other mixture.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.

title: cheesy potatoes
directions: Mix and place in a 3-quart casserole dish or a 10 x 13-inch aluminum cake pan.
Bake in 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: creamy tomato soup
directions: Melt margarine in a soup pot over low heat.
Add onion, carrot and garlic.
Cook, covered, for 20 minutes, stirring occasionally, until vegetables are tender.

title: santa fe wild rice soup(serves 4)
directions: In a large saucepan over medium heat, combine corn, onion, carrot and 1 can chicken broth and bring to a boil. Reduce heat and simmer 10 to 15 minutes or until onion is tender. Stir in remaining chicken broth, wild rice, green chili peppers, chili powder, cumin, oregano and cayenne pepper. Simmer, uncovered, about 5 minutes or until heated through. Top each bowl with fresh tomato salsa; sprinkle with cilantro and serve.

title: rhubarb crunch
directions: Combine flour, oatmeal, brown sugar, cinnamon and margarine until crumbly.
Press half mix in 9-inch square pan.
Cover with rhubarb.
Set aside.

title: spinach - orange salad(with honey vinaigrette dressing)
directions: Remove coarse stems from spinach, then wash and dry leaves. Tear spinach into bite sized pieces; add orange slices and onion; toss gently to mix.
Mix together vinegar, oil, honey, salt and pepper; pour over spinach.
Sprinkle almonds over the top.
Serves 4.

title: cheese ball
directions: Beat cheese and mayonnaise until smooth.
Stir in next 5 ingredients.
Cover; chill several hours.
Form into ball; roll in nuts to coat.

title: baked scallops
directions: Grease a baking dish.
Put in scallops.
Cover with cream. Mix cracker crumbs and butter.
Spread cracker crumb mixture on top of scallops.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: butterfinger cake
directions: Bake cake as directed on box.
Remove from oven and punch holes in cake.
Pour milk into holes and over cake.
Pour topping into holes and over cake.
Let chill until set.
Cover with Cool Whip and top with crushed Butterfinger candy bar.

title: quick cheeseburger pie
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Prepare pastry.
Pat in bottom and up sides of quiche dish, 8 x 2-inch, or round pan, 8 x 1 1/2-inch. Bake 15 minutes.

title: sausage rice casserole
directions: Saute sausage; remove and drain from grease.
Saute pepper, onion and celery, then drain.
Cook 1/2 cup of rice in 4 cups of water for 20 minutes.

title: delicious angel food pound cake
directions: Mix the first 5 ingredients together with mixer; beat for 15 minutes.
Sift 1 cup flour and fold in.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour in a tube pan.
This cake can be split and filled or melt preserves and pour over cake.

title: creole black-eyed peas and polenta
directions: Combine 3 cups water and salt in a medium saucepan; bring to a boil. Add polenta in a slow, steady stream, stirring constantly. Reduce heat to medium and cook 20 minutes, stirring constantly, until mixture pulls away from sides of pan. Add Parmesan cheese, stirring until cheese melts.
Spoon polenta mixture into a 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan coated with vegetable cooking spray. Set aside and let cool completely.

title: german chocolate pie
directions: Stir dry ingredients together well.
Add other ingredients, except nuts.
Mix well.
Pour in 9-inch unbaked pie shell. Sprinkle nuts on top.
Bake 50 minutes at 350°.

title: banana waldorf
directions: Use well chilled fruit.
Prepare it and combine all ingredients.
Mix well and serve immediately on top of lettuce leaf or some sprouts.
Yields 6 small servings.

title: island ecstasy cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Prepare cake mix according to package directions.
Bake in a greased and floured glass pan, 13 x 9 x 2-inch, for 30 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean.

title: beer quick bread
directions: In a large bowl, mix flour, sugar, baking powder, baking soda and salt.
Add beer; mix just until evenly moistened.
Spread batter to make level in an oiled 4 1/2 x 8 1/2-inch loaf pan. Bake in a 400° oven until loaf is well browned, about 45 minutes. Invert onto a rack.

title: chocolate caramel bars
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Beat eggs, sugar, mayonnaise and vanilla at medium speed with electric mixer; add flour and baking soda. Set aside one cup of this batter.
Spread remaining batter into lightly greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes, or until lightly browned.
Cool for 10 minutes.

title: old fashioned rice pudding
directions: Combine all together in a 2 1/2-quart baking dish.
Raisins and cinnamon are optional and amounts to use are flexible.
I use 1/2 to 3/4 cup raisins and 1 1/2 teaspoons cinnamon.
Cover dish for 1 1/2 hours, stirring every 1/2 hour, then remove lid and finish baking total baking time is approximately 2 1/4 hours (depending on your oven.)

title: no bake cookies
directions: In large saucepan, combine first 4 ingredients.
Bring to a rolling boil over medium heat.
Stir constantly.
Boil for 5 minutes while stirring.
Remove from heat and add vanilla.
Add peanut butter, if desired.
Add oats.
Drop by rounded spoonfuls onto lightly buttered foil.
Cool completely.

title: poppy seed cake
directions: 1. Preheat oven to 350°.

title: ham loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients together except the tomato juice.
Bake 1 hour.
Pour the tomato juice over top and bake 1 more hour.

title: garden cabbage salad
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients.
Cover and refrigerate.
To serve, toss with dressing.

title: snow flurries
directions: Cream together sugar, lemon peel, butter and shortening.
Beat in eggs, vanilla and almond extract.
Combine flour, salt and baking powder.
Stir into sugar mixture.
Chill dough 1 hour. Roll dough and cut into snow flurries with 3 inch star cookie cutter.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet 10 minutes.
Sandwich 2 stars together with 1/8 teaspoon jam with points off angle.
Sift powdered sugar over cookies.

title: coconut pie
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients; cook until hot.
Add 5 egg yolks; cook until thick.
Remove from heat; add vanilla and coconut. Pour into baked pie shells.

title: kelly's turtles
directions: Melt caramels
and
evaporated milk in a double boiler. Put pecans in
after
melting and mix together.
Drop by spoon onto greased wax paper.	Set until hard.

title: chicken pie
directions: Boil chicken in plenty of salted water, then take meat off the bone and cut up in small pieces.
For the crust and dumplings, sift together flour and salt.
Add shortening and blend, then add water to mixture.
Grease Pyrex and line with strips of dough. Layer chicken, dough and black pepper to your taste.
Dot with margarine.
Keep layering until out of chicken.
On last layer, pour chicken broth (enough to nearly reach the top) and add top layer.
Make a few holes in top.
Cook at 350° until top crust is brown.

title: okra fritters
directions: Make batter with ingredients (except okra).
Stir in mixture 1 cup sliced okra.
Drop by teaspoon into hot fat until golden brown.

title: rice pudding
directions: Put all the ingredients in a double boiler except eggs.
Cook rice until done and then add eggs.
Put in greased dish and bake 1 1/2 hours in a 350° oven.

title: oatmeal candy
directions: Bring sugar, cocoa, milk and butter to boil in a pan and cook for 30 seconds.
Add oats, peanut butter and vanilla.
Drop by spoon onto wax paper; let cool.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Saute onion in a little butter; add drained can and green beans, mushroom soup (undiluted) and cheese.
Bake 10 minutes at 400°.
Add onion rings on top.
Bake for 2 minutes, then serve.

title: cranberry-orange nut bread
directions: Combine Bisquick, sugar, flour, egg, milk and orange peel. Beat vigorously 1/2 minute.
Stir in cranberries and nuts.
Pour into greased loaf pan.
Bake 1 hour at 350° or until toothpick comes out clean.
Remove from pan.
Cool thoroughly before slicing.

title: hot rolls
directions: Dissolve 2 teaspoons of warm water with yeast and add to all other ingredients.
Then work it into a large ball.
Grease slightly.
Cover in bowl.
Refrigerate and use in small or large quantities the next day.
Make into rolls and sit about 1 hour before baking.
Cook at 475° for 15 minutes or until brown.

title: just for fun punch
directions: Put ice cream and sherbet in large bowl.
Add liquids, and beat with mixer until well blended.

title: grandma's fudge
directions: Mix sugar and cocoa thoroughly.
Add milk and cream.
Mix well.
Heat butter until foamy.
Set aside.
Bring to boil sugar, cocoa, milk, and cream.
Cook for 10 min. stirring constantly. Add butter.
Cook 5 min. more.
Add 1 Tbsp. vanilla.
Let cool. Add flour; enough to thicken for spreading in cookie sheet.

title: spenny's favorite chicken
directions: In a saucepan, cook onion in margarine until tender. Stir in tomato soup, beer, curry powder, oregano and pepper (dash). Simmer, uncovered, 10 minutes.
Arrange chicken breasts in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour tomato mixture over chicken.
Bake, uncovered, 50 to 55 minutes at 350°.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.

title: cream cheese cookies
directions: Cream butter and cheese.
Blend in egg yolk and vanilla.
Add dry cake mix, 1/3 at a time, mixing well after each addition.
(If mixer is used, add last third of cake mix by hand.)
Cover; chill 30 minutes.
Heat oven to 375°.
Drop by level teaspoonfuls onto ungreased baking sheet.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes or until light brown.
Cool slightly before removing from baking sheet.

title: poor man's pound cake
directions: Put ingredients in a large bowl and beat at high speed for 10 minutes.
Pour into tube pan.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: sinful potatoes
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: delicious casserole
directions: Put in baking dish.
Cook at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes. Toward the last, cover with crumbs, grated cheese and almonds.

title: peanut butter and jelly dip
directions: In small bowl combine ingredients; mix well.
Serve with sliced apples, celery, carrots, etc.
Refrigerate leftovers. Makes 1 cup.

title: stuffed baked potatoes
directions: Scrub and bake potatoes at 400° for 1 hour.
Meanwhile, prepare filling:
steam saute onion, carrots, broccoli and cauliflower until tender (8 minutes).
Add bell pepper and spices and saute a couple minutes longer.
Add more distilled water in vegetable soup stock; cover and steam until bell pepper is tender.
Stir in almond cheese and Bragg liquid aminos to taste.
Set aside.
After potatoes are cool enough to handle, make a lengthwise cut in the top of each one and remove half of the potato pulp, leaving 1/2-inch rim of the vegetable/cheese mixture.
Lower oven temperature to 350° and stuff the potato shells.
Place on a nonstick baking dish and cover with parchment paper and bake for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: chili
directions: Brown (in large pan) ground beef.
Add onions, celery and garlic and cook until soft.
Add tomatoes and tomato sauce.
Cook about 1 hour; add green pepper.
Cook 2 to 3 minutes.
Add kidney beans and heat.
Serve over mashed or baked potatoes.
Top with shredded Cheddar cheese.

title: corned beef and noodles
directions: Mix well.
Bake in oven for half hour at 350°.

title: my mother's cake
directions: Cream margarine and sugar; add eggs.
Beat until smooth.
Add milk and vanilla; beat in flour.
Grease and flour three 8 or 9-inch pans.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Cake will be golden brown.

title: texas squash skillet
directions: In a large skillet, saute onion, green pepper and garlic. Stir in squash, tomatoes and seasoning.
Cook over low heat, stirring occasionally, until squash is tender.
Sprinkle cheese over top and serve.

title: scooby snacks
directions: Cut bologna and cheese into little squares to fit on a cracker. Put one piece of bologna and one piece of cheese between two crackers.
Good for munchies.

title: vanilla ice cream
directions: Beat eggs, then slowly add other ingredients.
Pour into freezer can of ice cream maker.
Add enough whole milk to fill can to freezer line.
Very good.

title: poppy seed dressing
directions: In blender, put vinegar, sugar, salt and dry mustard; blend. Slowly add the oil, then the poppy seed.
Add water last.
Blend until mixed well.
Goes great over salads.
Makes 1 quart.
Lasts up to 1 month in refrigerator.

title: my own jiffy mix
directions: Combine all ingredients and work with hands like pie dough. Store in tight container.
Keep in refrigerator.
This can be used as Bisquick.

title: tropical cooler
directions: Pour fruit juices into a large pitcher; stir to mix.
Just before serving, stir in lemonade.
Pour into glasses containing crushed ice.
Makes about 20 tall drinks.

title: italian bread
directions: Combine yeast in water in mixing bowl.
Add sugar.
Let stand about
5 minutes.
Add
salt
and
butter.
Stir
until dissolved. Add 3 1/2 cups flour.
Mix
to blend, then beat at medium speed until smooth and elastic (about 5 minutes).
Beat in 2 eggs.
Then gradually add
cups more flour.
Turn dough onto board and coat with
1/2 cup of flour.
Knead 10 to 15 minutes.
Turn dough into greased bowl.
Cover and let rise 1 1/2 hours.

title: buttery biscuit bread
directions: Melt margarine in large skillet in a 400° oven. Mix flour and buttermilk. Pour mixture over melted margarine. Use a small glass to make indentions in the dough, but
do not cut through the dough. Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes. This bread has a very buttery, crusty bottom.

title: *broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli as directed; drain.
Mix mayonnaise, chicken soup, 1 cup of cheese and eggs with broccoli.
Pour into casserole dish and sprinkle other cup of cheese and top with
Ritz crackers. Pour melted margarine on crackers.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.

title: crunchy top chicken
directions: Boil chicken.
Place in bottom of Pyrex dish.
Add a layer of Swiss cheese.
Spoon out soup and smooth over cheese.
Melt margarine and mix with 2 cups stuffing mix.
Spread mixture on top. Cover and bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: crackers
directions: Put in brown grocery bag.
Dump oil on top.
Shake bag.

title: bourbon cake
directions: Combine cherries, raisins and bourbon.
Cover and let stand overnight.
Drain fruits; reserve bourbon.
Cream butter or margarine and sugars together until light.
Add ege yolks and beat well. Combine 1/2 cup flour and pecans.
Sift remaining 4 1/2 cups flour, nutmeg and baking powder together. Add flour mixture and bourbon alternately to butter or margarine mixture, beating well after each addition.
Beat egg whites until stiff, but not dry.
Fold egg whites into flour mixture.
Fold soaked fruits and pecan-flour mixture into batter.
Turn into greased 10-inch tube pan lined with greased waxed paper.
Bake in slow oven (275°) for 3 1/2 hours.
Cool.
Remove from pan.
fill center of cake with cheesecloth which is saturated with bourbon.
Wrap in heavy waxed paper or aluminum foil.
Store in tightly covered container.
Keep in cool place.

title: *oyster stew
directions: Put all ingredients, except oysters, in crock-pot.
Cover and cook on high for 1 1/2 hours; stir well.
Add oysters and cook on low for 1 to 3 hours.
Serve hot.

title: taffy apple salad
directions: Cook flour, pineapple, vinegar, sugar and egg over medium heat until thick.
Cool in refrigerator.
Cut up apples.
Soak in salt water to keep fresh.
Drain apples and mix with cooled sauce, Cool Whip and 1/2 peanuts.
Top with remaining peanuts.

title: vegetable chow mein
directions: In small bowl combine soy sauce, water and cornstarch.
Mix to dissolve cornstarch; set aside.
Heat both types of oil in a nonstick skillet or wok over medium-high heat.
Add onions, celery, carrots and water chestnuts.
Add about 2 tablespoons water.
Cover and cook 5 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Add a little more water if necessary to prevent sticking.
Add bean sprouts, mushrooms, pea pods and bamboo shoots.
Mix well, cover and cook 3 minutes.
Add soy mixture and cook, uncovered, stirring constantly 1 minute.

title: poppy seed dressing
directions: Mix mustard, salt and sugar.
Add other ingredients and mix well.
May use mixer or blender.
Store in refrigerator.
Makes 1 1/2 cups.

title: aunt helen's sweet 'n sour relish
directions: Heat on medium-high stove the vinegar, sugar and salt until sugar dissolves (do not boil).
Pour over onions, pepper and cucumbers.
Let cool.
Refrigerate for 24 hours.
Serve with favorite entree.

title: german skillet dinner
directions: Melt butter in large skillet.
Spread sauerkraut over bottom. Layer remaining ingredients in order given over sauerkraut.
Cook tightly covered over low heat for 50 minutes.

title: scarlett's favorite potato rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Stir in sugar, salt, shortening, eggs, potatoes and 4 cups of the flour.
Beat until smooth.
Mix in 3 to 3 1/2 more cups flour with spoon until easy to handle.
Knead dough until smooth and elastic on a lightly floured surface.
Place in a greased bowl and turn greased side up.
Cover tightly and refrigerate overnight.
(Dough can be kept up to 5 days covered and in refrigerator.)
Punch down dough, take out amount you need. Roll out dough and cut with a biscuit cutter.
Let rise about an hour.
Bake 15 minutes in 400° oven.

title: pecan pie
directions: Cream butter to soften.
Add sugar gradually and cream until fluffy.
Add syrup and salt; beat well.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating thoroughly after each.
Stir in pecans.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake 50 minutes at 350°.

title: italian macaroni pie
directions: Once pocketed as a sandwich for Cornish miners, this is great as a meal for picnics and hikes today.

title: lemon sour cream pie
directions: Combine 1 cup sugar, cornstarch and salt in small saucepan. Stir in milk.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until thick, about 15 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Stir 1/4 of the hot mixture gradually into beaten egg yolks.
Pour egg mixture into saucepan, stirring constantly.
Cook and stir over medium heat 2 minutes.
Stir in butter and juice.
Cool 20 minutes.
Stir in sour cream.
Pour into prepared pie crust.

title: corn flake macaroons
directions: With only 4 ingredients, this cheesecake is almost too good to be true!
Top with fresh fruit in season.

title: mock cream cheese
directions: Rinse cottage cheese in a strainer to get rid of any liquid. Place cottage cheese in a blender with the cream cheese spread and blend until smooth.
Yields 1 cup (16 tablespoons).

title: cheese logs
directions: Have all ingredients at room temperature.
Mix all together, except chili powder.
Form into logs or balls and roll in the chili powder and pecans (optional).
Refrigerate.

title: christmas dessert
directions: Make jello according to package directions using part pineapple juice.
When partially set, add all other ingredients except cherries.
When all is set, top with opposite color cherries.

title: baked spaghetti
directions: Brown hamburger; drain fat.
Add spaghetti sauce to hamburger. Cook spaghetti; set aside.
In a 9-inch baking pan, layer spaghetti, sauce and soup.
Repeat layers.
Put cheese on top and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Bake with foil on top.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli; drain.
Combine all ingredients except crackers and butter.
Grease with butter all sides of baking dish to be used.
Pour in mixture and top with Ritz crackers, crumbled and pat with butter.
Bake for 45 to 50 minutes at 350° or until brown.

title: marinated cabbage slaw
directions: Pour 1 cup of sugar over cabbage, green pepper and onion.
Put in covered bowl and refrigerate overnight.
Pour vinegar, oil, salt and seed over mixture without stirring.
Refrigerate at least 4 hours or overnight, then mix and serve.

title: dock street dressing
directions: Beat all ingredients. Makes 1 1/4 cups.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Mix dry ingredients together.
Drain fruit cocktail; reserve juice.
Add eggs to juice; beat well. Drain pineapple; dispose of juice.
Add egg mix to dry mix; mix well.
Add fruit and mix well.
Pour into ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 1 hour.
Mix 1 1/2 cups sugar, milk and butter together.
Bring to boil and add vanilla.
Pour over all ready cut cake.
Serve.

title: fried venison
directions: Heat bacon fat in skillet and brown venison on both sides. Add celery and onions; brown.
Add Worcestershire sauce and tomatoes; cook 1 to 2 hours, until tender.
Cook noodles, drain and serve with meat.

title: fried pies
directions: Cook apples or peaches with sugar on low until there is no juice. Using biscuit dough for crust, roll out small amount, then fill with cooled fruit. Close with fork and deep fry.

title: swedish strawberry pancakes
directions: Beat eggs just to blend.
Add cream.
Sift in dry ingredients; beat with rotary beater until batter is smooth.
Let stand for 2 hours to allow batter to thicken.
Heat griddle to 375° or until water "dances" when dropped onto it.
Butter lightly.
Beat batter again.
Drop 2 tablespoons of batter for each pancake.
Turn when brown.
Fill each pancake with strawberries and roll up.
Arrange 3 on each serving plate.
Sift powdered sugar over all and top middle pancake with whipped cream.
Garnish with a "perfect" strawberry on top.
The pancakes themselves, without the filling, are good with just strawberry butter.

title: barbecue hamburgers
directions: Brown meat and onion.
In separate pan, place 1 tablespoon shortening, celery, lemon juice, vinegar, Worcestershire sauce, catsup, brown sugar and mustard.
Cook 1/2 hour.
Combine with cooked meat.

title: french salad dressing
directions: Mix together in jar and shake well.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Mix and put in casserole dish.
Cover.

title: chicken mexicali (hot)
directions: Saute onions in butter until tender.
Blend in flour.
Add broth, milk, sauce and seasonings.
Cook until smooth and creamy. Stir in other ingredients except cheese and spoon into 2-quart casserole.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: cocoa divinity cake
directions: Sift
flour,
sugar,
cocoa,
cream of tartar, soda and salt in
mixing
bowl.
Add shortening and 2/3 cup of milk and vanilla. Beat
until
well
blended.
Add
egg, unbeaten, and blend well. Then
add remaining milk and beat about 1 minute. Put in loaf pan and bake 30 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: french dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients together and refrigerate.

title: busy day brownies
directions: In a large bowl of electric mixer, combine all ingredients and beat just until blended. Spread mixture in greased 9 x 13-inch baking pan. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cool and cut into 1 1/2-inch squares. Enjoy!

title: pork chops with rice
directions: Brown pork chops
on both sides in a heavy skillet.
In a 2 quart
casserole
dish
place
rice,
water and soup.
Lay chops on mixture	and
top
each	with sliced onion, strips of bell pepper
and sliced tomatoes.
Season to taste.
Cover and bake 1 hour at 350°.
Serves 4.

title: gourmet beef
directions: Cut sirloin across grain in 1/8-inch slices.
Sprinkle with flour and mustard.

title: corn relish
directions: In saucepan, blend cornstarch and water.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cook and stir over medium heat until mixture thickens and boils.
Chill.
Makes 2 cups.

title: jewish apple cake
directions: Mix all the ingredients together.
Using Bundt pan start with batter.
Layer the batter, then apples.
Sprinkle with cinnamon and sugar.
Then repeat the layering of ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours in a greased and floured Bundt pan.

title: creamy banana pudding
directions: In large bowl, combine sweetened condensed milk and water.
Add pudding mix, beat well.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Spoon 1 c. pudding mixture into a 2 1/2 q.t bowl.
Layer with wafers, banana and pudding.
Repeat layering twice, end with pudding.
Chill thoroughly.

title: linda's pork tenderloin
directions: Mix saltines with salt and pepper to taste.
Pound filets to 1/4-inch thickness.
Dip in beaten egg, then in saltines.
Let set for 15 minutes.
Fry in butter until brown.
Mix together soup, 2 cans milk and garlic salt to taste.
Put filets in pan and pour sauce over.
Bake at 325° for 2 hours in oven or on simmer in an electric frypan.
Serve with rice or noodles.

title: mexican fudge(kids' favorite)
directions: Put 1 package cheese in baking dish. Add egg to taco sauce. Mix and layer over cheese.
Put second package of cheese on top. Bake at 350° approximately 15 minutes.
Serve with chips as snack.

title: meat loaf
directions: In a large mixing bowl combine all ingredients and mix with hands for a good blend.
Shape into 1 large loaf or 2 smaller ones.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: cherry-o-pie
directions: Soften cream cheese to room temperature and then beat until fluffy. Gradually add milk while mixing. Blend well. Add lemon juice and vanilla. Pour into prepared crust and chill for 2 hours in refrigerator (do not freeze). Add cherry pie filling to top. Keep in refrigerator.

title: crazy cake
directions: Mix the first 5 dry ingredients together in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Do Not Grease. Pour liquids on top and stir until moist. Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix dry pudding mix, Tang and fruit juices.
Stir in fruit. Chill well before serving.

title: homemade ice cream
directions: Beat eggs and sugar.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well. Pour into electric freezer and freeze.

title: baking powder biscuits
directions: Sift flour, baking powder and salt together in large mixing bowl.
Cut shortening into flour mixture with 2 knives or a pastry blender, until mixture looks like meal.
Add milk to flour mixture; stir quickly with fork just enough to make a soft ball. Put dough on lightly floured board or wax paper and knead 6 or 8 times, forming a ball.
Roll dough 1/4-inch thick for crusty biscuits and 1/2-inch for soft biscuits.
Cut with floured cutter.
Bake at 425° to 450° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: low-fat graham cracker pudding pie
directions: In a 9 x 13 pan, layer graham crackers. Mix pudding and milk and fold in Cool Whip. Put half of mixture on top of graham crackers. Add another layer of graham crackers. Put another layer of mixture on top of graham crackers. Cover with Saran Wrap and refrigerate overnight. Top with chocolate Cool Whip and serve.

title: date-nut loaf bread
directions: Pour boiling water over dates; let stand.
Cream oleo, sugar and egg.
Add water and dates to creamed mixture.
Add flour sifted with soda and salt, vanilla and nuts.
Pour into bread loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour.
Wrap in foil 1 day before slicing.

title: peach bran muffins
directions: Combine liquid ingredients.
Combine and mix dry ingredients; add liquid to dry and mix only until moistened.
Do not overmix. Fill greased or paper-lined muffin cups and bake in a preheated 350° oven for 15 to 18 minutes.
Makes 12 to 15 muffins.

title: funnel cakes
directions: Mix all ingredients together to make a batter.
Put oil in electric skillet about 1/2-inch deep.
Pour batter in a circle from a funnel or spouted pitcher.
Turn once.
Remove from oil to paper towel to drain and sprinkle top with powdered sugar.

title: corn loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients except cheese and cook 1 hour in 300° oven.
When almost done, sprinkle cheese on top and let melt.

title: boyfriend cookies
directions: Cream together butter, sugar and brown sugar.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix and drop on ungreased pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes or until brown.

title: cafe viennese(microwave)
directions: Combine all ingredients except water in small bowl (mix may be stored in airtight container).
Place 1 tablespoon mixture in serving mug.
Fill with water.
Stir to blend.
Heat on full power for 1 1/2 to 2 minutes or until heated through and temperature of 190° is reached.
Yields 14 (6 ounce) servings.

title: baked rice
directions: Combine ingredients in a 2-quart baking dish.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Check rice as it bakes to see if more liquid is needed.
If so, add a little water.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Tear up bread and place in a greased 9 x 13-inch baking pan. Brown and drain sausage.
Cut links in slices.
Spoon sausage over bread.
Sprinkle with grated Cheddar cheese.
Beat together eggs, milk, mustard, salt and pepper.
Pour over mixture.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Can prepare the night before.

title: sugarless apple pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Pour into pie shell and cover with top crust.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until done.

title: linda's cheese balls
directions: Soften cheeses at room temperature and cream together.
Add chopped green peppers and garlic salt.
Add hot sauce, Worcestershire sauce and barbecue sauce by drops and flavor to taste.
Form into ball and roll ball in chopped nuts.
Refrigerate an hour or so, or until firm.
Serve with crackers of choice.
You may add any ingredients you like or change it in any way to obtain the flavor you desire.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add mashed bananas.
Add salt, soda and flour to this mixture.
Bake at 350° in greased loaf pan for 1 hour.

title: grandma's pumpkin pies
directions: Beat until smooth.
Pour in pie crust.
Bake 15 minutes at 425°, then 45 minutes at 325° to 350°.
Makes 2 deep or 3 regular pies.

title: oreo sunday
directions: Blend cookies and margarine.
Press into 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Slice ice cream.
Cover with cookie mixture.
Sprinkle pecans over ice cream and freeze.

title: refrigerator yeast muffins
directions: Mix flour, sugar and yeast in a large bowl.
In a small bowl, mix egg, oil and water.
Add to flour mixture.
Fill greased muffin tin 2/3 full.
Bake at 400° for about 20 minutes.
Mix will keep in refrigerator for a week if tightly covered, but leave enough room to rise.

title: chocolate valentine's cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease 2 heart shaped pans, line bottom with waxed paper and dust with flour.
Stir together boiling water and cocoa until smooth, set aside.
Cream shortening and sugar in large bowl, blend in eggs, vanilla and salt.
Stir baking soda into the buttermilk.
Add cocoa/water mixture.
Combine with other ingredients and blend thoroughly.
Pour into prepared pans. Bake 30 to 35 minutes.
Cool 10 minutes.
Remove from pans and cool completely.
Frost with fudge frosting and pipe edges with pastel frosting.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix up all ingredients.
Put in refrigerator for 1/2 hour. Take out and shape into 1 or 2 balls.
Roll in crushed nuts.

title: graham cracker iced cream cake
directions: Whip cream until slightly stiff.
Add 1/4 c sugar and capful of vanilla and 2 tsp of chocolate.
Put layer of crackers on a plate. Cover with cream.
Alternate layers of crackers and cream.
Cover top and all sides of cake and drizzle chocolate syrup over all.

title: microwave honey coated carrots
directions: Place all ingredients in 1-quart casserole.
Cover.
Microwave on High for 4 minutes.
Stir.
Continue cooking 4 more minutes. Rest for 5 minutes.

title: spiced pecans
directions: Butter 2 cookie sheets.
Combine sugar, salt, allspice and cinnamon.
Stir in water and corn syrup.
Cook over medium heat until 235° on candy thermometer (soft ball water test).
Add nuts and vanilla; stir until thickens.
Coat pecan halves; place on cookie sheets and separate pieces.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Pour water over oatmeal and butter.
Let stand for 20 minutes. Add sugar, brown sugar, baking soda, flour, eggs, salt, cinnamon and vanilla to mixture.
Place in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes.
In a pot, melt butter.
Add brown sugar, cream, coconut and nuts.
Simmer.
Pour over the cake and then bake for an additional 5 to 10 minutes.

title: sweet muffins
directions: Heat
oven
Grease
muffin
pans.
Beat egg; stir in	milk
and
oil.
Mix
in remaining ingredients until flour is moistened.	Batter should be lumpy.
Fill muffin cups 2/3 full. Bake 20 to 25 minutes or until golden brown.

title: boiled cookies
directions: Mix together sugar, cocoa, margarine and milk. Boil 1 1/2 minutes. Remove from heat. Add peanut butter, oatmeal, nuts, raisins and vanilla extract. Drop by spoonfuls on wax paper and let cool.

title: chocolate delight
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients and pour into 8 x 8-inch baking dish. Bake at 375° for 20 minutes. Beat together next 3 items and spread over cooled crust. Make pudding, using 3 cups milk and pour over cheese mixture. Top with Cool Whip and sprinkle with chopped pecans.

title: lattice-top chicken
directions: Combine milk, soup, salt, chicken, vegetables, 1/2 cup cheese and 1/2 can onions.
Place in 8 x 12-inch baking dish.
Bake, covered, at 375° for 20 minutes.

title: emergency steak
directions: Mix together; pat into t-bone steak shape, 1 inch thick. Broil 8 to 15 minutes at 500°.
Turn once.
Makes 6 steaks.

title: chocolate oatmeal cookies
directions: In double boiler combine first 4 ingredients.
Bring to a rolling boil.
Remove from heat.
Let cool for 5 minutes.
Add oatmeal, peanut butter and vanilla to mixture.
Drop on wax paper with teaspoon.
Let cool.

title: homemade french dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients in shaker.
Shake well and serve.
It is best if you shake dressing before each use.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Beat first 4 ingredients until light and fluffy.
Mix dry ingredients and add alternately with 1 cup milk.
Add 1 teaspoon vanilla.
Bake in greased, floured tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: *Can use butter or margarine for either or both.

title: dill dip
directions: Mix at least 2 hours ahead.

title: chicken deviled eggs
directions: Cut eggs lengthwise in half.
Remove yolks and place in a small bowl.

title: apple cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Grease and flour tube pan. Pour mixture into pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: crystal garden
directions: Mix and place in dish and add blotter paper (cut into shapes like trees, etc., if desired).

title: chess cake
directions: Mix cake mix, 2 eggs and melted margarine.
Pour into a 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan; spread evenly.
Mix cream cheese, sugar and 2 eggs well.
Spread over cake batter.
Sprinkle chopped nuts on top. Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: salt water taffy
directions: Combine sugar and cornstarch in saucepan.
Add corn syrup, salt, margarine and water.
Stir to combine.

Bring to a boil over medium heat, stirring constantly, and cook until sugar dissolves. Continue cooking to hard ball stage, 255°, or until a small amount forms a hard ball when tested in very cold water. Stir gently until vanilla is well blended.
Pour into well buttered 9-inch square pan.
Let stand until cool enough to handle.
Pull until taffy has a satin-like finish and light color.
Pull into long strip, 1/2-inch wide.
Cut in 1-inch pieces with scissors.
Wrap individually in waxed paper.

title: portuguese rice pudding
directions: In medium-size pan, bring the milk to a boil.
Drizzle the rice in slowly so that the milk continues to boil.
Add sugar, cinnamon, salt, rind and butter; stir occasionally.
Boil, uncovered, for about 5 minutes.
Remove the rind and cinnamon stick and pour the mixture into a 2-quart bowl or individual dishes.
Sprinkle lightly with cinnamon.
Serve with a dollop of light cream.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: cheese ball
directions: Soften cream cheese with electric mixer.
Stir in remaining ingredients with a fork.
Chill mixture overnight for at least 4 to 5 hours.
Form into a ball or log and roll in chopped nuts. Garnish with red cherries or parsley.

title: canadian cheese soup
directions: Saute vegetables in broth until tender.
Stir in soup and 2 cups cheese.
Stir until cheese melts.
Garnish with parsley.

title: soft molasses cookies
directions: Cream Crisco; add sugar and the egg, well beaten, then the molasses and hot liquid.
Mix the sifted dry ingredients, spoon onto a warmed, greased pan and bake eight to ten minutes in a moderate oven.

title: apple salad
directions: Mix salad dressing, milk and sugar until blended.
Add the fruit and enjoy!

title: chicken divan(6 servings)
directions: Layer broccoli and chicken in dish.
Mix together soup, mayonnaise, cheese, curry powder and lemon juice and pour over broccoli and chicken.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: joanna gilliam's cheese-apple casserole
directions: Soften cheese and oleo.
Blend until smooth, then add sugar, flour and vanilla.
Blend until smooth.
If not moist enough, take juice from apples and add to cream mixture.

title: chicken linguine
directions: Cook pasta according to package directions, omitting salt and fat.
Set aside.
Melt 1 tablespoon light butter in a large skillet over medium-high heat.
Add chicken, and cook 2 minutes on each side or until lightly browned.
Stir in sherry and 1/2 cup water. Cover, reduce heat to low, and simmer 20 minutes or until done. Drain and reserve liquid.
Cut chicken into 1-inch pieces; set aside.
Melt remaining 1 tablespoon light butter in skillet.
Saute onion and mushroom over medium-high heat 5 minutes or until tender. Stir together flour and 1/2 cup broth.
Add reserved liquid, flour mixture, and remaining 1 1/2 cups broth to skillet.
Cook, stirring often, over medium-high heat until thickened.
Remove from heat. Stir in chicken, sour cream, Monterey Jack cheese, 1/4 cup Parmesan, and pepper.
Spoon mixture into lightly greased 13x9 inch baking dish.
Sprinkle with remaining 1/4 cup Parmesan cheese and breadcrumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until thoroughly heated.
Yield:
8 servings.
Prep:
45 minutes.
Bake 30 minutes.

title: red tomato ketchup
directions: Cook until thickens, 1 to 2 hours.
Makes 3 to 4 pints.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Pile lightly in small baking dish. Sprinkle with 2 ounces shredded American cheese, then 1 cup crushed potato chips.
Bake at 450° for 20 minutes.

title: chicken burritos
directions: Boil and chop or dice chicken.
Put a little chicken on wrap. Sprinkle some cheese and a little barbecue sauce on top.
Roll up burrito wrap.
Place burrito in sprayed baking dish.
Repeat until wraps are done.
Pour cream of chicken soup over burritos. Sprinkle with cheese.
Sprinkle chili powder on top.
Bake at 400 degrees for 15 or 20 minutes.

title: krautsalat(shredded cabbage salad)
directions: Grate the potatoes and onions on the fine side of a grater or through a blender with a little water.
Add the eggs and mix well. Add the matzo meal, salt and pepper and mix again.
Heat the oil in a frying pan and add the mixture, one tablespoon at a time, into the pan.
When the latkes are golden brown, turn them over and brown the other side.
Serves approximately 20.

title: hamburger stroganoff
directions: In skillet, saute onion and garlic in butter over medium heat.
Add ground beef and brown.
Mix in flour, salt, pepper and mushrooms.
Cook 5 minutes.
Stir in soup and simmer, uncovered, 10 minutes.
Add sour cream and heat thoroughly.
Serve over hot noodles and sprinkle with parsley.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Combine sugar, milk and butter.
Stir over medium heat until sugar dissolves.
Cook to firm ball stage (drop small amount in cold water to test).
Remove from heat and add peanut butter, marshmallow cream and vanilla.
Beat until it starts to thicken. Pour into greased pan.
Cool; cut into squares.

title: chocolate brownies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix everything but coconut and nuts; add them last.
Pour into greased pan and bake 25 to 30 minutes or until done.
When cool, frost with Chocolate Icing.

title: holiday pretzel salad
directions: Mix pretzels, butter and 3 tablespoons sugar.
Press into a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.
Cool completely.

title: speedy chicken pie
directions: Combine broth, chicken, eggs, soup, salt and pepper.
Mix flour and milk.
Dot bottom of 3-quart baking dish with oleo. Pour in batter.
Spoon chicken mixture over batter.
Bake at 350° for approximately 40 minutes.

title: blueberry pizza
directions: Melt butter, mix with flour and nuts.
Bake 20 minutes at 350° or until golden brown.
Cool.

title: quick beef stroganoff
directions: Cut meat in 1/4-inch strips.
Brown in hot margarine.
Add onion and garlic salt; cook until onion is tender.
Combine remaining ingredients except noodles.
Add to meat.
Heat through, but do not boil.
Cook 4 ounces noodles in large pot.
Drain. Serve sauce over noodles.
Serves 4 to 5.

title: sawdust salad
directions: The next day combine pineapple juice and flour.
Add beaten egg, sugar and salt.
Cook until thick.
After cooling this, spread it over the Jell-O mixture that has chilled overnight.
Add Cool Whip and whipped cream cheese which have been mixed together. Sprinkle grated cheese over the top of this mixture.

title: popover pizza
directions: Cook beef
and
onion together until brown and onion is tender.
Add
spaghetti
sauce and pour mixture into ungreased 13 x
9-inch
pan.
Arrange
cheese
over
top.
In same bowl, combine eggs, milk, oil, flour and salt.
Mix with mixer until smooth.
Pour batter evenly over cheese in pan.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.

title: crab salad
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Make dressing in separate bowl.

title: impossible cheesecake
directions: Blend milk, vanilla, eggs, sugar and baking mix in blender on high for 20 seconds.
Add cream cheese.
Blend on high 2 minutes. Pour into greased pie plate.
Bake at 350° until center is set (about 35 to 40 minutes).
Cool.
Spread topping of fruit (like strawberry or blueberry).

title: the malice of mary's surprise
directions: Roll lamb in flour and brown with about 3 tablespoons butter for about 15 minutes.
Remove from pan and drain on paper towel.

title: dressed up meat loaf
directions: Thoroughly blend all ingredients.
Press into loaf dish, 9 x 5-inches, or a 9-inch round baking dish with inverted custard cup in center.
Microwave at High (100%) until internal temperature reaches 150°, for 11 to 15 minutes.
If using oven other than Sharp Carousel, rotate meat loaf once or twice during cooking.
Let stand for 3 to 5 minutes.

title: italian sausage stuffed mushrooms
directions: Fry sausage to golden brown and drain well. De-stem mushrooms (save stems). De-gill and discard gills. Chop stems coarse and reserve. Saute chopped stems in olive oil. Add garlic, onion, basil and oregano; cook until mushrooms and onions are translucent. Combine sausage, beaten eggs, mushroom mixture, bread crumbs and Parmesan cheese. Place mushrooms in 9 x 13 pan and stuff with mixture. With remaining mixture, sprinkle pan generously using the entire mixture. Add shredded Mozzarella on top and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: matthew's crock-pot dip
directions: Fry sausage and hamburger until well done.
Drain grease.
Put in crock-pot.
Cut up Velveeta cheese and put in crock-pot.
Add onion and Ro-Tel.
Put lid on pot and let cook until all is melted.

title: savannah deviled crabs
directions: 1. Mix crab meat with mashed boiled eggs. Add 1/2 c. bread crumbs, Worcestershire sauce, Tabasco, Salt, Dressing,
and Mayonaise.
2. Put into crab shells, Cover with remaining 1/2 c. crumbs and melted butter. Bake 15 minutes in moderate

title: barbecue chicken
directions: You can use this sauce to baste chicken as you grill it or place 4 to 6 boneless, skinless chicken breasts in a 2-quart greased casserole and cover with sauce.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 1 hour.
Delicious!

title: chicken pineapple salad
directions: Put chicken into a bowl. Put marshmallow cream into microwave safe bowl and microwave until melted. Mix with softened cream cheese, stir in pineapple juice, pineapple chunks, walnuts and chicken. Chill in refrigerator. Garnish with watermelon, apples, etc. This is so good.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Mix cooked, drained meat and undiluted soups. Place in 2 quart casserole dish. Top with frozen tater tots. Bake at 375° for 35-40 minutes, or until meat mixture is bubbling and potatoes are beginning to brown.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Melt shortening and stir in sugar.
Add unbeaten egg and beat until well blended.
Sift together flour, salt and baking powder; stir into first mixture.
Blend in vanilla, oats and raisins. Drop by teaspoons onto greased baking sheet.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Remove to wire rack to cool.
Makes about 5 dozen cookies.

title: fast and easy whole wheat bread
directions: Stir 2 teaspoons honey into 2/3 cup lukewarm water.
Sprinkle yeast over mixture.
Set aside for 10 minutes.
Combine 3 tablespoons honey with 2/3 cup warm water and combine with yeast mixture.
Stir into flour.
Add salt, wheat germ and 1 1/3 cups warm water.
Dough will be sticky.
Pour dough into a nonstick loaf pan.
Smooth top with wet spatula.
Allow to raise to top of pan. Bake at 400° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Cool 10 minutes on a rack, then turn out of pan.
Cool before slicing.

title: egg custard
directions: Cream butter; add sugar and flour.
Add eggs one at a time. Add milk and then vanilla.
Mix well.
Pour in unbaked pie shell. Bake at 450° for 10 to 15 minutes, then reduce heat to 350° and cook an additional 25 to 30 minutes.

title: king crab au gratin
directions: Melt butter; stir in flour.
Gradually stir in milk, cream, broth.
Cook stirring constantly over low flame until sauce is smooth and thick.
Stir in cheese, salt, paprika, mushrooms, and onion.
Stir until cheese is melted.
Fold in chunks of crab. Pour into greased 2 quart casserole; top with bread crumbs.
Place in 400° oven and bake for 10 -12 minutes or till top brown. Yield: 4 to 6 servings.

title: crock-pot beans
directions: Mix together and cook in crock-pot 4 to 6 hours.

title: sausage roll-ups
directions: Cook lasagna noodles according to package; let cool.
Shred cheese.
Cut sausage to make 8 (2-inch) pieces; cut lengthwise 3/4 of the way through.
Add a small amount of cheese into sausage. Lay out lasagna noodles and roll one sausage per noodle.
Place in baking dish, cover with sauce and cheese.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: light caramel sauce(low-fat)
directions: In small saucepan, combine all ingredients except yogurt; mix well.
Bring to a boil over medium-high heat.
Boil 8 minutes without stirring.
Cool to room temperature.
Add yogurt; blend well.
Makes about 1 cup.
Serve over warm cakes.
Portions 1/9 of a cup, calories:
90; fat:

title: creamy red potatoes
directions: Slice potatoes 1/4-inch thick slices or thinner. Slice onions. Chop or press garlic. Brown potato slices in a skillet with a little olive oil until lightly browned on both sides. Add in onions. Add in garlic. Simmer until onions and garlic have loosened. Slowly add cream, allowing cream to heat as added. Cover skillet. Allow cream to reduce; add salt and pepper to taste.

title: chess pie
directions: Cream margarine and sugar in large mixing bowl.
Beat eggs in separate bowl.
Then add eggs and other ingredients.
Mix very well.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake for one hour at 300°.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: *Or use 3 teaspoons rum flavoring in place of vanilla and almond extracts.

title: orange-cranberry bread
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in large bowl.
Stir in pecans and 2 teaspoons orange rind.
Set aside.
Combine the eggs, orange juice and mayonnaise into a small bowl; mix well.
Stir into dry mixture until flour is just moistened.
Fold in cranberries. Spoon into a greased and floured 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 55 minutes.
Cover with foil and bake additional 10 minutes.
Cool on wire rack.

title: millionaire pie
directions: Mix milk and lemon juice.
Add Cool Whip and pineapple.
Pour into pie crust.
Chill 2 to 3 hours before you serve.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix soup, sour cream and cheese.
Pour over vegetables, then add chicken. Top with Ritz crackers and butter.
Put in 2-quart casserole dish and bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: marinated salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together in large bowl.
Marinate at least 8 hours before serving.
A good diet salad.

title: german chocolate heath cake
directions: Bake the German chocolate cake according to directions in a 9 x 13 pan. While the cake is still warm, punch holes in the cake with a straw or the end of a wooden spoon. Pour Eagle Brand milk over the top of the cake. After cake has cooled, pour on the caramel topping. Spread on the Cool Whip for the topping. Sprinkle the Heath pieces on top. Let set in refrigerator overnight.

title: sausage bread
directions: Cut bread loaf in half. Roll each half into a square. Sprinkle with garlic powder and pepper.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Bring to a boil the milk, sugar and cocoa.
Turn down heat and boil for 3 minutes, stirring once in a while.
Remove from heat and add other ingredients. Drop by spoonfuls onto wax paper.

title: aloha dip
directions: In a bowl, mix together cream cheese and powdered sugar until smooth. Add pineapple and chill until serving time. Serve in a bowl or shape into a ball. Will become firm once chilled. Serve with cookies, crackers, fruit or bagels, etc.

title: banana punch
directions: Melt sugar in hot water.
Cool and mix syrup with orange and pineapple juice.
Mash, then blend, the bananas and the juice from 2 lemons.
Mix all ahead of time and freeze (you can use the juice cans to freeze in or two Ziploc gallon size).
