About 3 to 4 hours before serving, remove from freezer and mash out lumps.
Pour ginger ale over frozen mixture to serve.
Good for open house, weddings and showers.
Can be colored with food coloring.

title: easy fudge
directions: Cut cheese and butter up in saucepan; place over low heat until melted.
Place sugar and cocoa in large bowl; stir together. Pour melted cheese and butter over sugar.
Add vanilla and nuts. Mix well with wooden spoon.
Pour into large pan; chill 1 hour and cut into squares.
(I use large jelly roll pan.)
Store in airtight container.

title: irresistible peanut butter cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Combine peanut butter, Crisco, brown sugar, milk and vanilla in large bowl.
Beat at medium speed of electric mixer until well blended.
Add egg.
Beat until well blended.
Combine flour, salt and baking soda.
Add to creamed mixture at low speed.
Mix until blended.
Make small balls. Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Flatten slightly with fork. Bake at 375° for 7 to 8 minutes.
Cool slightly.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Mix sugar and cinnamon. Roll chilled cookie dough into balls about the size of walnuts. Roll cookie balls in sugar mixture. Place 2 inches apart on cookie sheet. Bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes or until lightly browned, but still soft.

title: jalapeno jelly
directions: Grind peppers (use food processor or blender).
Add sugar and vinegar.
Boil 15 minutes.
Add Certo and boil additional 5 minutes.
Add coloring and pour into sterilized jars.
Serve on Ritz crackers.
Spread with cream cheese and jelly.
Great for parties.

title: coconut-pineapple bread
directions: Add ingredients in order.
Bake in small greased loaf pans at 325° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: pineapple fluff(dietary)
directions: Heat pineapple juice.
Blend in electric blender with gelatin until dissolved.
Add other ingredients and blend.
Makes 4 servings.
Chill or eat while still warm.
Delicious!

title: aunt ellen's oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix and bake according to package directions, but use orange juice instead of water.
If you use 2/3 C. orange juice add about 1 C. more dry oats.
Mix.

title: chicken imperial
directions: Marinate chicken in sherry for 2 to 3 hours.
Pat dry.
Combine crumbs, salt, pepper, cheese, parsley, garlic and 3/4 of almonds. Dip chicken in butter.
Roll in bread crumb mixture.
Arrange in a 9 x 13-inch pan and sprinkle with remaining almonds.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serves 6.

title: mint pie
directions: Mix cookies and hot water.
Spoon into pie crust, spread to cover bottom.
Beat cream cheese until smooth; gradually beat in sugar, milk and peppermint extract.
Fold in whipped topping.

title: no knead bread
directions: Mix in order given.
Handle gently; do not knead.
Let rise once until double.
Make into rolls or loaf.
Let rise.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.

title: hamburger dish
directions: Brown hamburger, onion and celery together until done.
Then add remaining ingredients.
Put into casserole dish and bake for 45 minutes to 1 hour at 350°.

title: pink stuff
directions: Mix jello and cottage cheese together.
Add fruit cocktail, then Cool Whip.
Refrigerate.
Delicious and easy.

title: quick cinnamon rolls
directions: Soak yeast in warm water.
Add milk, sugar, salt, shortening, eggs and flour.
Roll out and spread with butter, brown sugar and cinnamon.
Let rise until light and bake at 350°.
Makes 2 dozen.

title: ukranian goulash
directions: Heat oil, brown meat.
Remove meat, saute onions in pan. Return meat to pan, stir in 1 1/2 c. water.
Add rest of ingredients; bring to a boil.
Place in a baking pan and bake at 300° for 2 hours, keeping tightly covered.

title: pesto
directions: In a food processor, add/mix items one at a time:

title: mrs. butterworth's football crunch
directions: Preheat oven to 250°.
In a large, shallow roasting pan, combine cereal and peanuts.
In 2-quart saucepan, combine syrup, margarine, sugar and cinnamon.
Stirring constantly, bring to a boil over medium heat.
Without stirring, boil 2 minutes.
Pour over cereal mixture; toss to coat well.
Bake 1 hour, stirring occasionally.
Turn out onto waxed paper lined tray.
Break apart cereal as it cools.
Store in tightly covered container.
Makes 5 cups.

title: italian soup
directions: Brown beef and onion with garlic powder and oregano.
Drain any juices or fat from the beef mixture.
Add soups, seasoning and water.
Bring to a boil.
Add the cabbage and cook until the cabbage is tender.
Serve with Parmesan cheese sprinkled on top.

title: sticky buns
directions: Butter 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Sprinkle nuts to cover bottom. Tear one loaf of thawed bread into small pieces and place over nuts.

title: marinated carrots
directions: Bring to a boil the soup, sugar, vinegar, oil and salt.
Pour over the carrots, green pepper and onion.
Let set at least 4 hours.

title: stacked roll stroganoff
directions: Brown meat and drain.
Boil soup (undiluted) and add sour cream.
In casserole dish (2 1/2-quart) layer beef, then mushrooms, onions and then soup mix.*
Repeat layers.
Cut biscuits in half and put on top.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: perfect pie crust
directions: Mix salt and flour.
Cut in Crisco until lumps about the size of peas.
Beat egg in measuring cup.
Pour enough ice water to make 1/2 cup.
Add vinegar.
Stir all ingredients and chill. Makes 4 (9-inch) pie crusts.
Form unused portions in round balls and freeze.
Seems to roll better after being frozen.

title: green tomato relish
directions: Grind or grate all ingredients.
Add 1/2 cup salt.
Let stand 4 hours or overnight.
Drain well.

title: apricot streusel bars
directions: Bring apricots and 2 cups water to a boil.
Cover and simmer 40 minutes.
Drain and reserve 1/4 cup liquid.
Cool slightly. Puree apricots and reserved liquid and 1/4 cup sugar; set aside.

title: no fat rice krispies
directions: Spray large microwavable bowl with Pam and put marshmallows in bowl.
Spray spoon and 9 x 13-inch pan with Pam for later use. Microwave on High for 1 to 2 minutes until melted.
Fold in Rice Krispies with sprayed spoon.
Press mixture into 9 x 13-inch pan. (Spray hand with Pam to keep from sticking.)
Cut and refrigerate.

title: seven layered salad
directions: Place lettuce in bowl.
Top with layer of green onions, layer of celery and layer of water chestnuts.
Sprinkle frozen peas over salad.
Spread
mayonnaise over top.
Sprinkle with sugar.
Add Parmesan cheese, seasoned salt and garlic powder.
Cover and chill 24 hours in refrigerator.
Garnish with crumbled bacon and tomato wedges before serving.

title: power punch
directions: Thaw both frozen concentrates.
Combine with beverage (Pepsi, Coke, etc.).
Serve immediately with or without ice.

title: easy egg sausage puff
directions: Mix
all
ingredients together.
Cover and refrigerate. Heat oven to 350°.
Grease a 2-quart casserole.	Pour mixture into dish and
bake	until knife inserted in center comes out clean, about 1 hour.
Makes 6 servings.

title: fudge bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour a 13 x 9-inch pan. Mix all ingredients together, adding 1 egg at a time.
Pour into prepared pan and bake for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: 7-up meat loaf
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours in a 5 x 9-inch loaf pan.

title: spinach casserole
directions: Cook and drain spinach. Add sour cream and onion soup mix. Spoon into buttered casserole and bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: chicken on sunday
directions: Spread rice over bottom of large 13 1/2 x 8-inch pan.
Combine soups with milk; heat and pour over rice.
Lay pieces of chicken (raw) on top.
Sprinkle dry onion soup mix over top of chicken. Seal tightly with lid or foil.
Bake at 325° for 2 hours and 5 minutes.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Combine salad dressing and seasonings.
Pour over spaghetti and vegetables.
Mix well and chill.

title: velveeta salsa dip
directions: Microwave Velveeta cheese cubes and salsa in 1 1/2-quart microwave bowl on High heat for 5 minutes or until smooth, stirring after 3 minutes.
Stir in cilantro.
Serve hot with tortilla chips or broiled green, red and yellow pepper wedges. Makes 3 cups.

title: pull apart cookies
directions: Layer separated graham crackers on bottom of jelly roll pan. Mix other ingredients and spread over crackers.
Bake in a 350° oven for 10 minutes.
Pull cookies apart while hot and then let cool.

title: pecan tarts
directions: Beat together the eggs, sugar, salt, butter and corn syrup. Pour into tart shells.
Put pecan halves on top of tart shells. Bake at 350° to 375° for approximately 40 minutes or until pie is set and pastry is nicely browned.

title: brownies
directions: Melt chocolate and butter in saucepan.
Remove from heat.
Add sugar and mix well.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Combine flour, baking powder and salt.
Add to chocolate mixture.
Add vanilla and nuts.
Bake in a greased and floured 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Moist and delicious.

title: zucchini bread
directions: In a large bowl stir together all ingredients until you get to * sign.
In another bowl beat eggs, oil and vanilla.
Pour over flour mixture.
Stir until moistened.
Pour into 2 loaf pans or one 9x13 oblong pan.
Do not fill full.
Bake at 350 degrees for 1 hour.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Mix the ingredients.
Roll into small balls.
Cross each ball with a fork.
Bake 13 to 16 minutes.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix sugar, cocoa, cornstarch, add yolks and 1/2 c. milk.
Mix well; Add this to 3 c. milk mix well and cook in microwave, then add butter and vanilla; when thick pour in cooked pie shell. Chill and serve.

title: shortbread
directions: Place all ingredients in a mixing bowl and blend well.
Knead the dough by hand for a moment and form it into a circle 3/4-inch thick on a nonstick baking sheet.
Flute the edge and prick the entire circle with a fork.
Bake at 325° for 1/2 hour.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Place the chicken breasts in a 13-inch casserole dish.
Spread the cheese over the chicken.
On top of the cheese, spread the cream of mushroom soup.
On top of the soup, add the stuffing mix. Then pour melted margarine over the top of the stuffing mix. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: blonde brownies
directions: Melt margarine in saucepan.
Remove from heat.
Add brown sugar and mix well.
Add hot water; cool slightly.
Add slightly beaten egg and vanilla and stir.
Add flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt mixture a little at a time.
Mix well after each addition.
Fold in chips and walnuts.
Sprinkle chopped walnuts over top.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes in greased 9 x 9 x 2-inch pan.

title: bobbi jo's dessert
directions: For low calories, use sugar-free pudding, low-fat milk and Cool Whip.

title: triple chocolate bundt cake
directions: Mix together cake mix, pudding mix, eggs, oil, water and sour cream.
Fold in chocolate chips.
Pour into a greased Bundt pan. Bake in a 325° oven for 1 hour.
Check at 40 to 45 minutes.
Cool; turn onto a plate.
Sift confectioners sugar over it or put whipped cream on each slice when serving.

title: strawberry meringue bars
directions: Cream shortening and 1/3 cup of sugar until fluffy.
Beat in egg yolks.
Stir in flour and mix well.
Press mixture into bottom of ungreased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes or until golden brown.

title: hot chocolate mix
directions: Mix ingredients well.
Store in airtight container.
Use approximately 3 heaping teaspoonfuls of powder per 1 cup of hot chocolate.

title: hopping john
directions: Cook bacon, onion and garlic until bacon is crisp and onion is tender but not brown.
Remove bacon and drain.
Add peas and rice to onion, garlic and bacon drippings.
Cover and reduce heat to simmer; cook 5 minutes.
Add broken bacon bits and serve immediately with cornbread and pickle relish on the side.

title: stuffed peppers
directions: Combine ground beef, onion, 1/2 cup peppers, egg, oatmeal, tomato sauce, salt and pepper.
Shape into balls and press into green peppers that have been cut in half lengthwise.
Bake in a 350° oven in a deep dish casserole until brown on top, about 1 hour.
Can be topped with grated cheese when almost done.
I don't usually cover the casserole, but you can until the last 1/2 hour for more juicy peppers.
For more variety, you can add 1/2 cup of cooked rice to the meat mixture.

title: ham spaghetti casserole
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Cook spaghetti as directed on package. Drain.
Mix spaghetti, ham, sour cream, soup, mushrooms, onion, mustard and Worcestershire sauce.
Pour into ungreased baking dish, 11 x 3/4 x 7-inches.
Mix bread crumbs and butter.
Mix 1/2 cup cheese and the buttered bread crumbs. Sprinkle in diagonal rows over casserole.
Sprinkle remaining cheese between rows. Bake about 30 minutes.

title: cream cheese mints
directions: Mix all ingredients together with mixer.
Knead with hands until smooth (will be very thick).
Remove about 1/4 of dough, wrapping rest in plastic wrap.
Pinch off marble size portions and roll into balls.
Roll in sugar and press flat with fork.
Repeat until gone.

title: cranberry ginger glaze
directions: Combine all ingredients together.

title: raspberry glazed ham
directions: Score ham in diamond pattern, if desired.
Place on a rack in a shallow roasting pan.
Insert meat thermometer.
Bake, uncovered, in 325° oven 1 3/4 hours or until meat thermometer registers 140°. Meanwhile, in a small saucepan, blend wine and lemon juice into cornstarch.
Add about half of the jam.
Cook and stir until thickened and bubbly.
Stir in the remaining jam and butter or margarine.
Heat and stir until butter is melted.
Brush ham with raspberry glaze.
Bake 10 minutes more.
Spoon remaining glaze over ham.
Transfer to heated serving platter.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: lazy brunch dish
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Line an 8 x 10-inch baking dish with crescent rolls; press in and about 1-inch upon sides of dish. Brush the dough with Dijon mustard.
Slice the sausages into very small pieces and distribute over dough.
Sprinkle cheese over sausages.
Lightly beat the eggs, milk, salt, pepper and oregano; pour over cheese.
Bake 30 minutes or until set.
Let stand for 10 minutes before serving.

title: honey pork chops
directions: Place all ingredients except pork chops in blender. Mix thoroughly. Place chops and blender mixture in baking dish. Bake in oven at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Turn chops occasionally.

title: cinnamon breadsticks
directions: Remove crusts from bread and brush both sides of bread slices with oil and milk. Cut each slice into 6 equal strips. Roll strips in mixture of sugar and cinnamon. Toast on cookie sheet in oven at 350° for 10 minutes or until crisp.

title: vanilla wafer cake
directions: Cream sugar and margarine together.
Crush vanilla wafers and add to sugar and margarine mixture.
Add eggs, one at a time. Then add coconut and walnuts.
Beat at high speed until well blended.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Add icing when cool.

title: summer punch
directions: Chill water, pineapple juice and ginger ale separately.
When chilled, mix water and pineapple juice and combine with all three packages of Kool-Aid.
Just before serving, slowly add chilled ginger ale.
Pour into punch bowl.
Add ice ring and serve.

title: hobo dinner
directions: Press ground beef in bottom of 2 1/2-quart casserole dish. Sprinkle with milk, salt and pepper.
Slice potatoes over milk. Slice onions over potatoes.
Cube cheese over onions.
Cover with cream of mushroom soup.
Bake in covered dish at 350° for 1 hour or until potatoes are done.

title: brownies
directions: Combine caramels and 1/3 cup evaporated milk.
Melt in top of double boiler.
Stir until mixture is melted.
Combine cake mix and remaining milk, as well as the softened margarine.
Blend until mixture holds together well.
Stir in nuts.
Press half of cake mix in greased 13 x 9-inch pan and bake for 6 minutes at 350°.
Remove from oven and sprinkle chocolate chips over the top evenly.
Then pour melted caramel mixture evenly over top, adding remaining cake mix.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Mix sugars. shortening, peanut butter and eggs. Stir in the dry ingredients.
Shape dough into 1-inch balls.
Place 2 inches apart on an ungreased cookie sheet.
Pat down each ball.
Bake until set but not hard, about 10 minutes. Cool slightly before removing from cookie sheet.

title: eggplant sauté
directions: With oil in a deep saute pan with medium heat, saute onions and garlic until onions are just translucent. Add bell peppers and stir. Cook for 2 minutes. Add tomatoes and cook 2 more minutes. Add eggplant and continue cooking 2 to 3 more minutes. Add parsley and continue cooking until all vegetables are cooked. Season with salt and pepper to taste. Serves 6.

title: basic pancake recipe
directions: Sift together the flour, baking powder, sugar and salt. Combine egg, milk and shortening.
Add to dry ingredients, stirring just until flour is moistened.
Batter will be lumpy.
Bake on ungreased griddle, get to 400F if electric.
Makes about 20.

title: broccoli cheese casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients in a 2 1/2-quart dish.
Bake, uncovered, 1 hour at 350°.
Stir after first 15 minutes and once again before serving.

title: no peek chicken
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients.
Put mixture in 13 x 9-inch pan, then add rice to soup mixture.
Lay chicken, skin side up, over rice. Sprinkle dry onion soup over chicken.
Cover and bake for 1 hour at 425°.
Do not open oven until the hour is up.

title: icebox pie
directions: Combine sugar and eggs; mix well.
Add pineapple juice.
Let come to a boil.
Then while hot, add lemon Jell-O; let cool.
Whip large can Milnot.
Then add crushed pineapple.
Fold into mixture. Pour into 2 pie pans lined with vanilla wafers.

title: slow cooked meat loaf
directions: In a bowl, beat egg and milk. Stir in the bread cubes, onion, green pepper, salt and pepper. Add the beef and mix well.
Shape into a round loaf. Place in a 5-quart slow cooker. Spread ketchup on top of loaf.

title: seven up jello
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in hot water.
Add 7-Up.
Chill until syrupy. Add pineapple and bananas.
Chill until firm.

title: coconut cream pie
directions: Put sugar, flour and egg yolks in a bowl and mix with a little milk.
In top of a double boiler put 3 cups of milk and margarine. Then add flour mixture.
Stir often.
Cook until thick and then add vanilla and coconut.
Pour in pie shell.
Then fix meringue.

title: hot salsa
directions: Cut jalapenos into slices.
Dice onions.
Empty one can of tomatoes into food processor with approximately 1/3 of jalapenos and onions, 1 teaspoon garlic and cilantro.
Repeat process until all ingredients are used.
Mix in very large bowl; salt and pepper to taste.
Makes approximately 3 to 4 quarts.
You may vary how hot it is by increasing or decreasing the number of cans of tomatoes you use.

title: coconut cream pie
directions: Add sugar and salt to flour and stir.
Add milk gradually, stirring until smooth.
Cook over heat until mixture thickens, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Add small amount of cooked mixture to egg yolks, then stir eggs into cooked mixture. Return to heat; bring to boil.
Remove from heat.
Stir in vanilla, margarine and 3/4 cup coconut.

title: chipped beef in scrambled eggs
directions: Pour hot water over beef and simmer 15 minutes.
Drain.
Mix milk and eggs; stir into beef.
Put butter or margarine in frying pan and scramble all together.
Serve over toast.

title: peanut butter fudge cake
directions: Bake cake in 13 x 9-inch pan.
In saucepan heat butter, buttermilk, water, cocoa and vanilla.
Cook over medium heat. Stir occasionally until mixture comes to a boil.
In another bowl mix sugar, flour, soda and eggs.
Pour hot mixture over dry ingredients.
Mix well, pour into pan and bake on 350° for 25 minutes.

title: city chicken
directions: Put beef, veal and pork alternately on skewers.
Dip them in the milk and egg mixture.
Then dip into the Italian bread crumbs that have been mixed with the remaining ingredients, except the soup.

title: banana freeze
directions: Thaw bananas slightly at room temperature, 5 to 10 minutes; cut into pieces.
Place milk, milk powder, brown sugar and vanilla extract in blender.
With blender on low speed, add frozen banana pieces, processing until fruit begins to blend into mixture.
Increase speed to high and process until smooth.
Makes 3 cups.
One cup serving equals 165 calories; 2 grams fat, 1 mg. cholesterol and 1/2 serving of fruit.

title: mushrooms a la creole
directions: In a large pan, put peeled and stemmed mushrooms.
Pour over them the oil.
Cover with the bread crumbs and seasonings.
Set in a hot oven (375°) and bake for approximately 20 minutes.

title: potato casserole
directions: Layer hash browns in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Combine 1 stick butter, cheese, sour cream, onions and soup.
Stir and pour over hash browns.
Sprinkle with corn flakes; drizzle with remaining stick of butter on top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: french fried onion rings
directions: Combine flour, salt, milk, oil and egg.
Beat until smooth. Cut onions into 1/4-inch slices; separate into rings.
Dip each ring in the batter.
Drop a few at a time in the oil, heated at 375°.
Cook 2 to 3 minutes.
Drain on absorbent paper.
Sprinkle with salt, if desired.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli as directed on the bag; drain, saving 1/2 cup of broth.
In a medium size casserole dish, combine rice, mushroom soup, Cheddar cheese soup, broccoli and broth; stir until well blended.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes, or until rice is well cooked.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: In pan bring sugar and milk to a boil. Boil for 3 minutes. Add peanut butter and marshmallow cream.
Mix well.
Quickly pour into a buttered 8 inch square pan.
Chill until set.

title: speedy chicken pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Boil fryer and remove meat from bones. Combine broth, chicken, eggs, soup and pepper. Mix flour and milk. Dot bottom of 3-quart baking dish with margarine. Pour in batter. Spoon chicken over batter. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: lemon sour cream pie
directions: Combine 1 cup sugar with cornstarch and salt, stirring thoroughly.
Slowly stir in milk, then cook and stir over medium heat until mixture is boiling and thickened.
Remove pan from heat. Blend a small amount of hot mixture into the slightly beaten egg yolks.
Return egg yolk mixture to hot mixture in pan.
Cook and stir 2 minutes over medium heat.
Add butter, lemon peel and lemon juice.
Cover and cool.
Fold in sour cream.
Spoon mixture into baked pie shell.
Beat egg whites with cream of tartar and vanilla until soft peaks form.
Gradually add remaining 6 tablespoons sugar, beating until stiff peaks form.
Top pie with meringue, seal edges well.
Bake in preheated oven at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes or until meringue is golden brown.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: chocolate icing
directions: Bring margarine to a boil.
Boil for 3 minutes.
Add chips and vanilla.
Remove from heat and stir until chocolate has melted. Pour over warm cake.

title: buffalo wings
directions: Put first 5 ingredients in a sauce pan and simmer on low until it is all melted/mixed well. Keep warm while doing the chicken.

title: sugar wafer cookies
directions: Cream together the first 4 ingredients, add eggs and vanilla. Add all dry ingredients.
Refrigerate at least 1 hr.
To bake, pinch off about 1 t of dough, roll into a ball and place on a greased cookie sheet.
Press each cookie into a circle with the bottom of a glass or cookie press dipped into sugar.
Bake at 375 F for 10-12 minutes.
Do not let them get too brown.
Cool completely.
Keep in airtight container.
These will keep for up to four weeks and they get better with age.

title: funnel cakes
directions: Make thin enough to pour through funnel.
Fry in skillet 1/2 to 3/4 full of shortening.
Sprinkle with 10x sugar.

title: peanut brittle
directions: In large skillet mix first 3 ingredients, bring to a boil. Boil until syrup forms a hard ball when dropped in a cup of cold water.
Peanuts will turn golden brown. Add vanilla, soda and water.
Pour into a greased cookie sheet to cool.

title: mushroom beef burger
directions: Crush Rice Krispies slightly.
In large mixing bowl, beat egg until foamy.
Add crushed cereal, salt, pepper, Worcestershire sauce, onion and mushrooms, including broth.
Beat well; add ground beef.
Mix only until combined.
Shape into patties.
Place on foil-lined pan.
Bake at 375° for about 25 minutes.

title: matzah balls
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly and let stand in refrigerator several
hours (overnight is best).
Moisten hands and form into balls.
Drop into boiling water for 1 hour (no less, but more is okay).

title: brownie cake
directions: Combine margarine, water and cocoa.
Bring to a boil and set aside.
Combine remaining ingredients.
Stir for 2 minutes. Slowly add cocoa mixture into flour mixture.
When all ingredients have been thoroughly mixed, pour into floured pan.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: pat's chicken casserole
directions: Mix and put in buttered 9 x 13-inch casserole.
Cover with crumbled Doritos; top with 1/2 pound grated cheese.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: spiced mixed nuts
directions: Combine egg white and water.
Add nuts then toss to coat. Combine sugar, spice and salt, then toss the nuts until well coated with this mixture.
Place in single layer on greased baking sheet.
Bake in 300° oven 20 to 25 minutes.
Cool on waxed paper then break into large clusters.
Place in decorated tin, bag or basket.
Yields about 4 1/2 cups of candy.

title: my favorite banana bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease two 8 x 4-inch pans.
In a large bowl, with electric mixer at medium speed, cream margarine, sugar, eggs and orange peel until light and fluffy.
Beat in mashed bananas.

title: popovers
directions: Heat oven to 450°.
Put 1/2 teaspoon butter in each slot of muffin pan.
Heat in oven for 5 minutes.
Combine remaining butter, flour, eggs and salt and blend in blender or on medium speed of mixer.
Divide dough into 9 portions of the muffin pan.
Bake for 15 minutes at 450° and reduce temperature of oven to 350°.
Bake until browned, about 20 minutes.
Serve immediately.

title: veal cutlets
directions: Pound veal steak thin or partially freeze veal roast and slice thin.
Beat eggs; add Romano cheese, salt and black pepper.
Add veal slices to egg mixture and let set for 1 hour.

title: canned vinegar beans
directions: Mix vinegar, beans, water and salt together in a large cook pot. Bring to a boil, add beans and cook 15 minutes. Pack into hot sterilized jars and seal.

title: peanut butter fingers
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream together butter, sugar and brown sugar.
Blend in egg, peanut butter (1/3 cup), baking soda, salt and vanilla.
Stir in flour and quick-cooking rolled oats.
Spread in a greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes. Sprinkle with semi-sweet chocolate morsels.
Let sit 5 minutes. Combine powdered sugar, 1/4 cup peanut butter and evaporated milk. Mix well.
Spread chocolate evenly.
Drizzle with peanut butter mixture.
Cool and cut.

title: sweet and sour pork
directions: Chop vegetables into small chunks.
Put carrots on to boil for about 20 minutes.
Put meat in a small bowl with soy sauce (enough to cover) and add ginger and sake; set aside.

title: broccoli cheese sauce
directions: Combine soup and milk in saucepan on medium heat.
Stir until hot.
Serve over vegetables like broccoli, cauliflower and carrots.

title: cube steaks with butter sauce
directions: In skillet, cook steaks over medium heat until browned on both sides.
Season with garlic salt.
Remove steaks from skillet and keep warm and drain off fat.
Melt butter in same skillet.
Stir in remaining ingredients and heat.
Place steaks on dinner plate and pour mixture over each and enjoy.

title: easy maple frosting
directions: Heat the first 2 ingredients to a boil.
Pour over the butter, vanilla and salt. Beat all together thoroughly. Add the powdered sugar, a little at a time.
If it seems too thick, add a few drops of milk.

title: hello dolly cookies
directions: Mix butter, sugar and graham cracker crumbs.
Press into bottom of pan.
Layer coconut, butterscotch chips and chocolate chips.
Pour Eagle Brand milk over.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: cantaloupe pie
directions: Cover diced cantaloupe with water; cook until tender.
Drain excess juice off and measure 3 cups.
Pour into large saucepan. Add milk and other ingredients (except vanilla and oleo).
Cook until thick.
Add vanilla and oleo.
Pour into baked pie shells. Top with meringue (made with egg whites) and brown in moderate oven.

title: shredded beef b~b~q sandwiches
directions: Remove fat from roast.
Put all ingredients in large roaster pan.
Bake for 6 hours on 300 degree
Shred with fork.
Serve on Buns.

title: pickled mushrooms
directions: Wash mushrooms in cold, salted water.
Drain and place in saucepan.
Combine remaining ingredients and pour over mushrooms. Bring to boil and simmer for 10 minutes.
Cool, cover and refrigerate.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Mix ingredients.
Bake at 450° until golden brown.

title: hot crab dip
directions: Combine ingredients.
Cook, stirring, until blended and hot. Serve in hot chafing dish with crackers.
Makes 2 1/2 cups.

title: easy refrigerator rolls
directions: In mixing bowl, dissolve yeast in warm water.
Add sugar, shortening, egg and half of the flour.
Beat thoroughly 2 minutes. Add enough remaining flour to handle easily.
Knead 5 minutes. Place in a greased bowl and grease top of dough; cover with foil. Place in refrigerator.
Punch down occasionally as dough rises (double) about 1 hour before shaping.
Set out of refrigerator. Shape into desired rolls or coffee cake.
Cover and let rise until double in size (about 1 to 1 1/2 hours).
Bake at 400° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix first 7 ingredients.
Add oats, flour, baking soda and salt.
Mix and drop by teaspoon on greased cookie sheet.

title: pineapple delight cake
directions: Bake cake as directed.
Cool.
Mix dry pudding and cream cheese.
Add milk and pour over cake.
Put pineapple over pudding, then Cool Whip and nuts.

title: sausage, green beans and potatoes
directions: Use crock-pot; drain potatoes and wash off.
Put in crock-pot. Dump can of green beans in.
Cut sausage in large pieces.
Cook on low about 6 to 8 hours.

title: quick cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into baking dish.
Bake at 350° until cake springs when touched.
Makes good strawberry short cake or use with chocolate sauce.

title: iranian sweet chicken
directions: Heat sugar in heavy skillet with almonds.
Stir until sugar melts and begins to turn brown (careful not to burn).
Turn out on waxed paper to cool, then break apart.
Add chicken pieces to melted oleo in skillet with marmalade.
Mix in rice. Pour into greased casserole, top with almonds.
Bake 20 to 30 minutes in 350° oven.
(If too dry, add small amount of chicken broth.)

title: stewed wild duck casserole
directions: Rub ducks with salt and pepper.
Place onions and butter in a pot.
Cook until dark brown.
Add ducks, ham, garlic, parsley, thyme and bay leaf.
Cook for 3 minutes.
Add Claret; cook 10 minutes, cooking instantly; add water.
Cook slowly for 1 hour until tender.
Serves 8.

title: "cat's" pound cake
directions: Cream Crisco and sugar.
Add eggs and cream together. Add milk and flavoring, then add flour and milk alternately.
Pour into greased tube pan. Turn oven to 200°. Put cake into oven for 30 minutes, then turn oven to 275° and bake for 1 1/2 hours.

title: pineapple cheese bake
directions: Mix sugar and flour.
Add pineapple juice and lemon juice, then pineapple and cheese.
Melt butter and mix well with crushed crackers.
Pour pineapple cheese mixture into 2-quart casserole dish.
Top with buttered Ritz crackers.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: apple crunch pie
directions: Mix sugar, flour and margarine together.
Crumble until it is fine.
Put apples in bottom of dish.
If they are not sweetened, sprinkle some sugar over them.
Cover the apples with the crumb mixture mixed earlier.
Bake in a 350° oven for 40 minutes, or until done.
Top should brown and be crunchy.

title: candy strawberries
directions: Combine jello, pecans and coconut.
Stir in milk and vanilla; mix well.
Chill 1 hour.

title: baked chicken and rice
directions: Place chicken pieces in a greased baking dish.
Add chopped onion and dry rice.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Add a pinch of thyme and tarragon leaves.

title: green beans with cashews *
directions: Blanch the green beans in boiling salted water.
While beans are cooking, heat the oil, salt and pepper and parsley.
Stir to mix.
Drain beans and place in warm bowl.
Sprinkle nuts on top and then pour oil mixture over the beans.
Toss well.
Serve immediately or at room temperature.
Serves 6.

title: cherry cheese pie
directions: In large mixer bowl, beat cheese until fluffy.
Beat in Eagle Brand until smooth.
Stir in ReaLemon and vanilla.
Pour into crust.
Chill 3 hours or until set.
Top with desired amount of pie filling before serving.

title: strawberry punch
directions: Mix and serve in gallon pitcher.

title: hershey's chocolate cake
directions: Generously grease and flour 2 (9-inch) round cake pans. Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream butter, shortening, sugar and vanilla until light and fluffy; blend eggs.
Combine baking soda, cocoa, flour, baking powder and salt in bowl; add alternately with milk to batter.
Blend well.
Pour into prepared pans; bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until cake tester inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool 10 minutes; remove from pans.
After completely cooled, ice with your favorite frosting.
(This can be a vanilla cake by omitting the cocoa.)

title: swiss tuna bunny
directions: Mix thoroughly and spread in 8 hamburger rolls.
Wrap individually in aluminum foil and heat 20 minutes in preheated 350° oven.

title: country sausage casserole
directions: Cut sausage into 1/2-inch pieces.
Cook and stir sausage and onion in oil until onion is tender (about 5 minutes).
Stir in potato mix, water and pepper.
Heat to boiling.
Reduce heat and cook 10 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Stir in can of broccoli cream soup and carrots; simmer until tender.
Stir in broccoli and shredded Cheddar cheese.
Cook for 10 minutes or less.
Makes 4 to 5 servings.
May be frozen and reheated.

title: brownie pie
directions: Grease pie plate with butter.
Mix nuts, sugar, flour, eggs and vanilla.
Melt cocoa and butter; add to flour mixture.
Bake at 325° for 25 minutes.
Serve with ice cream.

title: vegetable lasagna
directions: Cook vegetables and garlic in oil until tender.
Stir in pasta sauce and oregano; simmer 15 minutes.
Combine cottage cheese and Parmesan.
In 13 x 9-inch baking dish, layer 1/2 each of the noodles, sauce, cottage cheese and Mozzarella.
Repeat layering; top with chopped parsley.
Cover; bake at 350° for 45 minutes. Uncover; bake 15 minutes.
Let stand 20 minutes.
Refrigerate leftovers.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.
tags: container Borden Light-Line nonfat cottage cheese

title: copper pennies
directions: Cut onions and peppers in thin slices; mix with cooked sliced carrots.
Mix all other ingredients and add to carrots.
Let stand overnight (marinate).
Serve chilled.

title: beer bread
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly in a large bowl.
Pour in greased bread loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour. Brush melted butter on top when loaf is done.

title: ricky's cheese ball
directions: Mix cream cheese, cheese and margarine together with hands. Add soy sauce and milk.
Put in refrigerator and chill.
Mold into a ball and roll in chopped nuts or chopped parsley to garnish.

title: turtle cake
directions: Mix cake mix according to directions.
Pour 1/2 into 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Melt caramels with milk.
Pour over cake.
Sprinkle chocolate chips and nuts over caramel.
Pour other half of cake mix on and bake another 20 minutes.

title: mack's kentucky cobbler
directions: Melt stick of butter in round Pyrex dish.
Mix all ingredients, except fruit, together in another bowl.
Pour batter over melted butter.
Spoon fruit in center of batter.
Do not mix. Bake 40 minutes at 325°.

title: fish delight
directions: Heat tomatoes in large pot.
Add onion, bell pepper and garlic.
Cook 10 minutes.
Add fish and water.
Cook 10 minutes. Add rice, salt and pepper.
Cook additional 15 minutes or until rice is done.
Swirl in butter.
Sprinkle with parsley.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Boil sugar, syrup and water until it forms a heavy syrup.
Do not stir.
Add nuts and cook until a light brown color.
Add soda. Stir quickly real well.
Pour into greased shallow pan.

title: eggnog cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
In a medium bowl, combine flour, baking powder, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Mix well with a wire whisk and set aside.
In a large bowl, cream sugar and butter with an electric mixer to form a grainy paste.
Add eggnog, vanilla and egg yolks and beat at medium speed until smooth.
Add the flour mixture and beat at low speed just until combined.
Do not overmix.
Drop by rounded teaspoonful onto ungreased baking sheets 1 inch apart. Sprinkle lightly with nutmeg.
Bake for 23 to 25 minutes or until bottoms turn light brown.
Transfer to cool, flat surface immediately with spatula.
Yields 3 dozen.

title: kraut salad
directions: Wash and drain kraut.
Cut up celery, pepper and onion; add pimiento.
Mix together vinegar, sugar and oil; pour over vegetables.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: out of this world cake
directions: Combine all ingredients except pineapple and beat with mixer until well blended.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan and bake for 45 minutes in a 350° oven.
Remove from oven.
While cake is still hot, pour pineapple over it and allow to soak thoroughly.
Let cake cool completely before frosting.

title: fried pickles
directions: Drain pickles, then spread on paper towels to soak up excess moisture. Combine buttermilk and hot sauce. In a separate bowl combine flour and cornmeal. Dip pickles in buttermilk mixture, then dredge in flour mixture, evenly coating. Drop into hot oil in batches, turning until all sides are golden brown and crisp. Drain on paper towels and season with salt. Best served hot.

title: million dollar salad
directions: Layer in order in a 9 x 12-inch pan. (Glass is pretty for the layers of salad.)
This salad keeps very well in the refrigerator hours before serving time.

title: easy no bake beans
directions: Soak navy beans overnight; drain and put in pressure cooker. Add sugar, ketchup, Worcestershire sauce, onion and salt pork. Cover with water. Cook 40 minutes at 15 pounds pressure.

title: broccoli and onions cheese sauce
directions: In a 1 1/2-quart casserole, combine broccoli, onion and water. Microcook, covered, on High for 4 to 7 minutes or until broccoli is tender, stirring every 3 minutes.
Drain broccoli and onion mixture well.

title: tutti-frutti cake
directions: Cream oleo, sugar and egg.
Mix vanilla and soda in milk. Sift cocoa with flour and add alternately with milk.
Add nuts and dates.
Bake in two layers in 350° oven.
Check in 20 minutes. When cooled, put together with filling.

title: carrot souffle
directions: Put all ingredients in blender. Blend until smooth. Pour into buttered casserole dish. Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: pumpkin cake
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients; set aside.
Mix sugar, oil, eggs and pumpkin.
Mix with dry ingredients.
Bake at 350° about 20 to 30 minutes.

title: sauerkraut
directions: Drain sauerkraut.
Cut peppers into small to medium pieces. Slice onions thinly.
Add tomato sauce, plus 1 can of water. Slice sausage into pieces.
Add all together.
Simmer for 2 to 2 1/2 hours.

title: corned beef casserole
directions: Precook macaroni
until
almost tender; drain.
Mix all ingredients together and
bake
in
a
9 x 13-inch Pyrex dish. Cover with buttered crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes until bubbly.

title: chocolate sauce
directions: In small saucepan, mix sugar, cocoa powder and cornstarch. Add milk.
Cook and stir until thickened and bubbly.
Cook and stir 2 minutes more.
Remove from heat.
Stir in vanilla.
Serve warm or cool.
Refrigerate any remaining sauce.
Makes 8 (2 tablespoon) servings.
Serve over angel cake, ice cream or frozen yogurt.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Form cookie dough in pizza pan and bake at 350° until golden brown.
Cool.
Cream the cream cheese; add rest of ingredients. Spread on crust.
Slice any fruit (fresh) and arrange (examples: peaches, kiwi, strawberries and blueberries).

title: glazed or candied sweet potatoes
directions: Boil the potatoes without paring them, and when tender drain and strip off skins.
Make a syrup by boiling together the sugar and water.
Cut each potato in half or in thick slices, dip each piece into the syrup and lay it in a greased baking-dish.
Season with salt and pepper and bits of butter.
When all the potatoes are in the dish, pour over it any syrup that remains and bake in oven 400° until the potatoes are brown.
They will brown quickly.

title: baked beans
directions: Cut up green peppers and onions in small pieces.
Cook until tender on top of stove.
Add pork and beans, ketchup, mustard and brown sugar or syrup.
Mix well and let set for a few minutes, then serve.

title: twinkie strawberry (banana) cake
directions: Slice Twinkies down the center and line a 9 x 13-inch pan (cream side up).
Mix Jell-O with 2 cups hot water.
Stir until dissolved, then pour in 1 cup of cold water.
Mix Jell-O with strawberries and pour this over Twinkies.
Refrigerate 30 minutes. Mix pudding as per directions.
Spread over Twinkies and strawberry mixture.
Top with Cool Whip.

title: unstuffed cabbage
directions: Combine meat, onion, green pepper, salt and pepper.
Do not cook.
Layer in 10 x 13-inch pan:
cabbage, meat mixture and repeat until all ingredients used.
Cover with tomato soup and chopped tomatoes.
Bake, covered, for 2 hours at 325°.

title: toasted potato salad
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Place potatoes on 15 x 10 x 1-inch baking pan sprayed with no-stick cooking spray.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes or until potatoes are tender and golden brown, stirring once.
Mix dressing, bacon, eggs, onions, salt and pepper in large bowl; add potatoes.
Mix lightly.
Serve warm or chilled.

title: corn relish
directions: Mix all ingredients except flour and 1 quart of vinegar.
Cook to a slow boil for 45 minutes.
Then add flour and remaining vinegar.
Cook 5 minutes.
Can while hot.
Makes 12 pints.

title: date nut bread
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Beat in eggs and vanilla.
Add walnuts.
Combine dates, soda and boiling water.
Cool.
Add to butter mixture.
Stir in flour.
Pour into 8 greased beer cans. Yields 8 servings.
These make nice gifts.

title: monkey bread
directions: Use what is left in the bowl and add oil, milk, eggs and vanilla.
Mix thoroughly.
In a separate bowl, mix flour, sugar, baking powder, salt, cinnamon, baking soda, pudding mix and nuts. Add to mixture and mix thoroughly.
Pour into 2 large loaf pans or one Bundt pan, well-greased and sugared (mixture of sugar and cinnamon).
Sprinkle some cinnamon sugar on top also.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour or more, depending on your oven.
Enjoy.

title: meatballs
directions: Mix all ingredients (except wieners) together.
Make into 1-inch balls.
In a heavy skillet, pour about 1/2-inch oil for frying.
Cook meatballs until they start to brown. Take up.

title: pizza meat loaf
directions: Mix first six ingredients.
Put 1/2 of mixture in loaf pan. Top with 1/2 Mozzarella cheese and remaining mixture.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Top with remaining cheese and bake for 5 minutes.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients together and form a ball and roll in chopped pecans.

title: spinach casserole
directions: For a thick crust, spread rolls in casserole dish (I prefer a thin crust).
Blend spinach, eggs and 1/2 of cheese and sausage. Spread over crust; add the other half of cheese to top.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: italian meatballs
directions: Combine all ingredients and shape into 1 1/2-inch meatballs (about 20).
Arrange in 11 x 7-inch dish.
Cook on High for 7 1/2 to 8 1/2 minutes.
Rearrange halfway through cooking.
Drain.
Let stand 3 minutes before serving.

title: pecan pie toffee bars
directions: Combine flour, sugar and butter in a mixing bowl.
Mix with beater or use pastry cutter to mix until resembles coarse meal. Press firmly in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes, until lightly golden and edges begin to darken.

title: dump cake
directions: Place pineapple on bottom of 9 x 13 pan. Spoon on cherry filling. Sprinkle dry cake mix on top. Slice cold butter on top. DO NOT MIX THIS TOGETHER. You may want to add chopped nuts to the top (optional). Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: pumpkin spice pound cake
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Grease and flour 10-inch tube pan.
Combine oil and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well.
Set aside. In another bowl, combine all dry ingredients; set aside.
In another bowl, combine pumpkin, water, vanilla, butter flavoring and orange extract.
Alternately mix 3 parts flour mixture into 2 parts pumpkin mixture.
Mix at low speed until blended.
Pour into pans. Bake for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Cool in pans for 10 minutes.

title: potato deutscher
directions: Grate raw potatoes on a coarse grater.
Soak bread cubes in milk and beaten eggs.
Add potatoes and seasoning.
Put in buttered baking dish.
Pour sour cream over top, which makes it taste like cheese.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or longer.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Mix rice, soup and milk.
Place in roaster.
Lay chicken in single layer on rice and sprinkle with onion soup mix.
Bake at 375° for 2 hours.
Don't peek!

title: cheese danish
directions: Place the first 5 ingredients in mixer and blend thoroughly. Spread 1 package crescent rolls in a 9 x 13-inch pan or long glass baking dish, pushing up sides.
Spread cheese mixture over rolls, leaving a small edge of bread showing.
Spread another package crescent rolls over cheese mixture. Mix the water and egg white and beat with fork.
Brush top bread with egg white/water mixture. Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: olive cheese balls
directions: Mix the first 5 ingredients into dough. Make into small balls. Press drained olives into each ball, leaving pimento end of olive uncovered.
Bake at 400° for 12 minutes.

title: coconut bonbons
directions: Cream together until all mixed.
Roll into small balls and dip in chocolate.

title: fruit fritters(serves 6)
directions: *Apples (firm), peeled, cored and cut into 1/4-inch slices; 1/2-inch slices of bananas; ripe, firm apricots or peaches, peeled and pitted or pineapple (remove rind) may be used.

title: twenty-four hour salad
directions: Put eggs in double boiler and add vinegar and sugar, stirring constantly, until thick and smooth. Add butter and cool. When cool, fold in whipped cream and fruit mixture.
Put in to cool for 24 hours.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Wash cranberries and put in freezer for about 20 minutes.
Run through food chopper or grinder.
Add sugar to cranberries and set aside.
Dissolve gelatin in 4 cups hot water.
Add pineapple and juice, lemon juice, pulp, celery, apples, nuts and ground cranberries.
Pour into 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan or mold.
Lightly brush salad oil on mold for easy removal.

title: microwave mints
directions: In
a 2-quart glass measure, combine sugar, corn syrup, milk and cream of tartar.
Cook on High (Maximum
power) for 5 to
6 minutes or until a few drops of mixture
in
cold
water forms
a soft ball (238° on candy thermometer).
Let
stand
3 minutes
to cool
slightly.
Beat with mixer
until
creamy. Flavor with 8 to 10 drops of peppermint extract and color with food
coloring. Drop mixture by teaspoonful onto
foil.
When cool, store in airtight container.

title: chocolate mousse pie
directions: Heat chocolate and 2 tablespoons of milk in saucepan, stirring until melted.
Beat sugar into cream cheese, add remaining milk and chocolate mixture, beat until smooth.
Fold chocolate mixture into whipped topping, saving a small amount of whipped topping to "ice" pie (if desired).
Blend until smooth.
Spoon into crust. Freeze until firm, about 4 hours.
Use any remaining whipped topping to spread on top.
Shaved chocolate can be used to garnish.
Store any leftover pie in refrigerator.

title: squash casserole
directions: In casserole place layer of cooked squash; add 1/2 cup grated Cheddar cheese; pour over milk mixture.
Top with crumbled crackers.
Repeat layers.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: triple chocolate cake
directions: Combine cake mix, pudding mix, eggs and chips in large bowl. Mix until well blended (2 minutes).
Pour into 10-inch Bundt pan. Bake at 350° for 50 or 55 minutes.
Cool 15 minutes in pan.
Put on rack to cool.

title: fresh vegetable dip
directions: Mix together and chill.

title: caramel corn(microwave)
directions: Combine sugar, corn syrup and oleo in 4-cup glass microwave container.
Place in microwave and bring to full boil (full power 2 to 4 minutes).
Stir in soda and salt.
Spray grocery bag with Pam and put in 3 quarts popped corn.
Pour syrup mixture over corn in bag.
Place in microwave for 1 1/2 minutes on High power.
Shake bag another 1 1/2 minutes on High power.
Shake bag another 1/2 minute on High power.
Shake bag another 1/2 minute on High power. Shake bag.
Spread on cookie sheet to cool.

title: potluck kraut dish
directions: Mix all ingredients and place in 2 1/2-quart buttered casserole.
Cover and bake 2 hours or until rice is done.
Bake at 350°.

title: angel buns
directions: Place first 3 items in a medium bowl.
Mix in Bisquick and milk until dough forms.
Gently smooth into a ball, on baking mix, knead 10 times.
Roll 1/2 inch thick.
Cut with a 2-inch biscuit cutter.
Let rise in a warm place for 30 minutes.
Bake at 425° or 450° for 6 to 8 minutes.

title: 5 hour beef stew
directions: Place all the ingredients in Dutch oven.
Cover and bake at 275° for 4 hours.
Remove cover and bake 1 more hour.

title: pickle wheels
directions: Wipe excess
moisture
from
pickles.
Spread with softened cream cheese.
Roll
in corned beef that has been broken up fine. Wrap
each	in
foil
and refrigerate overnight.
To serve, cut in 1/4 inch slices and keep cool until serving.

title: "crock-pot pizza"
directions: Cook ground beef, onion and bell pepper.
Cook noodles. Mix ground beef, onion, bell pepper and two sauces.
Layer in crock-pot noodles, meat mixture, Cheddar cheese, Mozzarella cheese, mushrooms and pepperoni.
Cook on low until cheese melts (about 2 hours).

title: green bean casserole
directions: Drain water from green beans and fry beans in margarine for about 15 minutes.
Pour the beans and margarine into a 9 x 9-inch dish (or equivalent).
Mix with cream of chicken and boned chicken.
Grate cheese over top.
(The amount you use depends on how much you like cheese; I use at least a cup of grated cheese.) Put the onions on top.
Cook at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: zucchini hors d'oeuvres
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake in a 9 x 13-inch greased baking dish at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until top is browned. Cut into squares when cool.

title: strawberry shortcake
directions: Bake cake as directed in 2 (9-inch) cake pans.
When done let cool on plate.
Take fork, poking holes in first layer.
Add 1 1/4 boxes of strawberries.
Carefully spoon on enough Cool Whip to cover cake.
Add second layer on top; repeat strawberries and Cool Whip to completely cover cake.
Take remaining 1/2 box strawberries and dribble over sides and top of cake.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: melon salad with orange-honey dressing
directions: Peel melons; discard seeds and membranes.
Cut each melon lengthwise into 8 slices.
Divide melon and grapes evenly among 4 lettuce-lined salad plates.

title: cornbread dressing
directions: Mix cornbread crumbs, dressing mix, onion, celery and sage. Add enough broth to make mixture very moist (make thin mixture). Spread in 9 x 13 baking dish. Pour melted butter over dressing. Bake at 325° for 1 hour. Serves about 15 people.

title: yummy peanut butter pie
directions: Mix together peanut butter and 10x sugar until slightly crumbly; set aside.
Combine flour, sugar and salt and mix well with beaten egg yolks and milk.
Cook, stirring constantly, until it thickens.
Remove from heat; add margarine and vanilla.
Place 2/3 of the peanut butter and 10x sugar mixture in the pie shell. Pour cooked filling on top of this.
Cover with a layer of Cool Whip and sprinkle remainder of peanut butter-sugar mixture on top.

title: barbecued wieners
directions: Split the wieners in half and place in casserole dish.
Pour ketchup and mustard over top.
Place in oven and cook until hot and begins to brown.

title: caramel popcorn
directions: Place popped popcorn in a large shallow roasting pan, popped kernels only.
In a large heavy 1 1/2-quart saucepan, stir sugar, margarine and corn syrup together.
Bring to a boil, stirring constantly over medium heat.
Boil for 5 minutes without stirring. Remove from heat; stir in vanilla and baking soda.
Pour over popcorn, stirring to coat well.
Bake at 250° for 10 minutes, stirring after 5 minutes.
Do not overbake.
Remove from oven, spoon popcorn onto a large piece of wax paper or aluminum foil. Break apart popcorn as it cools.

title: cherry pizza
directions: Crumb together cake mix, graham cracker crumbs, margarine and egg.
Press mixture into pizza pan.
Crimp on edge.
Bake 13 to 18 minutes in 300° oven.
Cool.
Top with softened cream cheese beaten until fluffy.
Top cream cheese with cherry pie filling. Sprinkle pecan chips on top of cherry pie filling.
Chill.
Cut into pizza wedges.
Serve.
Keep remaining pizza in refrigerator.

title: hot packed apples
directions: Wash, pare, half and core apples.
Drop in vinegar and salt water.
Boil equal parts of sugar and water together.
Rinse apples that have been soaking.
Add to hot syrup.
Cook 5 minutes. Pack in jars, overlapping layers.
Place jars in hot water bath for 15 minutes.

title: walnut parfait
directions: Mix orange juice, lemon juice and sugar and put in bottom of double ice tray or two single ice trays.
Put in freezer and leave long enough to thicken.
Mix whipped cream, powdered sugar, vanilla and walnuts and spread on top of first layer.
Freeze 6 hours.

title: stuffed peppers
directions: Clean peppers and place in boiling water for 3 minutes; drain. Brown ground beef and saute onion and garlic in oil.
Drain off fat.
Mix meat, onion, garlic, spices and beaten eggs to rice. Add half of the chili sauce to this mixture.
Stiff peppers and spoon chili sauce over peppers and sprinkle each pepper with bread crumbs and Parmesan cheese.
You can pour tomato sauce, tomato soup or tomatoes (of your choice) around peppers and bake in preheated 350° oven for about 50 or 60 minutes or until done.

title: copper pennies
directions: Bring to a boil all the ingredients except the carrots, onions and peppers.
Cool and pour over carrots.
Add onions and peppers. Seal in tight container.
Let stand overnight in refrigerator. Serve chilled.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Mix butter and cornflakes; put 2/3 in bottom of casserole dish.

title: spice tea
directions: Mix and stir in an airtight container.
Add 2 tablespoons of mixture with a cup of hot water.

title: strawberry heaven
directions: Cut cake horizontally into 3 layers.
Place 1 cake layer on serving plate.
Stir crushed strawberries and milk into 1 1/2 c. of the whipped topping in large bowl.
Spread 1/2 of strawberry mixture on cake layer.
Arrange 1/2 of the sliced strawberries on top of strawberry mixture.
Repeat layers ending with cake.
Frost top and sides of cake with whipped topping.
Refrigerate at least 1 hour or until ready to serve.
Decorate top and sides with strawberry fans, mint leaves.
Serves 12.

title: red rice with pigeon peas
directions: In a large pan, pour 1/4 cup of oil.
Add 2 cups of pork and brown.
Add green pepper and onion.
Saute.
Add pigeon peas; mix well.
Cook 10 minutes.
Add rest of ingredients, garlic, black pepper, salt, oregano, cumin, rest of oil and rice (that has been rinsed twice).
Mix well.
Add 2 cups of water; cook on medium-high heat until water is boiled out.
Stir and mix well. Lower heat, cover and cook on low heat until rice is tender.

title: garlic bread
directions: Cut bread in half horizontally.
Combine butter and remaining ingredients; spread on cut sides of bread.
Broil 4 inches from heat 4 or 5 minutes.

title: poppy seed loaf
directions: Combine eggs, oil and sugar; beat until well blended.
Sift all dry ingredients together.
Add flour mixture and milk alternately to oil mixture.
Add flavorings and poppy seed.
Pour into 2 greased loaf pans.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Top of loaves will crack.
Remove from pans; top with frosting.

title: tea cakes
directions: After placing in pans to bake, sprinkle each cake with cinnamon and sugar, mixed.
If lard is used, add salt to it before mixing.

title: mary clendenin's jalapeno cornbread
directions: Mix
first
4 ingredients together.
Blend in remaining ingredients.
Pour	batter into greased pan.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.

title: easy broccoli casserole
directions: Note:
This recipe may be halved or quartered (each item) depending on size of your family.

title: artichoke dip
directions: Cream mayonnaise and cream cheese together.
Add Parmesan cheese and mix well.
Drain and chop artichokes.
Add to mixture.

title: creamed sherry spinach
directions: Cook spinach according to package directions, drain well.
Melt butter, stir in flour, add soup and wine.
Cook, stirring, until mixture boils and thickens.
Add cheese; stir over low heat until melted.
Remove from heat.
Add spinach and other ingredients. Turn into well-greased casserole or custard cups.
Set in shallow pan of hot water.
Bake in 350° oven about 45 minutes or until firm.
Remove from oven; let stand 5 minutes or so before serving. Serves 6 to 8.

title: marinade for steak and chicken
directions: Score steak diagonally across grain.
Place meat in a shallow dish.
Pour marinade over.
Cover and refrigerate 8 hours, turning occasionally.

title: steaks stroganoff
directions: In large skillet, cook and stir thinly sliced onion in 1 tablespoon margarine until tender.
Remove onion and set aside. In same skillet add 1/4 cup shortening.
Add floured steak and cook over medium heat until brown and crispy.
Remove steaks and place on warm platter.
Pour fat from skillet.
Stir together onion, 1/2 cup sour cream and salt and pepper in skillet.
Heat until fully warmed.
Pour over steaks and serve.

title: pesto
directions: Remove leaves from basil and wash and dry thoroughly.
Place leaves in a mortar together with garlic, pine nuts and pinch of salt.
With the pestle, pound and grind into a paste against the side.
Add cheese and continue grinding into a smooth paste.
Stir in olive oil, a little at a time.
Sauce should have consistency of creamed butter.
Makes sauce for 6 servings of pasta.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Melt margarine in heavy pan.
Add cream and sugar.
Cook 9 minutes after it starts to boil. Remove from heat and add marshmallow cream, peanut butter and vanilla. Stir until well blended.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan. I spray my pan with Pam. Can use chocolate chips instead of peanut butter.

title: coffee cake
directions: Blend cake mix, eggs, pudding, oil and sour cream at medium speed for 2 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients in a small bowl. Put half of the batter in a greased pan; sprinkle half of nut mixture on top.
Spread remaining batter and sprinkle on rest of nut mixture.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: alma's tea cakes
directions: Stir ingredients well, then add flour to mixture.
Dip up by spoonfuls and space on a cookie sheet.
Bake until light brown at 350°.

title: soup
directions: Brown hamburger meat; drain.
Add all ingredients.
Cook for 1 hour on low heat.

title: deviled eggs
directions: Boil however many eggs you like.
Mix mustard and mayonnaise and salt and pepper with the mashed egg yolks.
Use a little more mustard than mayonnaise.
Stir really well, until smooth and creamy.
Scoop into eggs and sprinkle with paprika.

title: stuffed hot peppers
directions: Wash and deseed peppers.
Cut in half.
Put in container of cold water and
soak
for
4 or more hours (if time permits; this makes them
crisp).
Drain
on paper towel and fill peppers.

title: ranch potato salad
directions: Wash, cook and cube potatoes.
Mix in another bowl the Hidden Valley Ranch, water and mayonnaise.
Mix well.
Add to potatoes. Toss in celery, eggs and onion.
Chill.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: raw vegetable dip
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Chill several hours or overnight. Serve with raw vegetables.

title: "divine" chicken divan*
directions: *Low in calories because "cream sauce" is made from chicken broth.

title: coconut pie
directions: Mix flour and sugar. Mix egg yolks and water.
Combine with flour and sugar.
Add margarine.
Cook until thick.
Add coconut. Pour into a pie shell.
Add meringue and brown real good.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Beat together first 7 ingredients until blended.
Then, with a large spoon, add last 3 ingredients.
Pour into a well-greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan or tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes in 9 x 13-inch pan; 45 minutes to 1 hour in tube pan.
A glaze may be used, if desired.

title: pie pastry
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Yields 2-crust, 8 to 9-inch pie.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Brown hamburger; drain.
Add soup and stir.
Put into baking dish and top with Tater Tots.
Bake according to directions for baking Tater Tots.

title: pasta with clams
directions: In a medium saute pan, pour just enough olive oil to coat the bottom.
Saute garlic and red and green peppers on low heat.
Cover and stir occasionally for about 8 minutes or until peppers are soft.

title: easy fresh peach cobbler
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Combine peaches and 1/2 cup sugar; allow standing until sugar dissolves. Melt butter in an 11 x 7-inch baking dish in the microwave. In small bowl, stir together 1/2 cup sugar, flour, baking powder and milk; stir until just mixed and then pour over butter. DO NOT STIR! Spoon peaches over top. Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes.

title: rice salad
directions: Cook rice in chicken broth for 15 minutes.
Cool.
Chop and dice next 6 items.
Mix with marinade juice.
May use brown rice, it's a healthy choice.

title: hot apple cider punch
directions: Pour apple cider and ginger ale into a 30 cup percolator. Place candies and remaining ingredients in percolator basket. Perk through complete cycle of percolator.
Serve hot.
Yield:
1 1/4 gallons.

title: dip for wings
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Chill before serving.

title: pasta and beans
directions: Saute garlic in oil.
Crush tomatoes; add to pan, along with bay leaves.
Cook for about 45 minutes.
Add undrained beans and ditalini.
Heat over low heat about 15 to 20 minutes longer. Serve in bowls with grated cheese.

title: shipwreck
directions: Layer the potatoes, onions, celery and rice in a large greased casserole, salting each layer.
Season ground chuck with onion and garlic salts, cumin, chili powder, pepper and salt to taste and egg.
Mix well and pat layer of meat over the vegetables.
Add kidney beans.
Spread the tomato soup.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 1 1/2 hours, uncovering during the last 30 minutes.

title: coconut pie
directions: Beat eggs.
Add all remaining ingredients.
Stir until well blended.
Bake at 325° until set.
Makes 2 pies.

title: nut pimento sandwich
directions: Combine pimento, cheese, eggs and nuts. Add enough mayonnaise to moisten to spreading consistency. Spread butter and pimento filling on bread. Makes about 20 sandwiches.

title: greek tomato salad
directions: The longer this stands at room temperature, the better.

title: shrimp scampi
directions: Peel and devein shrimp.
Set aside.
Cook onion and garlic in butter in a large skillet over medium heat, stirring constantly 3 or 4 minutes.
Add tarragon and next 4 ingredients.
Bring to a boil.
Add shrimp and cook, stirring constantly 5 to 6 minutes or until shrimp turns pink.
Sprinkle with parsley.
Serve over fettucine.
Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: pecan coconut balls
directions: Mix all ingredients, except chocolate chips and paraffin.
Mold into balls and lay on wax paper.
Melt chocolate chips and paraffin.
Dip balls into chocolate and put on wax paper until dry.

title: microwave turtle cake
directions: Mix cake, eggs and water with electric mixer.
Fold in (by hand) the sour cream.
Place cone in 3-quart pan.
Spread pecans on bottom.
Pour in batter.
Drizzle caramel topping on batter without touching sides or cone.

title: pork and green chile casserole
directions: Cut pork into bite size strips.
In a large skillet, stir-fry pork in hot oil until no longer pink.
Drain.
Return all meat to skillet.
Stir in remaining ingredients except cheese.
Heat and stir until bubbly; pour into a 2-quart casserole or cook in Dutch oven for 25 minutes or until rice is tender.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake 3 to 4 minutes more until cheese is melted.

title: junk yard salad
directions: Mix well and refrigerate overnight.

title: amazin raisin cake
directions: Grease and flour 2 (9-inch) round baking pans or 9 x 13-inch pan.
In large bowl, with mixer at low speed, beat first 8 ingredients 2 minutes, scraping bowl frequently.
Batter will be thick.
With spoon, stir in apples, raisins and nuts.
Spoon batter into pans.
Bake in a 350° oven for 45 minutes or until tester comes out clean.
Cool in pans 10 minutes.
Remove and cool.
Fill and frost with whipping cream.

title: five cup fruit salad
directions: Stir all ingredients together and refrigerate.
Prepare the day before serving.

title: easy shrimp soup
directions: Saute onions in butter until tender.
Mix milk and soup together.
Add the onions.
Add thawed shrimp to mixture.
Then add dash of salt, pepper and 1 tablespoon of parsley.
Cook until hot, stirring occasionally.

title: indiana sugar pie(poor man's pie)
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Blend the flour, butter, sugar and salt in a food processor until well combined and smooth, about 5 seconds.
Pour into the pie shell.
Add the cream and mix gently with your fingers, being careful not to break through the bottom of the crust.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Cook syrup, sugar and water until it "hairs".
Put in peanuts and cook slowly until it's a golden brown.
Remove from heat and add soda and vanilla.
Pour onto buttered platter.

title: burritos
directions: Brown ground beef.
Drain grease.
Add Chili-O mix and beans and mix.
Serve in tortillas, rolling them.
You can add onions, cheese, sour cream or anything you like before rolling.

title: cornbread deluxe
directions: In mixing bowl blend in oil, egg, sugar, milk, baking powder, salt and 1/2 teaspoon dill seed.
Mix well.
Add cornmeal and flour, mixing thoroughly.
Gently mix in the chopped meat and cheese.
Pour into greased and floured muffin tins or loaf pans. Fill halfway and sprinkle with remaining dill seed.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes or when medium brown at 375°.
Start testing with a toothpick for doneness.
Do not overbake.

title: orange balls
directions: Mix together well.
Form into balls.
Roll balls in coconut.

title: cheese potatoes
directions: Boil potatoes in skins, then peel and dice.
Heat soup, onion, butter and cheese.
Add sour cream.
Pour over diced potatoes. Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: caramel pecan french toast souffle
directions: In a saucepan, combine brown sugar, butter and corn syrup. Cook, stirring constantly, until sugar is dissolved. Add pecans, mix well.

title: spicy hot cocoa
directions: Combine cocoa, sugar, cinnamon, nutmeg and salt in a saucepan. Blend in hot water.
Bring to a boil over medium heat, stirring constantly.
Boil and stir 2 minutes.
Add milk; heat to serving temperature, stirring occasionally.
Do not boil.
Remove from heat and add vanilla.
Whip until foamy.
Garnish with cinnamon sticks.
Serve hot.

title: great grandma's molasses cookies
directions: Combine all except flour.
Mix quite stiff.
Roll out on floured surface and cut out shapes.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 325° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: joe's chili
directions: Saute salt pork, ground pork, suet, beef, onions, garlic, peppers and celery until meat is cooked.
Add remaining ingredients except beans.
Simmer 1 hour.
Add beans.
Cook another 20 minutes. Stir gently.

title: french coconut pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into pie shell.
Bake in 350° oven for about 35 minutes.

title: chicken broccoli casserole
directions: Place cooked broccoli in bottom of 3-quart casserole.
Cover with chicken.
Combine rest of ingredients and pour over chicken. Then sprinkle another 1/4 pound of grated cheese over top and cover with buttered Pepperidge Farm crumbs.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.

title: broccoli and ham casserole
directions: Cook broccoli 2 minutes in boiling salted water.
Drain well. Mix soup, milk, mayonnaise, egg, cheese, onion, ham and noodles together.
Add salt and pepper to suit your taste.
Stir in broccoli and pour the mixture into a lightly buttered 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Combine the butter and crackers to add as a topping to mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: apple cake
directions: You will need a 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook and drain broccoli.
Put rice in boiling water and let stand 5 minutes.
Saute onions in oleo. Add milk to mushroom soup and heat.
Then mix with other ingredients.
Pour in casserole and cover with grated cheese.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: good green beans
directions: To cooked green beans, add remaining ingredients.
May choose to add garlic and cooked mushrooms.

title: ground beef 'n tater casserole
directions: Brown beef in skillet; drain. Combine beef, green beans, soup, water, salt and pepper.
Pour into a 1 1/2-quart casserole.

title: nacho dip
directions: Heat chili and cheese until cheese melts.
Add olives and salsa.
Serve warm with chips.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Mix pretzels, margarine and 3 teaspoons sugar in bowl; press mixture into a 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake 10 minutes at 350°; let cool. Mix cream cheese, whipped topping and 1 cup sugar until very creamy. Mix gelatin with boiling water and add fresh fruit. Refrigerate until gelatin begins to set.
Add gelatin to top of cream cheese mixture.

title: chocolate caramel brownies
directions: In large bowl, combine cake mix and nuts.
Cut in butter. Stir in 1/2 cup evaporated milk.
Spread 1/2 batter in greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 15 minutes.

title: chocolate bark cookies
directions: Line a jelly roll pan with tinfoil.
Spray with Pam.
Place saltines on top of foil.
Bring margarine and sugar to a boil; boil for 1 minute.
Pour over crackers.
Bake at 350° for 5 to 6 minutes, until light caramel color.
Remove from oven.
Pour chocolate chips over top.
Spread evenly as they melt.
Sprinkle chopped nuts over top.
Chill or freeze, then peel off tinfoil and break into pieces.

title: jello two-tone salad
directions: Dissolve lemon jello in 1 c. hot water. While still hot, add cream cheese and stir well. When starting to jell, add crushed pineapple with
juice and whipped cream. Pour into oblong pan. Let set until firm. Take 1 cup apricot nectar, (hot) and pour over orange jello with one cup hot water. When cold pour over top of first mixture.

title: blueberry crisp
directions: Combine all ingredients except blueberries.
Blend well with pastry blender.
Press 2/3 of mixture into greased glass baking pan (large size, at least 13 x 9-inches).
Top with blueberries that have been washed and picked over.
Cover with remaining oatmeal mixture.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serve warm with ice cream.
Serves 8.

title: 15-pound dark fruit cake
directions: Mix butter, sugar and eggs in a large bowl.
Mix in another large bowl the flour, baking powder and nutmeg.
Cut fruit into small pieces and roll all pieces and nuts in 1 cup flour.
Add butter, egg and sugar mixture.
Mix well.
Add pineapple juice. Add remaining ingredients and blend well.
Pour into pans.
Bake at 275° for 3 hours or until done.

title: overnight lettuce salad
directions: Cut the lettuce, onion and eggs.
Put the first 4 ingredients in a 9 x 13-inch pan in the order given.
Mix salad dressing and sugar; spread over entire top.
Put Cheddar cheese on top of salad dressing.
Sprinkle bacon bits on top.
Be sure to wash vegetables and dry well on paper towel.

title: shrimp casserole for a crowd
directions: Combine chopped pepper, celery, onion and water and cook until vegetables are tender.
Drain.
Add pimentos, shrimp, crabmeat and eggs.
Make cheese sauce:
melt butter and stir in flour until smooth.
Gradually add cream and cook until mixture thickens, stirring constantly.
Add cheese, salt and pepper.
Add sauce to shrimp mixture and put in 3-quart casserole dish.
Sprinkle crumbs over top and bake at 400° for 15 minutes.
Yields 12 to 15 servings.

title: sue's texas corn muffins
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease bottom only of 12 muffin cups. Lightly spoon flour into measuring cup and level off.
In medium bowl combine flour, cornmeal, sugar, baking powder and salt.
Mix well.
Stir in bacon and corn.

title: grandmom's marinara sauce
directions: Coat bottom of cooking pan with olive oil.
Add and cook garlic cloves until brown.
Slowly add crushed tomatoes, water, salt, oregano, parsley and white pepper.
Cook on low heat for 15 minutes, stirring.
Add tomato paste; stir well.
Shake Italian seasoning on top.
Cook on low heat; stir.
The longer you cook it the better it tastes. After adding meat balls to sauce, add 2 tablespoons grated cheese on top.

title: orange slice cake
directions: Cream the butter and sugar. Add eggs, one at a time.
Add soda, flour and buttermilk.
Chop candy, dates and pecans and dust with flour. Add this to mixture and coconut to the other mixture. Bake at 275° or 300° for 2 1/2 hours in tube pan.

title: cinnamon play dough
directions: Combine dry ingredients in saucepan.
Add water and oil; mix. Cook a few minutes over medium-high heat (stir constantly) until it forms a ball.

title: joe's special
directions: In heavy skillet, saute onion and garlic in oil. Add beef. Brown thoroughly and pour off fat if necessary. Sprinkle in salt and pepper. Add spinach, keeping heat high. Add eggs and stir constantly until cooked. Serve immediately on warmed platter surrounded by a ring of French fries.

title: sour cream cheddar biscuits
directions: Preheat oven to 400°. Combine butter, sour cream and cheese. Stir in flour. Drop batter by teaspoonfuls into ungreased mini-muffin pans. Bake 15 minutes or until brown. Remove from pan immediately.

title: crunchy sausage casserole
directions: Cook rice mixture and set aside.
Cook sausage, beef and onion until brown.
Drain.
Add rice, mushrooms, chopped chestnuts, soy sauce.
Stir well.
Spoon into an ungreased 2 quart casserole. Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Bake uncovered at 325° for 50 minutes.
If ready to eat now, bake uncovered at 300° for 20 minutes.

title: beef burgundy
directions: Place beef and soup in casserole.
Mix together.
Pour wine over all.
Cover and bake at 375° for 10 minutes.
Reduce heat to 325°.
Bake for 2 1/2 to 3 hours.
Serve with rice, noodles or potatoes.

title: hot cranberry punch
directions: Boil water and sugar.
Add tea bags, let stand for 6 minutes. Remove bags.
Add cloves and cinnamon sticks.
Cover and let stand for 30 minutes.
Remove spices.
Add jello and juices.

title: sausage stuffing
directions: Mix together and put
into
greased loaf pan.
Bake for approximately 35 to 45 minutes.

title: caramel corn(microwave)
directions: In a
1 1/2-quart casserole dish, combine the first 4 ingredients.
Place in the microwave and bring to a boil (about 1 minute and 45 seconds).
Continue to boil 2 minutes on High. Remove and stir in soda.
Place corn in brown grocery bag; pour syrup over corn.
Close bag and shake.
Cook in bag in microwave 1 1/2 minutes on High.
Shake again.
Cook 1 1/2 minutes.
Tear open bag and spread corn out.
It will be sticky and hot.
Let it cool and enjoy!

title: lemonade pie
directions: Combine milk, thawed lemonade and softened Cool Whip.
Pour into graham cracker crust.
Refrigerate until served.
This pie freezes well.
If you double the recipe, it will make 3 (8-inch) pies.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Pour boiling water over oatmeal and cool. Cream the shortening and sugars. Add eggs and cooled oatmeal.
Add sifted dry ingredients and vanilla. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Cream butter, sugar and sour cream.
Put eggs in one at a time and beat well.
Add other ingredients.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes and at 350° until done, approximately 1 hour and 15 minutes (the cake will bake for 1 hour and 45 minutes total or until done).

title: cap'n crunch bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease 13 x 9-inch pan.
Crush 4 cups of cereal with bottom of a cup in the baking pan.
Spread evenly a layer of peanuts, raisins, chocolate pieces and the remaining 2 cups cereal.
Drizzle sweetened condensed milk evenly over mixture. Bake 20 to 25 minutes, or until golden brown.
Kids love them.

title: fresh peach parfait pie
directions: In medium bowl, pour hot water over Jell-O.
Stir until dissolved.
Add ice cream and stir well.
Stir in peach slices and pour into crust.
Freeze 3 hours or until set.
Yum!

title: cornbread salad
directions: Make Ranch Mixture by combining mayonnaise, cream cheese and Ranch dressing mix.
Set aside.
Prepare cornbread using 2 cups meal and green chilies (use your favorite recipe); cool and crumble.
Then halve the ingredients and prepare as follows:

1/2 cornbread, 1 can pinto beans, 2 chopped tomatoes, 1/4 cup green pepper, 1/4 cup green onion, 1 can whole kernel corn, 5 slices crumbled bacon, 3/4 cup shredded Cheddar cheese and 3/4 cup Ranch Mixture.
Begin again with cornbread and layer again but reverse order of last 3 ingredients (bacon, Cheddar cheese and Ranch Mixture).
Chill at least 3 hours before serving.
Better after 24 hours.
Top with bacon and cheese just before serving.

title: homemade noodles
directions: Combine beaten eggs, salt and cream.
Add enough flour to make stiff dough.
Roll out very thin on a floured surface and let stand 1 hour.
Roll up with flour and cut in strips 1/8-inch thick.
Spread out and let dry at least 3 hours.
Cook 10 minutes or until done.

title: orange garlic salad
directions: Peel oranges, remove pulp and place slices in a mixing bowl. Peel and slice garlic to taste.
Add garlic to oranges with salt. Cover with vegetable oil.
Let set at room temperature for 2 hours.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Grease 12 to 14 muffin tins.
Cream the butter and sugar in a large bowl.
Add eggs one at a time.
Beat well.
Combine flours, baking powder and salt.
Add alternately to creamed mixture with milk and vanilla.
Fold berries into batter. Spoon into muffin tins.
Bake 30 minutes.
Cool in pan 5 minutes. Turn onto wire rack to completely cool.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix together egg, sugar, cinnamon and melted margarine.
Add to drained potatoes and toss gently.

title: italian biscotte(biscuits)
directions: Cream sugar and oil.
Add eggs and beat well.
Add flavoring and anise seed.
